title: shrimp creole
directions: Make roux of flour and cooking oil. Add onions, bell peppers and garlic and cook until soft. Add tomatoes and tomato paste. Mix well and cook about 5 minutes. Add about 6 cups water and the rest of the seasonings. Let simmer for 1 hour. Add shrimp and cook for 15 minutes. Add parsley and continue to cook until sauce is thick. Serve over hot rice.

title: tijuana torte
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Drain.
Add stewed tomatoes, sauce and taco seasoning.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Place 2 tortillas side by side in baking dish.
Put meat mixture on top of tortillas, then sprinkle with cheese (about 3 large tablespoons of mixture on each layer).
Repeat until each stack has 6 tortillas.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Add sour cream and sliced tomatoes on top.

title: green pea salad
directions: Stir together the first 7 ingredients, toss well. Mix mayonnaise and sour cream together. Toss pea mixture with mayonnaise and sour cream mixture. Serve immediately. You can sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, if desired. Serves 10-15.

title: potato casserole
directions: Use amounts of ingredients to your preference.
Cut up potatoes.
Cut up sausage.
Put all in baking dish.
Put butter all over top.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° until potatoes are soft.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese all over top.
Put back in oven; melt cheese.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa
and
cornstarch real good in a double boiler.
Add the milk
and	mix well.
Add the egg yolks, beat with a beater until mixed good.
Add vanilla, salt and butter. Cook in the double boiler until thick.
Stir often.
Pour into pie crust.

title: river black duck(modern)
directions: Chop shallots and carrots.
Brown ducks and shallots in a large frying pan until all blood is cooked.
Pour some fat into roasting pan; add carrots, juniper
and cherries.
Place ducks on top of mixture and roast at 350° for 3 hours,
basting often.

title: rosemary chicken
directions: Pound chicken to 1/2-inch thickness.
Sprinkle each piece of chicken with rosemary, garlic salt and pepper.
Heat olive oil in skillet over medium heat.
Add chicken and cook until done. Chicken should be lightly brown.
Serve with rice.

title: chocolate chip pudding cookies
directions: Mix flour with baking soda.
Combine butter, the sugars, pudding mix and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat until smooth and creamy. Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Then stir in chips and nuts.
Drop by rounded spoonful onto ungreased baking sheet, about 2-inches apart.
Makes about 7 dozen cookies.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: special chicken
directions: Beat eggs and milk.
Place chicken in egg mixture.
Marinate in refrigerator 2 to 4 hours.
Turn chicken every 30 minutes.
Remove chicken from marinade and roll in crumbs.
Brown in butter.
Place chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover with cheese slices and mushrooms.
Heat oven to 350°.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes. Sprinkle with wine twice during baking.
Serve with wild rice. Serves 8 people.

title: mushroom soup
directions: Wash and chop mushrooms; add with onion and cook in stock about 20 minutes.
Then rub through a sieve.
Reheat and add thickening; then milk and cream which have been heated in a double boiler.
Serve very hot with a little whipped cream.

title: carrot oatmeal muffins
directions: In a large bowl, mix together flour, brown sugar, sugar, baking powder, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon and oatmeal; set aside.
In a small bowl, mix together milk, butter and eggs.
Add wet mixture to dry mixture and blend.
Stir in carrots.
Bake in muffin cups or greased pan for 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
You may sprinkle with brown sugar before baking.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: ozark skillet breakfast
directions: In a large cast-iron skillet, fry bacon until crispy.
Remove bacon and crumble.
In bacon drippings, brown potatoes, onion and peppers.
Drain excess drippings.
Pour eggs on top; add crumbled bacon.
Cover and cook over medium-low fire.
After eggs begin to firm, add grated cheese.
Cook until eggs are done.
Top with sour cream.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Be creative!
Add what you like best.
But, remember, cook slow so you don't scorch the eggs.

title: slush
directions: Boil 3 cups sugar and 6 cups water until sugar is dissolved. Cool.
Add juices and freeze.
Scoop into glasses and mix with 7-Up.

title: the fry's orange jello salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese and dry jello until well blended.
Add drained fruit.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Chill.
Does not keep well overnight.

title: thanksgiving stuffing
directions: Add barbecue sauce to leftover meats and serve as sandwiches.

title: no egg chocolate cake
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together.
Add vanilla and vinegar last.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 9-inch square pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: crispy chicken rolls
directions: Place each chicken breast on a sheet of wax paper.
Flatten chicken to 1/4-inch thickness, using a mallet or rolling pin. Combine shrimp, butter, onion and 3/4 teaspoon salt; spoon 1/4 cup mixture in center of each chicken breast.
Roll up lengthwise, and secure with a wooden pick.
Cover and refrigerate 15 minutes. Combine 1 cup flour, baking powder, salt and water.
Dredge each chicken roll in flour, and coat with batter.
Fry in 1 inch hot oil (375°) in a large skillet about 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Drain thoroughly on paper towels.
Serve immediately. Yields 6 servings.

title: cold cucumber soup
directions: Mix all ingredients together in blender and blend well.
Pour into a large bowl, cover and chill.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: chili bean dip
directions: Mash beans with reserved cooking liquid until no large bean pieces remain.
Stir in vinegar, chili powder, cumin, onion, parsley and salsa.
Mix well.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Drain tuna. Cook noodles and drain. Add tuna, noodles, onions and celery.
Blend next 5 ingredients. Spoon half of the mixture into a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish. Top with zucchini.
Repeat 1 layer at a time.
Top last layer of zucchini with cheese. Bake about 30 minutes at 325°.
After removing from oven, add diced tomatoes.

title: bubba's cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 375° to 400°.
Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Diced hot pepper can be added if desired.

title: mama de carmine's sausage bread
directions: Take sausage, remove from casing and fry.
Mix with fried peppers.
On floured surface, roll out pizza dough no thicker than 1/4-inch.
Spread cooled mixture of sausage and peppers all over dough.
Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese, parsley, garlic powder, pepper and Mozzarella cheese all over.
Roll down from top edge.
Place on ungreased baking pan.
Brush with beaten egg yolk for shine.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: my man cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Mix in medium size saucepan the flour into melted butter; cook 5 minutes until dark brown, stirring constantly.
Add paprika, salt and pepper; cook for 3 minutes.
Add finely chopped green pepper, onion and garlic.
Cook slowly for 5 minutes.
Add lemon juice and Worcestershire to oysters which have been picked over and heated in their own liquor.
Pour mixture into baking dish. Sprinkle fine cracker crumbs over top.
Bake 30 minutes in 375° to 400° oven.

title: sweet potato delight
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into buttered baking dish.

title: chuck wagon stew
directions: Combine
sugar and flour.
Coat beef with flour mixture and brown
in
hot
shortening.
Add seasonings, tomatoes and broth to	meat.
Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Stir in vegetables,
except
peas, cover and cook 30 minutes.
Add peas and cool for 15 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Mix zucchini with onion and salt.
Let stand overnight; drain and rinse 3 times.
Then add vinegar, sugar, mustard, celery seed, black pepper, turmeric, cornstarch and nutmeg.
Cook slow until clear or about 45 minutes.

title: ruffann tuna fish salad
directions: Mix with salt and pepper mixture to taste and maybe onion and garlic powder added to a somewhat lumpy mixture.
Serves two.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients; bring to a boil and cool.

title: sweet, sour pineapple glaze
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer 5 minutes.
Spoon small amount slowly over ham during last 45 minutes of baking.
Enough for large ham.
Spoon glaze on frequently to build up a high gloss.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese., Stir well.
Pour into baking dish (2-quart) and cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peppernuts
directions: Move
lower
rack in oven up 1 notch.
Beat eggs, sugar and shortening	until
fluffy.	Add
milk and dry ingredients alternately.
Drop	by
teaspoonfuls on cookie sheets and bake in 450° about 8 minutes or until slightly brown on top.

title: cream pull candy
directions: Combine all ingredients in a deep, heavy pan (at least 10 inches deep).
Heat and stir only until sugar dissolves.
Wipe down sides with a damp cloth and let boil without stirring for 15 to 20 minutes, until it cracks on side of glass of cold water or candy thermometer is 250 degrees.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Fix rice according to package.
Mix broccoli and rice.
Add Cheez Whiz, soup and mushrooms.
Mix well.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: salsa dip
directions: Using an electric mixer, mix all ingredients until blended. Place in 1-quart casserole dish.
Cover; bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serve with taco chips.

title: chocolate cake - good
directions: Mix together and bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: salmon stew or fish
directions: Saute onions and potatoes in bacon grease or fat back until done.
Then add the rest of the ingredients and let come to a boil, stirring so it won't stick to pot.
Then turn down and let simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: margaret's special treats(homemade twix bars)
directions: Unwrap caramels.
Put caramels on microwave plate and put in microwave about 2 minutes to soften.
Put 1 caramel between 2 Ritz crackers.
Melt chocolate.
Cover entire cracker (with caramel) with the chocolate to make a candy bar.
Place in a cool place for chocolate to get firm.

title: pineapple marshmallow pie
directions: Heat until melted, then let it get cold.
Then beat a tall can of ice cold Milnot until whipped.
Add the marshmallow mix and beat well.
Add 1 cup chopped pecans.
Pour in graham cracker crust and chill.
Makes 2 pies.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Put Jell-O and pudding mixtures in large saucepan.
Add 3 cups cold water.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cook until it thickens.
Let cool, then stir in Cool Whip and mandarin oranges. Refrigerate.

title: crisco pound cake
directions: You can put all of this in one bowl at the same time; mix on high speed very well.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chili-topped potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes and rub with oil.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until done.
Cook ground beef, onion and garlic in a large skillet until beef is browned, stirring to crumble.
Drain well.
Add next 5 ingredients; reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes or until thickened.

title: chicken and dressing bake
directions: In a 1-quart saucepan over high heat, heat water and butter to boiling.
In large bowl, pour hot water over stuffing mix.
Toss to mix well.
Pat 1/2 of the stuffing mix into the bottom of a 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
In a second bowl, stir together soup, mayo, milk, chicken, celery, broccoli and seasoning until well mixed. Spoon evenly over stuffing mix; top with remaining stuffing.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 5 minutes more or until cheese is melted.
Makes 6 servings.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Combine crushed pretzels, margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar; mix well.
Press into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven and let cool completely.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Rinse kraut well with cold water; drain.
Cut onion, pepper and celery fine.
Mix oil, vinegar, sugar and water with ingredients.
Will keep several weeks in refrigerator.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: jefferson davis pie
directions: Cream the
butter
and	sugar.	Beat
in the egg yolks. Sift, then add the flour, cinnamon, nutmeg and allspice.	Add the remaining ingredients.
Fill the pie shell.
Bake at 300° for
40 minutes, or until set.
When cool, top with meringue. Bake meringue according to directions.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender.
Blend well.
Chill overnight.

title: caramel sticky buns
directions: Combine brown sugar, butter or margarine, salt and
corn syrup in a small saucepan. Cook over low heat until mixture comes to boiling. Bubble 1 minute. Remove from heat. Cool.
Spoon mixture into each of 12 large muffin pan cups.
Separate rolls.
Place 1 roll in each muffin cup. Bake in a hot oven at 400° for 15 minutes or until golden.
Let cool 5 minutes in cups. Turn out onto wire rack and cool.

title: 7 layered salad
directions: Put layers in this
order in 9 x 13-inch pan:
lettuce, peas, radishes, green
onions and cucumbers.
Mix Miracle Whip and sour cream.
Seal
in
lettuce and vegetables with Miracle Whip mixture.
Top with cheese and bacon.

title: taco dip
directions: Layer all ingredients in order listed. Use a 9 x 11-inch pan. Bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes or until cheese is fully melted.
Dip with nacho chips.

title: cheese krispies
directions: Soften margarine; add cheese and mix well.
Add other ingredients and mix.
Roll in marble size balls and place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Flatten balls with palm of hand. Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 dozen.

title: rich chocolate cake
directions: Combine oil, cocoa and sugar in mixing bowl; beat on low speed until well mixed.
Add eggs; beat on medium speed until well blended.
Add salt, buttermilk, flour and vanilla.
Add to mixture on low speed until combined, then beat on high speed for 2 minutes.
Add soda to hot water; dissolve well.
Add gradually to cake batter; mix just until combined.
(Batter will be very thin before baking.)
Bake in greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan (or two layer pans) at 375° for 40 minutes.
Test with toothpick in center of cake for doneness.
Frost with Chocolate Fudge Frosting, if desired.

title: zucchini bake(microwave)
directions: Microwave first 4 ingredients for 10 minutes on High.
Add the remaining items and cook for 10 to 15 minutes in microwave.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti until tender. Add salt and pepper. Rinse and drain. Cook sugar, egg and vinegar. Bring to a boil. Pour liquid over spaghetti while hot. Add chopped and sliced vegetables. Chill.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Cook sugar, vanilla and milk until it boils and becomes thick. Add peanut butter and marshmallow cream.
Stir until well mixed. Pour into a buttered 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Cool before cutting.

title: potato casserole
directions: Pour frozen potatoes into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt 1 stick margarine and mix into potatoes.
Mix sour cream and soup together in a bowl, then mix into potatoes.
Mix corn flakes and 1/2 stick melted margarine together and spread over potatoes.
Cover with foil.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: texas caviar
directions: Stir together. Cover and chill, stirring occasionally, for 8 hours.

title: tex-mex barbecue pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Bring 4 cups of water to a boil in a large saucepan over high heat.
Add chicken.
Cover.
Remove from heat and let stand 15 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink in center.
Drain and cut into small cubes.
If recommended cooking time for crust is longer than 5 to 7 minutes, prebake crust until this amount of time remains.
Combine barbecue sauce, onion and lemon juice in small bowl.
Spread over crust, leaving 1/2 inch border.
Top with chicken.
Sprinkle cheese evenly over top.
Bake 5 to 7 minutes or until cheese begins to brown.
Cut pizza into 8 wedges and top with cilantro.

title: one hour rolls
directions: A good many husbands are spoiled by mismanagement so are not tender!
Some women keep them in hot water, some freeze them, keep them stewing or keep them in a pickle.
Husbands are really quite delicious when properly treated.
Since selection is important, do not be guided by silvery appearance...You are not buying a mackerel!
And do not look for the golden tint as you would in a salmon.
Tastes differ, so do not allow others to select for you and do not look for a husband in the marketplaces.
Add sugar, but no vinegar and he will keep as long as you want.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, water and cornstarch until thick.
Add strawberry jello.
Cool this mixture slightly.

title: blanc mange
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar and water in pan.
Stirring, cook until mixture thickens like pudding.
Remove from heat and add vanilla. Pour into desert dishes.
Cover and place in fridge until set.

title: baked stuffed fish
directions: Have fish boned and cleaned for stuffing.
Wash and salt it 1/2 hour before stuffing it.
Wash it again.
Pat it dry.
Place in baking pan.

title: autumn apple pancakes
directions: Wash apples.
Leaving skins on, either grate them or finely chop them (1 cup chunky applesauce may be substituted for grated apples).
Mix all ingredients except oil.
Mix until smooth.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Mix margarine, salt, cheese, egg, milk and onion.
Blend with rice.
Add broccoli.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake and 1/2 can of milk.
Pour 1/2 of the cake mixture in a greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake 5 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate ice cream(makes 2 quarts)
directions: Melt the chocolate in a double boiler.
Add the salt, milk and sugar; scald thoroughly.
Beat to blend the mixture.
Separate the eggs and pour a little of this mixture over the beaten egg yolks. Return all to the double boiler and cook until slightly thickened. Chill.
Add flavorings.
Fold in the egg whites, beaten stiff, then the whipped cream.
Freeze.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and dark syrup; add enough milk to mix good. Cook until it forms a soft ball.
Then add butter, vanilla and peanut butter.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cut squash into small pieces.
Blend together squash, sour cream and cream of chicken soup.
Mix stuffing with margarine and spread half of crumbs in 9 x 13-inch pan/casserole dish.
Spread squash mixture over this and top with remaining buttered crumbs. Bake uncovered at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.
Casserole can be topped with shredded cheese, if desired.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Cut spareribs between every third rib about halfway through the strip.
Salt and pepper them. Place ribs in a shallow roasting pan and bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Pour off all excess fat after baking.

title: chili and beans
directions: Brown meat; add tomato paste and onion.
Mix.
Add beans; do not drain.
Mix well.
Add chili powder to taste.
Simmer for 1 hour or longer.
To serve, add grated cheese and salsa, if desired.
Delicious with garlic bread, corn muffins or tortilla chips.

title: taco dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and spread on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Chop onion and jalapeno pepper.
Cover cream cheese mixture.
Add layer of chili followed by a layer of salsa.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Sprinkle cheese on top.

title: mississippi fudge cake
directions: Melt oleo; let cool to warm.
Add eggs.
Mix and add flour, cocoa and sugar.
Add coconut and pecans.
Bake 25 minutes at 350° in a greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch pan.
While cake is hot, spread jar of marshmallow cream on top.
Let cool before icing.

title: green bean salad
directions: Melt sugar in vinegar on low heat.
Mix in other ingredients. Add vinegar mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: kneophla and potato soup
directions: Mix flour, egg, baking powder, salt and water to make stiff dough.
Set aside to rest.
Cover.
Peel and dice potatoes and onion; dice celery.
Put in large enough kettle and add enough water so you can add the kneophla.
When boiling real good cut kneophla with scissors, making them as big as a large lima bean. Boil about 15 to 20 minutes.
Add milk or half and half, salt and seasoning to desired taste.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes 1/2-inch thick.
Dip first in egg; then in cornmeal, salt and pepper mixture.
Fry in hot oil until browned on both sides.

title: mother's sally lunn
directions: Add sugar to beaten egg yolks.
Mix other dry ingredients; mix alternately with milk into egg and sugar mixture, then add melted butter.
Beat egg whites until stiff (not dry); fold in.
Bake in well-greased oblong or square pan or muffin tins.
For the loaf, allow 40 minutes in moderate oven (350°).

title: corn flake candy
directions: Put corn flakes in large container.
Put in saucepan peanut butter, white syrup and sugar.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Pour over corn flakes.
Mix good until corn flakes are coated.
Roll in balls (dampen hands).
Place on wax paper.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine all ingredients well. Chill thoroughly before serving.

title: hearty healthy chicken fettuccine primavera
directions: Saute onions and garlic in oil until tender.
Mix together cornstarch, Mrs. Dash, pepper and broth.
Stir into onion mixture. Bring to boil, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add vegetables and chicken.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes, until hot. Spoon over cooked pasta.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: lemon bread pudding
directions: Cut the slices of bread into 1/2-inch cubes.
Heat the butter in a frypan and fry the bread cubes until golden brown.
Put them in a baking dish.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Put cookie dough in pizza pan, roll and bake according to package.
Beat Cool Whip, cream cheese and powdered sugar together.
Spread on cooled cookie crust and top with fresh fruit of your choice.

title: strawberry angel food yogurt
directions: Crumble up the cake. Add yogurt (need to be melting), Cool Whip and strawberries, stirring well. Put in baking dish for slicing or in bowl and freeze.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour, Crisco and salt together until the consistency of coarse meal.
Mix egg, cold water and vinegar together and add to flour mixture.
Shape into 3 balls.
Roll out on a lightly floured board (or flat surface).
Use for favorite fillings and bake accordingly.
For fruit filled crust with top, bake at 425° for 10 minutes and reduce heat to 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Milk can be brushed on top of the crust the last 10 minutes of baking to give pies a glazed look.

title: raisin toppers
directions: Combine raisins, 1/2 cup brown sugar, flour, salt and 1/3 cup water.
Cook, stirring until thick.
Remove from heat and stir in lemon juice.
Cool.
Sift flour, salt, 1 1/2 cups brown sugar and soda.
Cut in shortening.
Stir in oats, water and lemon rind. Blend.
Form balls, 1 tablespoon each.
Put on greased baking sheet.
Dent center with thumb.
Fill with raisin mixture.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Cool on wire rack. Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: cabbage salad
directions: One Day Before:
Mix dressing and refrigerate.

title: confetti salad
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together.
Mix sugar and vinegar and bring to a boil for 1 or 2 minutes.
Pour over sauerkraut mixture.
Make a few hours ahead of time.
Even better if made the night before.

title: nadines chocolate frosting
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well.
Add boiling water.
Mix well. Add enough powdered sugar for right consistency to spread.

title: rice casserole
directions: Cut up margarine in bottom of casserole pan.
Add rest of ingredients and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken kiev (baked)
directions: In small bowl, combine butter, chives, garlic and 1/4 teaspoon each salt and pepper; mix until blended.
Spoon onto plastic wrap; shape into 2-inch squares.
Freeze 30 minutes.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat the eggs.
Add sugar, cornstarch and nutmeg.
Mix well. Add milk.
Pour into unbaked crust and bake at least 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mayonnaise cake and topping
directions: Mix together water with soda and mayonnaise. Add remaining ingredients. Mix well; pour into 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350°.

title: very good punch
directions: Heat part of
the
water
and dissolve the sugar in it. Add to remaining ingredients, except ginger ale.
Mix well and freeze in plastic
milk
jug.
Thaw
about
4 hours.	Put into punch bowl and
break	up
mixture
(it
becomes slush).
Add ginger ale when serving.
May
add food coloring to make your desired color.

title: choco-scotch clusters
directions: Melt chocolate chips, butterscotch chips and peanut butter over low heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add Rice Krispies; stir.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Refrigerate.

title: russian chicken
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a bowl mixing well.
Rinse your chicken after removing skin and debone breast.
(Optional) Pat dry. Place in 9x13-inch pan or roaster.
Spray with Pam to keep from sticking.
Pour mixture over chicken and place in a 350° oven. Cook breasts 50-60 minutes.
Cook legs and thighs about 90 minutes. Serves 8.

title: sweet potatoes and apples
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Slice cooked potatoes and apples 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick.
Place half of each in a buttered baking dish. Sprinkle with half the sugar and salt and then dot with half the butter.
Repeat.
Cover and bake 40 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine cream cheese, one cup sugar and salt.
Mix well.
Add the flour and egg yolks.
Beat thoroughly. Mix in the lemon juice, nutmeg, vanilla, almond flavoring and sour cream.

title: pumpkin almond bisque
directions: Remove flesh from pumpkin.
Keep shell as a serving container. Simmer pumpkin flesh in a small amount of broth until tender. Puree in blender.
Melt butter in heavy pan.
Add celery and onion. Simmer 5 minutes.
Add to pumpkin in blender along with tomato paste and almond paste.
Blend until smooth.
Return to pot and simmer 30 minutes.
Blend cream into soup.
Cook until hot.
Season with nutmeg, pepper, salt and Amaretto.
Float pumpkin seeds on each serving.

title: granny's deviled eggs
directions: Cook, cool and peel one dozen eggs.
Cut in half, removing yolk.
Put yolks in a bowl, mash with a fork and add small amounts of salad dressing, sweet pickle juice and mustard until it forms a thick paste.
Fill egg white halves and sprinkle with paprika.

title: coconut pie
directions: Cook on stove until thick, then put coconut in.
Put in cooked pie shell.
Beat egg whites with sugar (about 3 teaspoons).
Put on pie and bake.

title: oatmeal scotchies cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine flour, soda, salt and cinnamon in bowl; set aside.
Beat butter, sugar, eggs, brown sugar and vanilla until creamy.
Beat in flour mixture.
Stir in oats and butterscotch chips.
Drop by spoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake 8 minutes.

title: orange julius
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender until frothy.
Pour into glass and enjoy.

title: custard pie
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° for 30 minutes.

title: hot dogs and sauce
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together in a crock-pot.
Put in cut up hot dogs and sausages.
Let cook in crock-pot until bubbly. Serve on rolls or by themselves.

title: chicken cutlets
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Blend.
Add chicken soup, then cook until thick.
Add chicken.
Spread in shallow pan and chill until stiff.
Cut into cutlets with biscuit cutter. Roll in crumbs, then beaten egg then crumbs again.
Fry in deep fat about 1 1/2 inches deep until brown.
Drain on absorbent paper.

title: chili #1
directions: In a large pot, brown ground beef and drain off grease.
Add green peppers and onion; saute until soft.
Add the spices and seasonings.
Add tomatoes and tomato paste.
Drain and rinse kidney beans and add them to the pot.
Add baked beans and brown sugar; simmer for 1/2 hour.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: lu's whole wheat bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in the two cups warm water.
Add the one tablespoon sugar and set aside.
Mix together the flours, sugar, shortening and salt until crumbly.
Add to the yeast mixture along with the four cups of water.
Mix by hand.
Cover and let rise overnight.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Sift flour into bowl. Add shortening and cut in with pastry cutter. Add buttermilk; mix well and turn out on lightly floured surface. Knead for 30 seconds; roll 1/2-inch thick. Place on well greased baking pan; brush with melted shortening. Bake in hot 500° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: zucchini pineapple
directions: Mix first four ingredients together and simmer for 20 minutes. Add pineapple oil. Pour into clean, sterilized jars.
Process in hot water bath for 30 minutes.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Drain spaghetti and toss with 1/2 stick butter.
Saute and brown onion, sausage and mushrooms.

Put some sauce in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan, then add 1/2 of the spaghetti, 1/2 of the sauce, 1/2 of the cheeses, 1/2 of the pepperoni, 1/2 sausage, etc., then rest of the spaghetti and so on, just like lasagna! Top with grated Parmesan and pepperoni.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: quick meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in loaf pan.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Top with ketchup.

title: baked fish with parmesan-sour cream sauce
directions: Place fillets in a single layer in a lightly greased 13x9-inch pan.
Stir together sour cream and next 4 ingredients; spread mixture evenly over fillets.
Sprinkle with breadcrumbs, and drizzle with butter.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20-25 minutes or until fish flakes with a fork.
Yield:
4-6 servings.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together with a spoon (do not use mixer). Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: no roll cookies(sugar)
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add the eggs and vanilla. Mix the flour with the cream of tartar, soda and salt and add. Mix and form into balls.
Flatten with a glass dipped in sugar. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: onion cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease an 8-inch square pan.
In medium skillet, melt margarine and saute onion.
Cool.
Add sour cream, salt and 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese to the onions and set aside.

title: garden cheese ball
directions: Press vegetables between paper towels to remove water. Combine cheeses, onion and garlic in large bowl.
Stir well.
Stir in vegetables.
Cover and chill 2 hours.
Roll cheese ball in combined cereal and parsley.
Wrap in waxed paper.
Chill.

title: cocktail spread
directions: Mix together and spread on round cocktail rye bread.
Heat at 350° for 10 minutes (until cheese melts).
Makes about 25 bread rounds.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and egg.
Add 2 cups flour, baking soda and salt.
Add vanilla, lemon extract and sour cream.
Mix in a third cup of flour.
Chill overnight.

title: easy spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Cook ground beef.
Add Velveeta cheese, spaghetti sauce and tomato puree.
Let simmer well.

title: applesauce salad
directions: Heat water to boiling.
Add red hots and Jell-O.
Stir until dissolved.
Add applesauce and food coloring.
Chill.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 10-inch Bundt or tube pan.
Combine cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, water and oil in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed with electric mixer for 2 minutes. Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes, or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 25 minutes.
Invert onto serving plate.
Cool completely.
Glaze is optional.

title: crock-pot hamburger vegetable stew
directions: Brown ground beef and strain.
Layer vegetables in crock-pot in order listed, seasoning with salt and pepper.
Spoon ground beef over celery.
Pour soup with 1 soup can of water in bowl, mixing well.
Pour over ground beef.
Cook 6 to 8 hours on low or 2 to 4 hours on high.
Stir occasionally.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix 8 ounces of softened cream cheese, garlic salt and Worcestershire sauce to taste, and enough sour cream to make mixture spreadable.
Spread on a large, flat serving tray.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Prepare Dream Whip as directed on package.
Blend powdered sugar into softened cream cheese.
Blend Dream Whip into this and add lemon juice.
Pour into the prepared pie shell.
Scoop out the middle with a spoon (just push it to the sides so the middle will be scooped out).
Cover scooped out area with sliced bananas and top with blueberry pie filling.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: buttermilk pralines
directions: Use heavy skillet.
Cook buttermilk, sugar, and soda to a soft ball stage (234°).
Add butter, vanilla and pecans.
Beat until firm.
Drop by spoonsful on waxed paper.

title: candy cookies
directions: Boil margarine, sugar, cocoa, salt and cream in microwave until soft ball stage (2 to 5 minutes). Add remaining ingredients. Mix and drop on wax paper. (You must work fast on dropping on wax paper.)

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients.
It will be very thick at first.
Put in greased muffin pans.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: cotton pickin' cake
directions: Add eggs, oil and water to cake mix.
Stir in oranges and pecans.
Pour into 3 (8-inch) cake pans, greased and floured. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool completely before frosting. Mix Cool Whip, pineapple and pudding together for frosting.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Step 1:
Cover cookie sheet with rolls.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes and then let cool.

title: chuck barbecue
directions: *With as much fat and connective tissue removed as possible.

title: strawberry cheese ball
directions: Add enough Ruby Port or any wine to mix with softened cream cheese and walnuts.
Form into ball.
Chill, then cover with strawberry preserves.
Serve with onion or Melba round crackers.

title: lo-cal sandwich
directions: Smear peanut butter on toast.
Make it very thin. Slice banana thin and put
on
top of peanut butter.
Put thin layer of peanut butter on other
slice
of bread and place on top of bananas.

title: jewish crumb cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add vanilla, then add eggs one at a time.
Beat well.
Fold in sour cream.
Sift the dry ingredients and fold into mixture.
Prepare mixture of sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Pour 1/2 the batter into greased pan.
Sprinkle half the cinnamon mixture over batter and cut it through with a knife. Pour in remaining batter and cut it through with a knife after pouring on the rest of the cinnamon mixture.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
The recipe is easily doubled and baked in a 9 inch x 13 inch pan and a small pan.
Allow an hour to bake.

title: bananas foster
directions: Melt butter in a large frying pan. Add the sugar. Place bananas in the hot butter and gently brown them. Pour the banana liqueur over the bananas and set it on fire. Swish the bananas around until the liqueur burns off. Place on a platter and top with vanilla ice cream.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Melt chocolate and let cool slightly.
In large bowl, combine chocolate, eggs, syrup, sugar, butter and vanilla.
Blend well. Stir in pecans.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Cool.
Serves 8.

title: claire's quiche
directions: Blend soup with milk.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Cool slightly.
Stir in cream and cheese.
Refrigerate 20 minutes until cool.
Beat eggs in bowl.
Add soup mixture, then dry ingredients.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Makes 2 large pies.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Bake sweet potatoes; peel and mash in large mixing bowl.
Melt a few pats of butter into warm potatoes.
Break egg into mixture and beat potatoes, butter and egg at low speed.
Add sugar to taste.
Add some milk and continue to beat until the mixture is soft, smooth consistency.
Pour into greased casserole dish and bake for 15 to 20 minutes, just long enough for the milk and egg to cook.
Enjoy and remember my Dad's sweet-tooth.

title: sugar crusted muffins
directions: Sift together the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Add in egg and milk.
Stir until moistened.
Put into greased muffin tin.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.
When done, dip in melted margarine, then into sugar.

title: chicken salad for sandwiches
directions: This soup recipe was given to me and is a take off on the famous Steamboat Springs Cheese Soup.
When they made it, they used Cheddar cheese, but when I made it, it seemed gritty so I tried Old English cheese the next time.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Good on chicken or for making Sloppy Joes.

title: kentucky fried chicken
directions: In plastic bag, mix flour, paprika, soup mixture and dressing mix; shake well.
Run chicken under cold water and dry well. Dredge chicken, one piece at a time, in the flour mixture to coat well.
Spray pans with Pam and place chicken, skin side up, in pans and drizzle with 2 tablespoons of oil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.
Yield:
Will coat up to 32 pieces.

title: chili con queso
directions: Saute garlic and onion in butter.
Add tomatoes, chilies, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Simmer until well blended.
Add cheese and stir until melted.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Beat egg slightly with a fork.
Stir in milk and oil.
Add dry ingredients and stir until moistened.
Batter should be lumpy. Don't overmix.
Blend in fresh blueberries.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: party pineapple pork
directions: Mix batter of first 4 ingredients.
Coat meat cubes in batter and deep fry until crisp.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan and set aside. In a large pan, pour juice from pineapple, cherries, water, sugar, vinegar and soy sauce.
Bring to boil and boil for 2 minutes.
Add pineapple, cherries and green pepper.
Boil 1 minute more, add thickening of cornstarch and water.
Pour mixture over pork.
Bake, covered, about 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with fried rice and egg foo yong.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Beat eggs, peanut butter and water.
Add cake mix.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: aunt margaret's homemade ice cream
directions: Mix and place in ice cream freezer.

title: broccoli quiche(large recipe)
directions: Place pie crusts in bottom of 9 x 13 pan that has been sprayed. Layer broccoli on top of crust. Whip eggs, cream and Parmesan together. Pour on top of broccoli. Cook at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes or until knife comes out clean of center.

title: fried cheese puffs
directions: Combine cheese, flour, salt and pepper.
Fold in egg whites. Form into balls.
Roll in cracker crumbs.
Fry in deep fat. Cheese balls can be made through rolling in cracker crumbs, then stored in your refrigerator until ready to fry.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Alternate in casserole layers of thinly sliced potatoes with skin, chopped green pepper and onion.
Season with salt and pepper.
Mix mushroom soup with milk and pour over potatoes. Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: country fried potatoes
directions: Melt butter and drippings in a heavy skillet.
Add sliced potatoes and chopped onion to the hot skillet.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Cook over low heat until bottom is brown; turn and brown other side.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain only the mandarin oranges. Mix all ingredients in large bowl and let chill.

title: mexican corn bread pie
directions: Mix cornmeal, soda, salt, grease, milk, eggs and corn together. Pour half of batter in a greased skillet.
Sprinkle cheese, onion, peppers and ground beef.
Pour remainder of batter in skillet. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Heat milk and butter.
Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar and beat, then add flour.
Stir, then add milk and butter.
Add baking powder and vanilla.
Mix together.
Bake in Bundt pan or loaf pan. Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.
Great with cream cheese frosting.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind the cranberries, oranges, apples and orange rind.
Add the sugar to this.
Add the jello, dissolved in the hot water. Add the cold pineapple juice. Chill and add the cranberry mixture, pineapple, nuts and grapes.

title: dutch meat loaf
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients and form into a loaf.
Place in pan and put into 350° oven until sauce is ready.
Mix remaining ingredients to make sauce and pour over meat loaf.
Bake for 1 1/4 hours, basting often.

title: sugar-free fruit cake
directions: Mix the first 8 ingredients.
Mix remainder and add to first bowl.
Line bottom of baking dish with pecans.
(Also put some on top.)
Bake in 2 greased 1 1/2-quart loaf pans for 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Best if sealed and refrigerated for 2 days.

title: seasoned pretzels
directions: Mix together.
Put broken pretzels on cookie sheet.
Pour mixture over pretzels.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Turn once.

title: joyce's southern pecan tassies
directions: Blend and make into approximately 24 balls; chill in refrigerator overnight. Press into miniature muffin pans, covering bottom and sides.

title: peanut butter banana ice cream
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs until blended.
Beat in sugar and corn syrup until smooth and light.
Beat in mashed bananas and lemon juice until blended.
Beat in half and half, whipping cream and peanut butter.
Pour into ice cream canister.
Freeze in ice cream maker according to manufacturer's directions.

title: hello dollies
directions: In
a
x
11-inch pan, put graham cracker crumbs and butter and put in a 250° oven until butter melts.	Remove from oven
and spread
nuts, chocolate chips and coconut over top. Pour milk over mixture and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: peanut butter cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat 9-inch spring-form pan with nonstick cooking spray.

title: barbecue pork roast or beef
directions: Cook pork or beef roast until it falls apart.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Remove roast from oven.
Drain grease.
Cut meat apart.
Add other ingredients.
Cook 30 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: green bean bundles
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Partially cook the green beans until they are still crisp-tender and bright green.
Take approximately 10 green beans and form into bundles. Trim both ends so that the bundles are even.
Wrap 1 slice of bacon that has been cut lengthwise around each bundle and loosely tie.
(Bacon can be partially cooked to make more pliable.)

title: berry cream salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Stir in fruit and ice cream. Refrigerate until set (about 20 minutes). Spoon into dishes.
Make it without fruit for a fast and refreshing dessert.

title: honey biscuits
directions: Boil the oleo, honey and sugar over low heat for 1 minute. Pour into a 9 x13-inch pan.
Sprinkle in nuts; lay biscuits on top.
Bake for 12 minutes at 425°.
Turn out on foil (like upside-down cake).

title: enchiladas
directions: Melt some bacon grease (3 tablespoons) and add 2 tablespoons flour.
Mix in broth a little at a time to prevent lumps. Add all other ingredients.
Mix in 2 tablespoons cornstarch (mixed with a little water) to thicken to gravy like consistency. Boil (simmer) for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: amish friendship cake
directions: Grease 2 loaf pans or 1 bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until shows clean.
When done, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles until done but not overly done.
In a large bowl combine noodles, shrimp or crab meat, onion, pepper, celery and mayonnaise.
Mix well; add garlic salt and pepper to taste.
Can be stored in Tupperware bowl in refrigerator for about 2 days.

title: peach pie
directions: Mix the cornstarch, sugar and hot water and cook. Add jello. Cool and add vanilla and almond. Mix peaches into cooled mixture and place in shells. Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with nutmeg. Refrigerate. Makes 2 (8-inch) pies or 1 large.

title: german individual apple fritters
directions: Peel apples and take out core, cut into 1/4-inch rounds in batter (it should stay on apples).
Fill pan with apples, fry and turn each side until golden brown.

title: cracklin bread
directions: Mix ingredients with hot water (not soupy). Make a pone and bake in hot oven until done.

title: oven french fries
directions: Beat 2 egg whites.
Add 1 1/2 teaspoons Cajun spice.
Add potatoes to egg mixture.
Shake to coat well.
Spray large cookie sheet with Pam.
Spread potatoes in single row on sheet.
Spray lightly with Pam.
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes, stirring every 7 to 8 minutes for even browning.

title: deep dish taco squares
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and cheese.
Set aside.	Mix baking mix (Bisquick) and water until soft dough forms.
Put in greased baking dish, pressing dough 1/2-inch up sides of dish.
Layer beef, tomatoes and green pepper in dish (1 layer each).
Spoon sour cream mixture over top.
Bake until edges of dough are light brown approximately 25 to 30 minutes at 375°.

title: poor man's sausage
directions: Mix thoroughly and form into 3-inch diameter rolls.
Wrap tightly in tinfoil.
Chill 24 hours.
Punch holes in bottom of foil and place on broiler pan.
Bake 4 hours at 225°.
Place on rack or paper towels until cool and drained.

title: chocolate caramel pecan cheesecake
directions: Combine cookie crumbs and butter; press firmly on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: aunt jamimah's pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell; bake in a 375° oven until done.

title: strawberry angel food cake
directions: Mix well the cream cheese, powdered sugar, sugar, Cool Whip and vanilla.
Take one angel food cake and cut in 3 rings.
Put mixture on each layer as you put together on top and sides.
Pour rest of fruit on top.

title: shrimp linguine
directions: Cook linguine in rapidly boiling water for 10 minutes; drain. Rinse in cold water and set aside.
Melt butter in 10-inch skillet.
Add garlic, shrimp and mushrooms and cook slowly in hot butter for 5 minutes.
Add linguine to skillet.
Sprinkle with cheese, salt and pepper.
Toss until linguine is very hot, but do not let butter brown.
Turn onto warm serving dish.
Sprinkle with more cheese and garnish with sprigs of parsley.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and shortening, adding sugar gradually.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift together three times the flour, baking powder, cocoa and salt. Add to mixture alternately with the milk.
Add vanilla.
Pour batter into a large tube pan that has been greased and dusted with flour.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients except oil thoroughly.
Form into small balls about 3/4 of an inch in diameter.
Let stand for 15 minutes. Heat oil in frying pan to 375°.
Deep fry meatballs for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Serve hot with toothpicks. Makes 60 meatballs.

title: carrots in wine
directions: In a saucepan, cover carrots with water and salt.
Bring to a boil and cook 10 minutes or until tender.
Drain carrots and return to saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients and heat until liquid is partially reduced.
Discard garlic and serve immediately.

title: parmesan mashed potatoes
directions: In a saucepan, combine the potatoes and salted water to cover generously.
Bring to a boil over moderate heat.
Reduce the heat to low, cover and simmer until tender, about 20 minutes.

title: greek chicken
directions: Brown chicken in large skillet.
Add remaining ingredients, except onions and garlic cloves.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Mince onions and garlic cloves and saute in a little butter.
Add to chicken and simmer 20 minutes or until chicken is done.
Serve over macaroni.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Mix pudding with the milk and blend well.
Add Cool Whip and sour cream.
Put layer of graham crackers into 9 x 12-inch pan. Spread half of pudding mixture over crackers.
Put another layer of crackers and spread the rest of pudding over them.
Top with crackers.
Heat can of frosting in microwave and put on top of cake.
Also good without the frosting.

title: easy salad
directions: Combine fruit and marshmallows in a bowl. Sprinkle with dry pudding. Mix well. Stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add Karo, salt and vanilla.
Add floured pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake for 30 to 35 minutes in 375° oven or until filling is firm.

title: autumn chowder
directions: Fry bacon, add onions - brown until bacon is crisp.
Stir in water, potatoes, carrots and bouillon.
Simmer until potatoes are tender.
Stir in milk, corn, and pepper and heat until simmering.

title: fish chowder
directions: Saute salt pork and onion in butter until almost golden.
Add 2 cups hot water, potatoes, fish, clams and clam juice. Boil. Simmer 20 minutes. Take off heat. Add evaporated milk and regular milk to suit your taste.
Salt and pepper.
To thicken, make cornstarch paste of 2 tablespoons cornstarch and cold water.

title: oriental fried rice
directions: Saute boiled rice in hot oil until golden; add scallions, carrots, celery, salt and pepper.
Toss until slightly tender. Hollow center of rice and break in eggs.
Scramble until half cooled and then stir into rice mixture, stirring until done.
Add in soy sauce.
Makes 6 servings.

title: leg of lamb
directions: Melt red currant or grape jelly in a saucepan and mix in all ingredients. Then pour over the lamb in a large bowl and marinate for at least 8 hours. Prepare on grill, turning often. Cook until done to your taste.

title: grandmother siler's cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, then dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Put batter in two 9-inch greased layer cake pans.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 35 minutes, or until cake springs back when lightly touched.

title: oil and vinegar dressing
directions: Combine ingredients in screw-top jar.
Shake to blend.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Saute onion, pepper and celery in oil in a large fry pan.
Add cabbage and cook 5 or 10 minutes with top on pan.
Add sugar and salt halfway through cooking process.
Chopped tomatoes may be added to recipe.
Delicious for different vegetable.

title: pina colada fruit dip
directions: Blend together.
Add additional sugar and/or rum to reach desired taste. Serve with fresh strawberries, pineapple or bananas.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Split zucchini long ways.
Hollow out to about 1/2-inch thickness.	Place
in
baking dish, combine all other ingredients except cheese.
Add the zucchini you dug out of the hull. Saute until
meat
is
done.
Pile into zucchini shells.	Top with Parmesan
cheese
and
bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until shells are well done.

title: sausage biscuit balls
directions: Mix all ingredients with fingers to form into marble sized balls.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 15 minutes or until browned.
May be frozen and reheated.

title: cheesecake cookies
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar until light.
Add flour and nuts until mixture resembles crumbs.
Set aside 1 cup.
Press remaining mixture into an 8-inch square pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°. While this is baking, combine granulated sugar and cream cheese; beat until smooth.
Add egg, milk, lemon juice and vanilla and beat well.
Spread mixture over baked crust.
Sprinkle reserved crumbs over top.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: mexicorn lasagna
directions: Simmer ground beef, corn, tomato sauce, picante sauce, chili powder and cumin in skillet for 5 minutes.
In bowl, mix cheese, eggs, oregano, garlic salt and Parmesan cheese and mix well. Arrange 6 tortillas on bottom and sides of lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, overlapping if necessary.
Top with half of the meat mixture and spoon the cheese mixture over meat.
Lay rest of tortillas over cheese mixture.
Top with remaining meat mixture. Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes until hot and bubbly.
Remove from oven and add cheese.
Stand 10 minutes and serve.

title: vegetable chili
directions: In a small bowl, combine onion and garlic with an equal amount of water; set aside 10 minutes to soften.
In a large skillet, heat oil until hot.
Add onion and garlic; saute until lightly browned, about 3 minutes.
Add tomatoes, mushrooms, zucchini, green peppers, chili powder, salt, and black pepper.
Simmer, covered until vegetables are tender, about 15 minutes.
Combine flour and 3 Tbsp. water.
Add to chili along with kidney beans.
Cook and stir until thickened, about 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheddar cheese, if desired.
Makes 4 servings each with 199 calories, 2 g. fat and 0 mg. cholesterol.

title: strawberry dip
directions: Whip together and dip strawberries.
It's great.
Try other fruits also.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Mix well.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Add to wet mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: lil's best chili
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Combine all ingredients in large kettle.
Start to cook and cut heat to simmer. Stir occasionally to keep from sticking to bottom of kettle.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: souper meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, mix thoroughly 1/2 cup soup, beef, crumbs, onion and egg.
In baking pan, firmly shape into 8 x 4-inch loaf. Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Reserve 1 tablespoon drippings. Heat remaining soup, water and reserved drippings to boiling. Spoon over meat loaf.

title: nut cream drops
directions: Mix all ingredients together except the nuts. Cook in a double boiler until a drop of that mixture dropped in a cup of cool water forms a soft ball. Drop mixture onto wax paper by teaspoonful. Let cool and store in airtight container.
Makes about 40 pieces.

title: no bake peanut butter bars
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients well.
Press into buttered 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Melt the chocolate chips; pour over first mixture.
Refrigerate for several hours before cutting. Taste like Reese's peanut butter cups.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended. Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours. Bake in tube pan.

title: norwegian apple pie
directions: With a wooden spoon, mix the ingredients in the order given, folding in the nuts and apples last.
Put the mixture in an 8-inch greased pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.
Serves 6.

title: pie crust
directions: Cut flour and Crisco with pastry blender.
Mix oil and cold water with fork; add to flour mixture and form dough.
This is very soft so it helps to refrigerate for at least an hour.
Makes enough for a double crust pie and one shell.
When you roll it out, use Saran Wrap.
If pie pan is large, the freezer size wrap works better.
Moisten counter with dish cloth and Saran will not slip.

title: banana nut bread or muffins
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg, then bran.
Mix well. Combine water and bananas.
Add to creamed mixture.
Then add dry ingredients.
Mix well; add vanilla and nuts.
Bake in greased loaf pan or greased muffin tins.
For loaf, bake 1 hour at 350°.
For muffin tins, bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Cut meat into 1/2 inch strips, 2 or 3 inches long. In a skillet, brown meat in 2 tbsp. hot oil and drain. Remove meat from skillet. Drain syrup from pineapple and add enough water to it to equal 1 1/2 c. liquid. Combine this with the vinegar, brown sugar, cornstarch,

salt and soy sauce. Cook in the skillet until clear and slightly thickened. Add browned meat. Cover and simmer until the vegetables are crisp tender. Serve over rice. Serves 6. This can be made from leftover pork roast.

title: magic pumpkin pie
directions: In large bowl, blend together all ingredients.
Turn into shell.
Bake in
a moderate (375°) oven for 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool. Refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Top with whipped cream.

title: quick meal
directions: Cook potatoes.
Brown lunch meat.
Cook onion in butter.
Mix in soup and milk.
After potatoes are cooked and drained, mix all ingredients together.

title: dough for rolls
directions: Mix together, until smooth, the oleo (or shortening), sugar, salt and eggs.
Stir in milk and yeast, dissolved in warm water. Add enough flour to make a soft dough.
Cover and let rise until double.
Make into desired shapes and let rise again.
Bake.

title: spinach side dish
directions: Boil and salt spinach.
Drain.
Mix all ingredients.
Put in a greased 8-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Scald milk and let stand until lukewarm.
Add yeast to milk.
Mix flour, salt, sugar, butter and water together in a large bowl.
Add yeast mixture to flour mixture.
Cover with a cloth and let rise in a warm place until dough is doubled in size, about 40 minutes.
Punch dough down. Divide into 24 pieces.
Place each piece into lightly greased muffin pan and cover, letting rise again.
Bake for 15 minutes. Makes 2 dozen rolls.

title: wanda's red velvet cake and frosting
directions: Add all ingredients together in mixing bowl.
Beat well but do not overbeat.
Bake in 3 layers in 350° oven.
I like cake in 2 layers better.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Stir together. Cook at 425° for 25 minutes or until done. (Batter will be thin.)

title: orange delight salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add juice and fruit.
Pour into baking dish and chill until set.
Mix pudding and milk.
Whip cream and fold into pudding.
Spread topping over congealed gelatin and fruit.
Chill until serving.

title: pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, beat eggs well.
Add sugar, brown sugar, corn syrup, flour, vanilla and salt to eggs; beat until well combined.
Fold in melted butter and chopped pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Arrange pecan halves on top.
Bake until filling is set (center of the pie will stay firm when pie is shaken gently), about 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool completely before serving.
Yields 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: filled cream puffs
directions: Melt butter in boiling water.
Add flour and salt.
Stir vigorously.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture forms ball that doesn't separate.
Remove from heat and let cool slightly. Add eggs one at a time, beating vigorously after each addition until mixture is smooth.
Grease cookie sheet.
Use tablespoon to spoon out mixture onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 40 minutes.

title: old-time soda biscuits
directions: Cut
shortening
in flour, baking powder and salt.
Add milk with soda in it.
You can use a little more milk and drop them instead of rolling and cutting them.
Bake in a 400° oven until brown.

title: fantastic apple salad
directions: Cook the first 5 ingredients until it is thick; set aside and let it cool.
Mix together the Cool Whip, pineapple and the cooked mixture when it is cool.
Now, pour over the apples.
You can add the peanuts, if desired.

title: baked red snapper
directions: Place fillets in greased baking pan. Drizzle juice over fish. Sprinkle with 1/4 teaspoon of cloves and mace. Bake fish in 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: strawberry glaze
directions: Blend sugar and cornstarch in small pan.
Stir in water and strawberries.
Cook, stirring constantly until thickens and comes to a boil.

title: pork fried rice
directions: Stir hot water and rice in bowl.
Cover with foil and let stand 5 minutes or until water is absorbed.
Fluff with fork. Meanwhile, cook and stir pork, onion and green pepper in hot oil in large skillet for 2-3 minutes.
Add rice.
Cook and stir for 2-3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Move rice to one side and pour the egg into bottom of skillet.
Cook until egg is set then stir into rice.
Stir in scallions, soy sauce, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook over low heat for 2-3 minutes to heat thoroughly.
Beef may be a substitute for pork.

title: punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in very warm (not hot) water.
Add Kool-Aid. Mix in juices and freeze until icy.
Just before serving, place in punch bowl and pour ginger ale over mixture to serve.

title: old fashion stack cake
directions: Sift flour together with baking powder.
Set aside.
Mix eggs and sugar well.
Add butter, milk and flour mixture, beating after each addition.
Add flavoring last.
Makes 4 layers.
Bake about 25 minutes at 350°.
Spread applesauce between each layer.
Let stand overnight or several hours before serving.

title: gramp's farm meat loaf
directions: Mix salt with hamburg.
Add milk gradually; add beaten eggs. Mix well.
Add cracker crumbs.
If mixture seems too dry, add more milk, a little at a time, for right consistency.
Bake in a greased glass loaf dish one hour in 350° oven.

title: art chapman's pickled beets
directions: Boil mixture.
Add cooked beef and simmer 15 minutes.
Pack in sterile jars and seal.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Mix together by hand and then layer in oblong dish or pan with vanilla wafers.
Crumble small amount of wafers on top.

title: pork casserole
directions: Brown pork and onion; drain fat and save. Add macaroni, tomatoes and half of cheese to meat. Pour into casserole dish. Coat bread crumbs with fat. Sprinkle over casserole.
Top with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: filling for lemon meringue pie
directions: Combine cornstarch, sugar, lemon juice and lemon rind in a sauce pan.
Beat egg yolks, add to the corn starch mixture. Gradually add boiling water.
Heat to boiling over direct heat. Boil gently 4 minutes, stirring constantly.

title: canned slaw or hot dog relish
directions: Mix all up and cook.
Boil 25 minutes.
Pack in hot jars and seal.

title: frozen curry sauce(to have ready to serve with cooked chicken or shrimp.)
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet; add onion and apples.
Saute until just tender.
Combine dry ingredients and add to onion and apple mixture, stirring to blend.
Add stock and milk; cook, stirring constantly until thickened.
Remove from heat; add lemon juice.
Cool to room temperature; put in freezer containers and freeze.
Makes 12 servings.

title: easy cheese cake
directions: Prepare Dream Whip according to directions.
Add sugar and softened cream cheese.
Blend until most of the lumps are out. Add lemon juice.
Pour into crust.
Can be topped with any flavor of pie filling.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt in bowl.
Beat in eggs, melted margarine, milk and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie crust and drop pecans (halved) to almost cover top.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then bake at 350° for almost 20 minutes or until done.
Makes 2 pies.

title: baked macaroni with cheese
directions: Melt butter and add onion, flour, mustard, salt, pepper and milk.
Cut 3/4 of cheese in thin slices and add to mixture, stirring constantly until cheese is melted.
Remove from heat. Boil macaroni in salted water for 9 minutes.
Butter casserole dish and mix sauce and macaroni.
Slice rest of cheese and lay on top of mixture.
Sprinkle liberally with fine, dry bread crumbs and bake (uncovered) at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: pineapple spoonbread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Mix in the other ingredients. Pour into buttered 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces in baking dish. Squeeze lemon juice over chicken. Sprinkle with salt, pepper, paprika, garlic salt and dot with butter. Cover and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: very good ice cream(for 1 gallon)
directions: Dissolve gelatin in small amount of cold water.
Add evaporated milk, beaten eggs, sugar and cream.
Mix good.
Add boiling water to mix.
Strain into freezer.
Add 3 teaspoons or more vanilla and milk to fill.

title: kindergarten taco with cheese only!
directions: Get bread and then put cheese on it.
Put it in the microwave for about 10 minutes.
Take it out and put it on the plate.
Cut it and then eat it.

title: canned sweet peppers
directions: Bring juice to a boil; add sliced peppers and bring to boil. Put in jars and immediately cap jars.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown and drain hamburg; add taco mix and water.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Mix all vegetables and cheese.
Add hamburg; toss all with dressing.
Add Doritos.
Serve.

title: cream of broccoli and cheddar soup(serves 4)
directions: In a large saucepan, warm the butter over medium heat until melted. Add the onion and saute until softened. Stir in the flour and cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until no longer visible, about 1 minute. Slowly stir in broth, then the broccoli. Bring the mixture to a boil over medium-high heat. Reduce the heat to medium-low; cover and simmer until the broccoli is tender, about 10 minutes. Stir in the cheese and cook over low heat until melted, about 30 seconds. Stir in the half and half, salt and pepper. Warm the soup over low heat (do not let the soup boil).

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Grease a baking dish and make a layer of potatoes (each about 1-inch deep).
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and flour and dot with butter.
Make 2 more layers the same way.
Add enough milk so you can see it between the slices of potatoes, BUT DO NOT COVER the top with milk.
Cover pan and bake in a 350° oven until potatoes are tender when pierced with a fork (about 1 to 1 1/4 hours). Remove cover the last 15 minutes to brown.
Serve from baking dish.

title: candied carrots(microwave)
directions: Scrape and cut carrots into thin strips.
Place carrots in a deep, 1 1/2-quart, heat-resistant, nonmetallic casserole.
Set aside.
In a small, heat-resistant, nonmetallic bowl combine remaining ingredients.
Heat uncovered on Full power 1 minute or until butter is melted.
Spoon butter sugar mixture over carrots. Heat covered on Full power 7 minutes.
Spoon sauce over carrots and heat uncovered on Full power an additional 3 minutes.

title: salad dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in a salad dressing bottle and shake. This may be used on a regular lettuce and tomato salad and is excellent on cooked fresh string beans.

title: tropical fruit cooler
directions: Mix orange juice, orange soda, ginger ale and pineapple juice in a large punch bowl.
Garnish with scoops of sherbet and strawberries and/or cherries.
Serve chilled in frosted glasses.

title: chicken and spinach quiche
directions: Pierce pastry shell thoroughly with fork.
Bake in 375° oven 10 minutes; remove.
In large bowl toss together chicken, cheese, spinach and onion.
Spoon into pastry shell.
In small bowl stir together eggs, real mayonnaise, milk, basil and pepper until smooth.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Bake in 350° oven 40 minutes or until golden and knife inserted in center comes out clean. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: diabetic pumpkin walnut bread
directions: In large bowl, mix oil, Sweet 'N Low, eggs, pumpkin and water. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into mini loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool.
May use regular loaf pan, but will need to bake longer.

title: corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine flour and meal in large mixing bowl.
Add milk, egg and salt.
Mix well.
Pour into greased baking pan and bake for 30 minutes.

title: spicy pumpkin dessert
directions: Combine crumbs and 1/4 cup margarine.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: aunt jenny's chili
directions: Simmer hamburger meat, onions, bell pepper and celery together.
Add salt, black pepper, Worcestershire sauce, catsup and chili powder.
Simmer a little longer.
Add kidney beans and water.
Cook about an hour.

title: egg pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together, put on an open pie crust and bake for 30 minutes.

title: oven omelet brunch
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
In oven melt butter in baking dish (9 x 13-inch) until dish is coated on bottom.
In a large mixing bowl beat eggs, sour cream, milk and salt until blended.
Stir in onion.
Pour into dish.
Bake until eggs are set but still moist, about 35 minutes.
Makes 12 servings.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Pack into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake.
Unmold; serve hot or cold.

title: dill macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni. Drain and cool. Add celery, green
pepper, carrots and pimento.
Mix remaining ingredients. Spoon over macaroni and toss to mix thoroughly. Chill.

title: hemlock inn tomato casserole
directions: Combine tomatoes, bread or croutons, salt, pepper, eggs and milk.
Pour
into
casserole
dish and top with onions and cheese. Bake in a 350° oven until hot and bubbly.

title: mint or butter candy
directions: Mix altogether with hands.
Let set in refrigerator for awhile.
Pat into molds and be sure to sprinkle sugar in bottom of molds.
You may color with food color.

title: quick scallop potatoes
directions: Place sliced potatoes in casserole dish.
Mix all other ingredients in pan on top of stove until melted together.
Then pour over potatoes and cook at 350°, covered, for 1 hour; uncovered, until browned on top.

title: italian zucchini
directions: Bring to boil water, corn, tomatoes and seasoning.
Reduce heat and cook for 3 minutes.
Stir in zucchini and cook for 5 minutes.
Top with cheese and serve.
Serves 4.

title: tater-topped casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease shallow 2-quart baking dish. Brown onions, 1/2 cup celery and hamburger.
Spoon off fat.
Add salt and pepper.
Spread mixture in a baking dish.
Pour cream of celery soup over everything.
Top with a layer of Tater Tots.
Bake 45 minutes.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Beat together sugar, syrup, salt, flour and eggs.
Add vanilla, butter and pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
(Turn pecan halves, rounded side up.)
Bake at 300° for about 1 hour, until filling is set.
Serve with whipped cream, if desired.

title: hamburger corn bread
directions: Brown meat and next 3 ingredients.
Cook a few minutes and set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Grease skillet and heat.
Pour in half of corn bread mixture.
Add all of meat mixture.
Spread evenly.
Pour in remainder of corn bread mixture; spread evenly.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: oysterette nibbles
directions: Mix thoroughly in a large bowl all ingredients.
Add 24 ounces oyster crackers.
Fold over and over until all oil is absorbed. Cover bowl with a cloth.
When crackers look dry, put into container.

title: grit souffl
directions: Add all ingredients to cooked grits, except the eggs, milk and 3/4 cup of the cheese. Cool the grit mixture for a few minutes. Beat in the eggs and milk. Pour into a buttered casserole dish. Top with remaining cheese and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into hot pan.
Bake 30-40 minutes at 450°.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: eggnog
directions: Beat all ingredients together or put into blender.
Serves 2.

title: trees and raisins
directions: Combine broccoli, cauliflower, onions, raisins, and bacon in large bowl.
Pour dressing over vegetables, and stir to coat. Cover and marinate at least an hour.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream bananas, eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla.
Stir in nuts. Add dry ingredients, just until all ingredients are moistened.
Do not overmix.
Turn into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
May frost cake if you wish or it's delicious unfrosted.

title: grandma's oyster stew
directions: Make a hoecake of cornmeal. Cook on top of stove in hot skillet until done.
Cool the hoecake.
Crumble it up and set it aside.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.

In a large bowl, stir all ingredients together until well mixed. Drop from a teaspoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes until centers of cookies are golden brown. (Edges will look darker.)
Cool on cookie sheet about 1 minute, then remove to rack to finish cooling.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Dip pork chops in egg on both sides, then dip in crushed stuffing.
Brown on both sides in frying pan.
Use deep casserole dish.
Put a little water in bottom of dish; stack chops up on end.
Do not lay them down on bottom of dish.
Cover; bake for 1 hour.

title: country gravies
directions: Heat fat in skillet, add flour, salt and pepper.
Stir until mixture is dark brown.
Add cold water.
Simmer approximately 5 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream together sugars and butter. Add eggs.
Mix flour, baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon, cloves and allspice. Add alternately with cider and pumpkin puree. Beat well.
Bake in loaf pan 1 hour at 350°.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients together.
Sift together flour, soda, baking powder and nuts.
Stir well and bake in moderate oven (325°) for 1 hour.
Grease and flour bottom and sides.
Makes 1 large loaf.
Can also add 1/4 cup nuts or 1/4 cup maraschino cherries or 1/2 cup chocolate chips.

title: pecan crescents
directions: Cream butter, sugar and water.
Add vanilla and flour; add pecans.

title: peanut brittle
directions: In a heavy, medium saucepan over medium heat, heat to boiling sugar, corn syrup, salt and water, stirring constantly until sugar dissolves.
Stir in peanuts.
Continue cooking, stirring frequently, until mixture reaches 300° on
a candy thermometer or until a small amount of mixture dropped in cold water separates into hard and brittle threads.
Remove from heat and quickly stir in butter or margarine and baking soda.
Immediately pour into greased cookie sheet.
Cool.
Snap candy into small pieces. Store in tightly covered container.

title: fudge(ho-made and easy)
directions: Line an 8-inch square pan with foil and grease the foil with 1 teaspoon butter; set aside. In a large bowl, combine the powdered sugar, cocoa and salt. Melt remaining butter; add milk and vanilla. Stir into sugar mixture and mix until smooth, then stir in the M&M's. Spread this mixture into the foil-lined pan and refrigerate until firm, at least 2 hours. Lift foil out of pan. Cut fudge into 1-inch squares. Store in airtight container in the refrigerator.

title: bread pudding
directions: Beat eggs until light in color.
Add sugar, milk, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Add vanilla.
Break bread into small pieces in separate bowl.
Add egg mixture and remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour into buttered casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: nacho dip
directions: In round pie plate, spread cream cheese over entire bottom. Cover with salsa and cheese.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1/2 hour or until golden brown.
Serve with nachos to dip.
Enjoy!

title: mexican beef stew
directions: In a Dutch oven, heat oil over medium-high heat until hot. Add beef, half at a time; brown evenly. Pour off drippings. Season with salt, stir in salsa and broth, bring to a boil; reduce heat to low. Cover tightly; simmer 1 1/4 hours or until beef is tender. Stir in zucchini, beans, and corn. Bring to a boil; reduce heat to low, cover tightly; continue cooking 15-20 minutes or until veggies are tender. Add cornstarch mixture; cook and stir 1 minute or until thickened and bubbly. Serve with toppings, if desired.

title: copper pennies
directions: Boil carrots until tender.
Layer carrots, onions and peppers. Combine remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour over carrots and refrigerate overnight.

title: potatoes florentine
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a 2-quart baking dish. Whip the potatoes with cream, sugar, butter, salt and pepper.
Add chives, dill weed or seed and spinach. Beat well. Bake for 20 minutes, uncovered.
Serves 8.

title: monkey knuckles
directions: Cut biscuits in four.
Shake in plastic bag with cinnamon and sugar. Pour melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a Bundt greased pan.

title: michael's sister pizza
directions: Warm metal mixing bowl in hot water, then empty bowl.
In warm bowl, place warm water and sprinkle dry yeast.
Let yeast set until dissolved.
Do not stir.
Add olive oil to yeast and water. Add salt to mixture.
Add flour to mixture.
Blend in mixture on low speed until flour is mixed.
Knead dough on floured surface until dough is not sticky.
(If using a mixer, at least 10 minutes.)
Add olive oil to bowl (just enough to coat dough). Cover dough and let stand in warm place for 1 hour.
Coat pizza pan or cookie sheet with olive oil and corn meal.
Corn meal makes bottom crust crisp.
Push with finger to shape of pan.

title: shrimp cakes
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in butter.
Mix all ingredients together.
Add more shrimp if needed for thicker consistency. Chill in refrigerator until able to form into patties, 2 inches in diameter.
Fry in butter.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together except crackers.
Sprinkle crackers on top. Bake at 350° until crackers are brown.

title: date nut loaf
directions: Combine sugar, dates, cream, milk and salt in deep pan.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Bring to a boil until it reaches soft ball stage.
Remove from fire and add butter and vanilla.
Cool and wrap in wet cloth until hard enough to cut.

title: lime salad
directions: Mix jello, cream cheese, water and marshmallows.
Chill until slightly set.
Add nuts and pineapple.
Chill until firm.

title: bonnie's delicious salad
directions: Mix together oil, vinegar, lemon, garlic, pepper, Parmesan cheese and Worcestershire sauce.
Shake in a jar.
Tear up romaine lettuce.
Add bacon, mushrooms and cheese.
Toss with dressing. Add croutons and toss just before serving.

title: marge mantoni's summer squash casserole
directions: Boil squash and onion for 5 minutes; drain.
Mix soup, sour cream and carrots together in a bowl; pour over squash.
Mix all together.
Melt butter and mix stuffing together.
Take half and cover bottom of casserole dish, then pour squash mixture in pan. Sprinkle rest of stuffing mix on top.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: soap recipe
directions: First put peanut butter on pine cones, well you roll them up. Well you rollin bird seed like Micheal did. Well, you hang pine cones outside for birds. Wait for birds to come.
Get string on cones. Be quiet so birds will come.

title: zesty punch sipper
directions: Combine all ingredients in large punch bowl or 2 large pitchers.
Makes 20 servings.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash broccoli and chop.
Toss with onion, bacon and raisins. Add dressing 1 hour before serving.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt margarine in microwave or saucepan.
Remove from heat and blend in flour, salt and mustard; add milk.
Heat until sauce thickens and is smooth.
Add 1 1/2 cups cheese and heat until melted.

title: cole slaw
directions: Clean and finely grate the cabbage. Place grated cabbage in a colander and drain. Squeeze the moisture from cabbage by handfuls.
Place the squeezed cabbage in a mixing bowl.

title: mushroom salad
directions: Bring water to a boil; add lemon juice.
