Add mushrooms and simmer for three minutes.
Remove from heat and drain.
Combine cream, onion, sugar, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Add mushrooms and toss.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Drain and save liquid; flake salmon.
Combine bread crumbs and seasonings with liquid.
Mix thoroughly.
Pack into small greased loaf pan.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 45 minutes in moderate oven (350°).
Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed on box.
Place 1/2 of baked cake into punch bowl.
Layer with 1/2 of pudding mix, then a layer of chocolate syrup, then a layer of Cool Whip.
Repeat.
Place cherries on top.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Combine all ingredients except butter in a 2-quart casserole dish. Dot with butter.
Cook, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes. Stir. Cover and cook 45 minutes longer.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: cottage potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients with your hands.
Cover with semi-crushed corn flakes.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender.
Drain, add margarine and mash.
Add the remaining ingredients, except the bread crumbs, and mix well. Pour into buttered casserole dish and top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Simmer onion in shortening.
When tender, stir in ground beef and brown lightly.
Add tomato sauce and mixed vegetables.
Season with salt and pepper.
Bring to boil.
Pour in casserole and spread with corn muffin batter.
Bake in 375° oven for 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Serves 4 or 5.

title: cheesy hash browns
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in greased 8 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 1/2 hours.
Can substitute part of cheese with other cheeses.
Also good without veggies and sausage as a side dish.

title: buttermilk yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water, mix with milk and Crisco.
Set aside while sifting all dry ingredients together and add liquid gradually.
Put dough into covered bowl.
Put in refrigerator and use as needed.
Roll amount needed on floured board and cut as biscuits.
No kneading or rising needed.
I let mine rise some. This dough will last several days.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Mix together and put in casserole.
Cook at 300° for 3 hours or 350° for 1 hour.
Add small can sliced mushrooms before serving.
Serve on noodles.

title: pralines
directions: Cook first 6 ingredients in a double boiler to a soft ball stage.
Beat briskly until
the mixture loses its shine.
Quickly stir in pecans.
Quickly, drop on waxed paper in small mounds.

title: chocolate orange mousse
directions: Combine evaporated milk and chocolate, broken, in a small saucepan.
Place over low heat, stirring constantly, or whisk, until chocolate is melted.
Sprinkle gelatin onto water in small bowl.
Allow to soften a few minutes.
Add to hot mixture in saucepan.
Heat to dissolve gelatin.
Cool 5 minutes.
Beat in egg yolks, one at a time.
Stir in orange rind and vanilla.
Chill until mixture mounds from a spoon.
Beat egg whites until foamy; gradually add sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time, beating until meringue is stiff, but not dry.
Fold meringue into chocolate mixture.
Spoon into 6 dessert dishes.
Chill at least 2 hours. Garnish as desired.

title: banana muffins
directions: Mix together; let stand 5 to 10 minutes.
Fill pan 2/3 full with banana mixture.
Let rise for 20 minutes.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: rhubarb wine
directions: *To make liquid yeast, make as follows:
1/2 cake yeast dissolved in hot water to make 1 tablespoon.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well and shape into 2 balls.

title: barbecued chicken wrap
directions: Mix cooked chicken with sauce.
Layer chicken on tortilla. Top with coleslaw or shredded cabbage.
Roll up and eat.

title: chicken or turkey casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients (except bread crumbs) and put in a 13 x 9-inch buttered baking dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 1 hour before baking.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over top and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
After they are well mixed, drop by tablespoon into hot oil.
Using a slotted large spoon, move fritters around in hot oil until they are golden. Remove to paper towels to drain.
Sprinkle with maple syrup and/or powdered sugar.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Mix altogether.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: triple dream shake
directions: In blender, combine banana, juice, ice and milk.
Cover and blend well.
Serve frothy and cold.

title: easy butterscotch chip chocolate cookies
directions: Combine cake mix, oil and eggs in large bowl.
Stir in morsels and pecans.
Drop by tablespoon onto greased baking sheet.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until centers are just set.
Let stand for 2 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Spread rolls in bottom of lightly greased pizza pan, pressing together to line bottom of pan. Top with sausage, potatoes, cheese, onion and green pepper.
Combine eggs, milk and seasonings.
Pour over pizza.
Bake at 370° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: oven "fried" salmon cakes
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray cookie sheet with cooking spray. Beat egg with a fork.
Add remaining ingredients and mix until well blended.
Shape in 8 patties.
Place on the cookie sheet and bake 10 to 12 minutes, turning once until golden brown on both sides.

title: hamburger - bean pie
directions: Cook and stir ground beef and onion until meat is brown and onion tender.
Stir in salt, pepper, beans, and soup.
Bring to boil and stir.

title: spanish omelet sauce
directions: In medium skillet, cook and stir green pepper and onion in butter over low heat until onion is tender.
Stir in tomato sauce, sugar and seasonings.
Simmer 10 minutes or until sauce is thickened.
Keep warm over low heat.
Pour over top of standard omelet.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 9-inch pan; mix in brown sugar and pineapple.
Beat yolks;
add
sugar.
Add flour (with salt and baking powder) alternately with juice.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour over pineapple mixture.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: apple dessert
directions: Melt butter or margarine in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour butter into bowl.
Pour pie filling into pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over this, then the pecans.
Drizzle butter over all.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: blueberry muffins extraordinary
directions: Mix eggs, butter, sugar and sour cream.
Sift dry ingredients together and add blueberries to the mixture.
Fold blueberry flour mix into egg mixture until blended.
Fill greased muffin tins 3/4 full.
Bake at 375° about 25 minutes.
Makes 12 to 14, depending on size of tins.
Sprinkle bits of topping on each muffin.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Coat chicken in melted butter.	Roll in crumb mixture.	Spread on single layer baking sheet that has been coated with oil.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: hot clam dip
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together in saucepan.
Heat through. Add clams and continue to heat until clams are heated through. Serve hot on Triscuits.

title: wild rice soup
directions: Cook wild rice in covered pan with 1 1/2 cups water.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Simmer garlic and onion.
Add carrots; cook until tender.
Add flour; cook over low heat.
Pour in chicken broth.
Add thyme, bay leaf, nutmeg, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Add half and half or milk; heat.
Fold in rice mixture.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Pour sugar over apples and let set for about 30 minutes. Mix in oil, eggs, flour, soda, salt, spices, and flour. Add pecans and mix well. Bake in a greased floured bundt pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: peanut patties
directions: Cook sugar, Karo, peanuts and canned milk to soft ball (230°). Remove from heat and add oleo, vanilla and red food coloring. Beat until begins to thicken and hold shape.
Drop by spoon on buttered waxed paper.

title: hot beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook in a slow cooker 5 to 8 hours.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots until tender.
Drain and cool.
Add chopped onion and green pepper.
Mix remaining ingredients well.
Pour over carrot mixture and chill.
Keeps well for a week or more.

title: hot chicken casserole
directions: Blend meat lightly with mayonnaise, lemon juice and onion; mix.
Add celery and almonds.
Mix it all and put in baking dish. Top with 1 cup crushed potato chips and 1/2 cup grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
I double everything!
Even better leftover and cold.
Great for lunch.

title: rice krispies peanut butter candy
directions: Mix peanut butter, sugar and Karo together.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Then stir in Rice Krispies; mix well. Spread on greased cookie sheet.
Let cool.

title: instant pineapple-upside downs
directions: Melt butter in a skillet.
Add pineapple and sugar, stirring until sugar melts.
Dip one side of each shortcake into mixture. Place each on plate, coated side up.
Spoon pineapple from skillet onto each.

title: sweet-and-sour ribs
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a 2-cup glass measure. Microwave at High, uncovered, 1 minute.
Add barbecue sauce, preserves and vinegar; microwave at High 2 to 3 minutes or until preserves melt.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for an hour or until tender.

title: no bake wonderful pie
directions: Cream the sugar, vanilla and cream cheese together in a bowl. Fold in the Cool Whip.
Layer sliced bananas in bottom of pie crust.
Yummy, yummy.

title: fish dip
directions: Mix well.
Have fish wet and roll in flour mix.
Fry in hot oil.
You may want to use more spice.
If so, add more lemon pepper, red pepper and seasoned salt to your taste.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on package, using 2 (9-inch) round pans.
Cool completely.
Beat egg yolks slightly and pour into heavy 2 to 3-quart saucepan.
Add sugar, butter, vanilla and milk.
Stir together well; cook and stir over medium heat until thickened, about 10 to 12 minutes.
To help thicken, you may add 2 to 3 tablespoons cornstarch.
Add to ingredients before starting to cook.
Remove from heat; add coconut and chopped pecans, stirring well to mix.
Cool completely and spread between layers. Spread the rest over top and sides of cake.

title: tuna-noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles using package directions. Drain. Combine noodles, tuna, mayonnaise, celery, onion, pimento and salt.
Blend cream of celery soup and milk.
Heat through.
Add processed American cheese, shredded. Heat and stir until cheese melts. Add to noodle mixture.
Turn into 2-quart casserole. If desired, top with
with toasted almonds. Bake uncovered at 425° for 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In a
medium pan, melt butter.	Stir in brown sugar and milk. Bring
to
a
boil	and
boil for 2 minutes. Remove from heat. Stir in peanut butter and vanilla.	Mix in confectioners sugar (beat until smooth).
Spread into buttered 9-inch square pan. Chill until firm and cut into squares.

title: drop biscuits
directions: Mix shortening with fork until crumbly.
Add milk.
Mix enough to set dry ingredients. Drop dough from tablespoon on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes until browned. Makes 12 biscuits.

title: applesauce fruitcake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add applesauce, molasses, eggs and lemon juice.
Sift flour with baking soda, salt and spices. Dredge raisins in flour.
Add flour slowly to batter.
Beat.
Add raisins, citron and nuts.
Gumdrops optional.
Bake at 300° to 325° for 2 hours.

title: chocolate crown cake
directions: Melt 1/3
cup
chocolate chips;
set aside.
Grease and flour bottoms of 2 (9-inch) cake pans.
Combine graham cracker crumbs and melted	butter.
Stir in walnuts and 2/3 cup chocolate chips; set
aside.
Combine
flour,
soda	and
salt; set aside.
Cream butter, gradually

Add eggs, one at a time, beating well. Blend in melted chocolate chips
and vanilla.

title: honey brownies
directions: Mix shortening and chocolate together. Add honey, vanilla, sugar and eggs; mix well.
Sift and then combine flour, baking powder and salt with other ingredients.
Place batter in well-greased square pan.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Cool, cut and serve.

title: heath candy bar cake
directions: Mix together the flour, sugar and butter.
Set aside 1 cup of this mixture for topping.
Crush or break into small pieces the 6 candy bars.
Add candy and nuts to flour and sugar mixture.
Mix all other ingredients together and pour into greased and lightly floured baking dish.
Add topping mix and bake for 40 minutes at 350°.
Very rich but delicious.

title: spicy baked beans
directions: Drain beans and combine all into Dutch oven-style roaster. Add brown sugar, tomato soup, tomato paste, barbecue sauce and sausage.
Top with bacon.
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 300°.

title: kosher dill pickles
directions: Mix vinegar, salt and water to rowing boil.
Put garlic buds, pepper and dill in bottom of jar.
Pack cucumbers in jars.
Pour real hot mixture over this and add alum on top; seal.
Allow to settle 4 to 6 weeks before eating.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix altogether and chill until ready to serve.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Line a 9 x 11-inch baking dish with half soft tacos.
Brown hamburger, drain fat.
Add seasoning (follow directions on taco dinner package); mix well.
Add hamburger to baking dish; top with green chilies.
Add remaining soft tacos.
Top with shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Serve like tacos.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Mix well and pour in iron skillet.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: spinach bisque
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large saucepan on stove.
After well blended, transfer to crock-pot, cook on low for 2 hours or until spinach is tender.
If mixture is too thick, you can add some milk.

title: tangerine salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups hot water. Add pineapple and oranges including juice. Pour into serving dish. Immediately sprinkle with marshmallows. Whip cream and fold mayonnaise into it. Smooth over top of marshmallows. Grate cheese and sprinkle over top. Refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken pizzas
directions: Dip chicken in sauce.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes. Separate rolls; roll each one into a 5-inch circle.
Dip chicken in pizza sauce again; roll in cheese.
Place on round of dough. Pull dough around chicken and pinch together, leaving bony end of drumstick uncovered for finger eating.
Bake uncovered for 20 minutes.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Drain beans in strainer.
Pour in 9x13 baking dish.
Fry bacon, drain and put back in skillet and add the ketchup and brown sugar. Mix well, cover and let simmer for approximately 15 minutes.
Pour mixture over beans and mix well.
Bake uncovered for 40 minutes at 350.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: In large skillet, heat 2 tablespoons oil.
Add chicken and half of soy sauce.
Cook until chicken is done, about 5 or 6 minutes; set aside.
In another large skillet, heat remaining oil.
Add vegetables, almonds and remaining soy sauce.
Cook about 7 to 10 minutes.
Add chicken during last few minutes to reheat. Serve with rice.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Combine broccoli, cauliflower and onions.
Toss well.
Combine remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Pour over vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: cheese ball
directions: Dice onion and green pepper very finely.
Mix in cream cheese and pineapple.
Season with salt to taste.
Shape into ball.
Roll in nuts.
Refrigerate about 1 hour.

title: strawberry flans
directions: Sprinkle 1 tablespoon of orange juice in center of each shell. Cover and refrigerate.
Combine remaining juice with strawberries and sugar; mix gently.
Cover and chill 1 hour.
Divide strawberries equally into shells.
Pour over any remaining liquid. Whip the cream until stiff.
Fold in Cointreau.
Spoon over strawberries.
Serve immediately, garnished with whole berries. Yields 6 servings.

title: oat bran fruit muffins
directions: In large mixing bowl combine oat bran, flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix thoroughly; set aside. In small bowl, lightly beat egg with a fork; stir in milk, salad oil and grated orange peel.
Pour all at once into flour mixture; stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fold in apple. Fill 15 greased (with Pam) medium size muffin cups 1/2 full.
Bake in preheated 400° oven until done, about 20 minutes.
Yields 15 muffins, 110 calories each.

title: marinated flank steak
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pierce the flank steak.
Let steak marinate at least 1 hour and up to 8 hours.
Refrigerate while marinating.
Turn periodically.
Broil until done to your liking.

title: cheese and onion pie
directions: Parboil onions in small amount of water.
Drain well.
Blend with beaten eggs, milk, Cheddar cheese, sugar, salt and pepper and a dash of Lawry's seasoning salt, if desired.
Pour into pastry shell; decorate with thin slices of tomatoes.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: outlaw dave's choice
directions: Warm Dr. Pepper in a coffee mug.
Stir in cinnamon stick.
Add maraschino cherry and sprig of green mint.

title: stuffed eggs
directions: Pierce a small hole in the large end of each egg shell and lower the eggs gently into boiling water.
As the water returns to the boil, roll the eggs around for 2 minutes to help set the yolks. Cook for a further 8 minutes.
Drain, then set in cold water until ready to shell.
Shell the eggs; halve them lengthwise and remove the yolks.
Mash the yolks with the remaining ingredients except the breadcrumbs, butter and parsley.
Pipe or spoon the mixture back into the whites.
Sprinkle the breadcrumbs on top and drizzle with melted butter.
Place under preheated broiler for about 3 minutes until crisp and golden brown.
Serve garnished with parsley.

title: cucumber dill dip
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth and add all other ingredients, cucumbers last.
Cover and chill.

title: 3 autumn apple pie
directions: Mix 1/2 cup of sugar, the flour and cinnamon.
Add to half of the apples.
Toss to coat.
Turn apple mixture into pie shell, mounding slightly in center.
Arrange remaining apples on top, slightly overlapping in concentric circles.
Sprinkle with remaining 2 tablespoons of sugar.
Bake on middle rack in preheated 400° oven for 40 to 50 minutes, until crust is browned and apples cooked through.
If necessary, cover the crust with strips of foil to prevent excessive browning.
Stir jelly over low heat until melted; brush on top of hot pie.

title: impossible green bean pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Lightly grease pie plate. Heat beans in 1-inch of salted water (1/2 teaspoon salt to 1 cup water) to boiling. Cook, uncovered, for 5 minutes. Cover and cook until tender (5 to 10 minutes). Drain. Mix beans, mushrooms, onion, garlic and cheese in pie plate. Beat remaining ingredients until smooth (15 seconds in blender on high speed or 1 minute with hand mixer). Pour into pie plate. Bake until golden brown or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean (30 to 35 minutes). Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.

title: pie crust
directions: Using pie blender, cut shortening into flour and salt.
Blend well, then add 3/4 to 1 cup of cold water.
Mix well with fork. Roll out on floured board.
Use generous amount of flour on board. Dough will be sticky.
Makes 2 double crust pies.
For pie shell, bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
For double crust pie with filling, bake at 425° for 10 minutes and then 35 minutes at 350°.
For a nice brown crust, I sprinkle sugar on the unbaked crust.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together on low until thoroughly mixed. Serve with fresh fruit!

title: taco salad
directions: Stir-fry hamburg.
Drain grease.
Add beans.
Put mixture in large bowl.
Add lettuce (chopped), onion (chopped), avocados, 1 cut up tomato and shredded cheese.

title: oyster snack crackers
directions: Mix dry ingredients with crackers.
Add oil and shake until all crackers are covered.

title: blonde christmas fudge
directions: Combine first three items in large saucepan over low heat. Stir constantly.
Bring to boiling point.
Boil gently for 238°. Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla without stirring very much.
Let stand to cool (lukewarm).
Beat until candy no longer shines and starts to hold its shape.
Stir in nuts, cherries and coconut quickly.
Turn into a greased pan and cut into squares.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Mix
together
thoroughly
the shortening, brown sugar, egg yolk
and vanilla.	Stir in salt and flour.
Chill dough. Roll into 1-inch balls.	Place about 1 inch apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake in a 375° oven for 5 minutes.	Remove from oven
and quickly
press
thumb gently on top of each cookie. Return	to oven
and
bake 8 minutes longer.
Cool.
Place in thumbprint
a bit of chopped fruit, jam, tinted confectioners sugar
icing
or Hershey's Kisses.
If desired, sprinkle with confectioners sugar before serving.

title: pearls 'n chocolate cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In large mixing bowl, beat butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla extract until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in white chocolate.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 10 minutes until edges are lightly browned.
Let stand 2 minutes before removing from cookie sheets; cool completely.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: easy noodle pizza
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large deep saucepan, cook noodles to partially cooked stage.

title: fried pies
directions: Put oil in measuring cup. Fill to top with milk. Add salt and baking powder. Work in flour to roll out. Lay a saucer upside down on dough and cut around it. Lay fruit on half of circle. Turn over and pinch edges together to seal. Cook in hot oil on one side. Turn and finish cooking on other side. Drain on paper towel.

title: fresh raspberry cake
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together.
Cream the shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat 1 minute after final addition of eggs.
Add the sour milk and vanilla alternately with the flour mixture.
Mix the pecans and raspberries into a cake batter.
Bake in 2 (8-inch) round pans or a 9 x 13 pan at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Watch carefully.

title: chocolate oatmeal no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, butter, milk and cocoa together and boil for 1 minute; set aside.
Mix together peanut butter, oats and vanilla. Pour candy mixture over oats and vanilla.
Mix and spoon out.

title: beef and cornbread supper
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Brown beef in a 12-inch cast-iron frying pan.
Add soup, onion and Worcestershire sauce and simmer for 5 minutes.
Sift the flour, cornmeal, baking powder and salt together into bowl.
Add shortening and milk and beat until smooth.
Pour over the ground beef mixture and spread to within 1/2-inch of edge of pan.
Top with pepper rings.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat sugar, corn syrup and margarine in large bowl.
Add egg substitute and vanilla; mix well.
Set aside. Combine flour, baking soda and salt in medium bowl.
Add to sugar mixture; mix well.
Form dough into 2 (1 1/2 inch wide) rolls. Wrap in plastic wrap.
Freeze 1 hour.
Line baking sheets with parchment paper.
Cut dough into 1/4 inch thick slices; place 1 inch apart on prepared cookie sheets.
Sprinkle with cookie decorations, if desired.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until edges begin to turn golden brown.
Cool on wire racks.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: stir-fried chicken and snow peas
directions: Blend together soy sauce, sherry, water, ginger and garlic in a bowl.
Mix with chicken and let stand 30 minutes.
Pour oil into electric frying pan or wok.
Heat about 5 minutes, then add the marinated chicken, onions, mushrooms and snow peas.
Saute about 5 minutes, stirring constantly, until the chicken is tender and the vegetables are crisp.
Contains 250 calories per serving.

title: last minute casserole
directions: Butter a 2
1/2 quart casserole dish and add the ingredients in	order
given:
potatoes,
onions, hamburg, noodles, tomatoes, salt, pepper, oregano and parsley.

title: joseph's easy cabbage rolls
directions: Gently remove cabbage leaves.
Simmer leaves in large, covered skillet for about 10 minutes (in water).
While leaves are cooking, mix ground beef and turkey and seasonings.
When leaves are soft, remove from water.
Spoon mixture in leaves and roll. Simmer in covered skillet with 1/2 cup water for about 45 minutes.

title: caramel sauce
directions: Mix flour with brown sugar; mix a little cream with egg yolk. Beat well.
Mix in milk and butter.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Add vanilla at end of cooking.

title: orange roughy in citrus sauce
directions: Put fish in glass bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients except marmalade and arrowroot and mix to dissolve orange juice concentrate.
Reserve 1/2 cup for sauce; pour remaining mixture over fish.
Cover and marinate 45 minutes or longer, turning at least once in refrigerator.
Preheat oven.
Remove fish; place on broiler pan.
Add 3 tablespoons of marmalade to marinade; heat. Broil fish 10 to 15 minutes, until fish flakes, basting several times during cooking.
Heat reserved orange sauce in small saucepan with arrowroot and marmalade until thick.
Pour sauce over fish. Serve.

title: no bake graham cracker fruit cake
directions: Mix together and put in any size loaf pan.
Store in refrigerator.

title: cooked fudge frosting
directions: Combine chocolate, sugar, syrup, salt and milk in buttered 3-quart saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring until sugar dissolves and chocolate melts.
Cook to 234° or until mixture reaches soft ball stage, without stirring.
Remove from heat; add butter (don't stir) and cool until just warm.
Pour into small mixing bowl.
Add vanilla; beat until mixture is of spreading consistency.
Frosts tops and sides of two 8 or 9-inch cake layers.

title: pasta primavera salad
directions: Combine cooked macaroni, broccoli, celery, carrots, onion and green pepper in a large bowl.

title: ham roll casserole
directions: Place broccoli in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover tightly with heavy-duty plastic wrap; fold back a small corner of wrap to allow steam to escape.
Microwave at High 2 to 3 minutes. Rearrange spears.
Cover and microwave at High an additional 3 to 4 minutes.
Drain broccoli and set aside.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and cut eggplant in pieces.
Boil until tender and drain. Mash eggplant and butter.
Add beaten egg, onion, grated cheese, milk, saltines, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Pour into casserole dish and cook 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese coffeecake
directions: Scald milk and water and let cool.
Crumble in 1/2 large cake of yeast; set aside.
Mix together flour, margarine, salt and 4 beaten egg yolks.
Add yeast mixture (dough will be sticky).

title: hot cocoa
directions: Sift cocoa, Quik, and sugar.
Add rest of ingredients.
Shake well.

title: easy gourmet vanilla almond coffee
directions: Add vanilla extract to coffee in a container.
You can shake to mix.
Repeat with almond extract; shake to blend thoroughly.
Brew and enjoy.

title: mock filet mignon
directions: Place bacon on piece of wax paper so that edge of one overlaps the other.
Combine beef, onion, egg and cheese.
Season with ketchup, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Mix, then press and form into an approximate 10-inch roll.
Place roll on bacon strips; wrap bacon around roll and fasten with toothpicks.
Slice so that pieces of bacon circle each patty.
Broil or grill about 5 minutes on each side.
Serves 10.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Drain Veg-All and mix with next four ingredients.
Pour into an 8 x 8 baking dish.	Sprinkle top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Pour melted margarine over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Mix together sugar, flour, eggs, soda, nuts, and pineapple. Bake at 350 for 45 minutes.

title: pam's corn casserole
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Pour into 2 bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: mustard glazed chicken
directions: Combine ingredients and pour over cut up chicken in shallow dish; cover and refrigerate overnight.
Drain off marinade; save. Bake or microwave chicken until almost done.
Put on grill until brown, basting with marinade.
Just before serving, brush with mixture of 1/4 cup honey and 1/2 teaspoon mustard.

title: fat free vegetable soup
directions: Combine water, cabbage, potatoes, and onion in a large soup pot.
Cook over medium heat until potatoes are tender but not mushy.
Add remaining ingredients and let simmer for about 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: hannah cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, salt and soda into a bowl.
Put water, cocoa and oleo in pan and bring to a boil.
Add all at once to sugar and flour mixture.
Mix well. Add vanilla.
Add eggs and sour cream.
Mix well. Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 375° for 22 to 25 minutes.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together; add egg yolks.
Beat in all remaining ingredients except jelly.
Form into balls, indent with your thumb, and fill imprint with jelly.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350 degrees for approximately 8 - 9 minutes.

title: easy lemon chicken
directions: In a skillet brown chicken in 2 tablespoons vegetable oil. Pour off fat:add gravy, lemon, thyme and vegetables. Cover and cook on low heat for 5 minutes or until done. Spoon into pastry shells. Serves 6.

title: hidden valley ranch oyster crackers
directions: Combine Hidden Valley Ranch salad dressing mix with dill weed and oil.
Pour over crackers; stir to coat.
Place in a warm 250° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir gently halfway through baking. Excellent as an appetizer or snack, even great in soup.

title: dried apple stack cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and soda.
Stir eggs and buttermilk together; add to dry ingredients.
Stir in softened margarine and vanilla.
Make dough stiff enough to roll or pat flat in 5 or 6 greased cake pans.
(You may need to add a little more flour to be able to handle dough.)
Bake at 450° for 7 minutes or until brown.
Spread each layer with cooked sweetened dried apples.
Add cinnamon, if desired.
Pour brown sugar glaze on top layer.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Line casserole dish with carrots.
Sprinkle sugar over, dot with margarine.
Pour Cheez Whiz over.
Top with crushed crackers. Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: chile rellenos casserole
directions: Split, seed and rinse chiles.
Drain on paper towel.
Beat eggs and flour, then beat in half and half.
Mix cheeses together. Reserve 1/2 cup.
In lightly greased 2-quart casserole, layer chiles, cheese and egg mixture, 3 layers.
Pour tomato sauce over top and sprinkle reserved cheese on top.
Bake in microwave on High 25 to 30 minutes.
Let stand a few minutes before serving.
Or bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: hot chicken chunks
directions: Cut chicken into chunks.
Coat chicken with Cajun seasoning. Fry in hot oil until juices run clear.
Place a blob of yogurt on each dinner plate; dip chicken chunks in the yogurt as you eat.

title: hawaiian fruit pie
directions: Mix together pineapple, sugar and flour; bring to a boil. Remove from heat and add 1 package of orange jello.
Then add cherries, bananas and pecans.
Pour into pie shells.
Refrigerate. Top with Cool Whip when ready to serve.
Serves 12.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients except the dressing, then pour the dressing over them.
Toss before serving.
Best when set overnight.

title: party punch
directions: Combine all ingredients, except 7-Up.
Add 7-Up before serving.
Serves 30 to 40.

title: harvest casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat, onion and pepper.
Cook macaroni and cheese separately as directed.

title: oysters rockefeller casserole
directions: Cook and drain spinach thoroughly.
Stir it in hot butter over moderately high heat to evaporate excess moisture.
Mix anchovy paste with seasonings and blend with spinach.
Combine with oysters and spinach.
Spoon into a shallow casserole dish, top with cheese and bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until bubbly. Serve immediately.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Cut tortillas into small pieces.
Cut chicken meat into bite size pieces.
Mix together soups, milk, onion and broth from cooking chicken.
In a large greased pan, layer half of the following:
tortilla pieces, chicken meat, soup mix, salsa and cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake, uncovered, at 300° for 1 hour.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Save broth.
Debone chicken; set aside.

title: grandma's cabbage rolls(hungary)
directions: Put cabbage leaves and 1 cup water in large pot and steam until wilted.
Remove leaves and set aside.
Mix pork, rice, salt and pepper until combined thoroughly.
Place mound of meat mixture onto each cabbage leaf.
Roll loosely.
Fold sides to form roll. Put sauerkraut into large pot.
Layer cabbage rolls on top of kraut.
Pour over tomato juice.
Cook over medium heat for 2 hours.

title: homemade rye bread
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water.
Add remaining ingredients--adding just enough white flour so dough springs back to touch when kneading.
Cover and let rise until doubled.
Punch down and let rise again.
Divide dough into loaves.
Put into greased loaf pans filling pans about 1/3 full.
Let rise until 2/3 full.
Bake at 350 - 375 degrees for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: norwegian meat pie
directions: Baking Temperature: 400° and 350°.
Baking Time: 15 minutes and 30 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well; form into ball and chill.

title: rice pudding
directions: Pour 1 inch of hot water into a larger baking pan and place custard filled bowl or cup in water.
Bake in oven at 325° for about 3/4 of an hour.

title: strawberry slush
directions: Boil 7 cups water and 3 cups sugar.
Let cool.
Boil 2 cups water and pour over 4 tea bags.
Let cool.
In a blender, add cranberry juice, orange juice, lemonade and strawberries.
Add this the blender mixture to the cooled mixtures.
Freeze in an ice cream pail.
Mix with ginger ale, 7-Up or lemon-lime soda in individual glasses for a refreshing summer drink.

title: peanut butter delights
directions: Melt margarine over medium heat.
Add sugar, cocoa and milk. Mix well.
Stirring often, bring to rolling boil.
When it begins to boil, let stay on heat for only 1 minute.
After the minute of boiling, remove from heat and cool for 1 minute.
Add vanilla, salt, peanut butter and oatmeal.
Mix well.

title: cheddar stuffed potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut potatoes in half.
Spoon out center of potatoes, being careful not to break shells.

title: creamy broccoli bisque
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Blend in nutmeg and flour dissolved in 1/2 cup water.
Gradually stir in milk and remaining water. When mixture begins to cream, add cubed Velveeta and thawed broccoli (I like to cook broccoli slightly and drain well). Simmer until cheese is melted.
Makes 12 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: ranger casserole
directions: Brown first three ingredients in skillet then drain all fat and add rest of the ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Grease casserole and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until rice is tender.
Serve with a green tossed salad and buttery French bread.

title: glorified rice
directions: Mix jello as directed, using 2 cups scant water.
Cook rice and set aside.
Let jello stand until thick enough to whip smooth. Add pineapple and Cool Whip.
Mix together.
Add rice and powdered sugar.
Mix well and refrigerate.
Nuts may be added.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Boil water and add sugar and tartar; let boil.
Take pot off stove and add crackers; do not stir.
Boil for 2 minutes; shake pan only.
Pour into pie shell and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Dab with butter and put top crust on.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cream cheese fruit squares
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In medium saucepan, place 1/4 cup sugar and butter; heat until butter is melted, stirring occasionally. Stir in graham crumbs; press mixture evenly over the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
In a large bowl with an electric mixer, beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in remaining 3/4 cup sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time and vanilla until well blended.
Spoon blueberry filling evenly over crust.
Pour cream cheese over berries.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes.
Makes 24 squares.

title: pineapple sandwiches
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and place pineapple on a plate. Using the can, cut bread into circles.
Spread mayo (thin layer) on bread.
Add 1 pineapple ring, then cherry to center of ring.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Drain hamburger.
Add green chilies, taco seasoning and 1 cup of water; let cook for a few minutes.
Chopped onions may be added, if desired.
Crumble corn chips and place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch
pan, spraying pan first with nonstick coating. Layer meat and cheese on top of taco chips alternately until all used.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Garnish with sour cream, olives and green onion.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cube bread in bottom of pan.
Fry sausage and pour over bread. Top with cheese.
Pour egg and milk mixture over the top. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: egg nog
directions: In large bowl, beat egg yolks with electric mixer on medium-high speed until thick and lemon colored, about 5 minutes. Slowly beat in sugar, beat 5 minutes.
Slowly beat in bourbon in a slow, steady stream.
Beat in cream and milk; add vanilla.
In medium bowl, beat egg whites until medium stiff peaks form.
Fold beaten egg whites into yolk mixture.
To serve, add 1/4 cup ice to punch cups.
Add egg nog and top with nutmeg.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat
and
drain.
Add
remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.	Reduce	heat
and simmer 2 to 3 hours.	Pour over spaghetti.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Cream peanut butter, shortening and vanilla.
Beat in sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Alternately add dry ingredients and milk, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Bake in 3 greased and floured 9-inch layer cake pans.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until cake shrinks from sides of pans.
Cool layers on a rack and then frost with Crunchy Topping Frosting. Makes 1 (9-inch) cake.

title: mayonnaise cake(chocolate)
directions: Measure into bowl the dry ingredients.
Add water, mayonnaise and vanilla.
Pour into 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Nice and moist.

title: lemon cake
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Refrigerate while mixing cake. Mix cake mix, oil, eggs and lemon juice.
Add dissolved Jell-O to cake mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute onion, garlic and butter; add meat and brown.
Add flour, salt, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook 5 minutes and add soup. Simmer uncovered 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream and parsley. Heat thoroughly.
Serve over cooked noodles or rice.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar; add enough milk to moisten well.
Beat until no small lumps of flour or sugar remain.
Add egg yolks and mix well.
Add remaining milk and stir.
Cook in a double boiler or on top of stove at medium heat.
If on stove top, stir constantly as it will scorch easily.
Remove from heat when it thickens.
Add butter and vanilla.
Stir well; pour into baked pie shell.
Use egg whites for your favorite meringue.
Put in oven until slightly brown.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Put pork chops in a casserole dish.
Pour in soup. Bake until pork chops are done.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Microwave butter, brown sugar, Karo syrup and salt 3 minutes. Stir. Microwave 2 more minutes. Stir. Add baking soda. Stir. Put popcorn in doubled brown paper bag. Pour mixture over popcorn. Shake for 20 seconds. Put bag in microwave for 45 seconds. Take out and shake. Microwave 45 more seconds. Shake. Spread on wax paper to cool.

title: scottish shortbread
directions: Cream butter and sugar together thoroughly.
Add flour sifted with baking powder and salt; blend until smooth.
Roll or pat to 1/4-inch thickness on floured surface.
Cut with 2-inch cutter or in pie pans (must score before baking).
Place on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Do not brown! Makes 5 dozen.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar together.
Add egg and mix. Combine the dry ingredients in a medium bowl.
Add to the creamed mixture and blend.
Grease 10 muffin cups.
Fill cups about 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: 30 second pizza
directions: Layer in order listed after toasting muffin.
With paper napkin or plate put muffin layered with toppings in microwave for 20 to 30 seconds.
Watch through the door for melting or bubbling since timing varies with amount and type of filling used. Sandwiches topped with cheese heat rapidly.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook together water, sugar, cornstarch and Jell-O.
Cook until clear.
Cool and pour over berries and pour into pie shell.
Put in refrigerator until thickened and firm.
Serve with topping of choice.

title: rice casserole
directions: Melt
margarine.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: bloody mary dip
directions: In a medium bowl, combine ingredients.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours until well chilled.
Serve as a dip for raw vegetables, seafood or meat.

title: squash casserole
directions: Dice squash and precook.
Saute bell pepper and onions together.
Put squash in bottom of dish.
Place onions and bell peppers on top of squash.
Put soup on thin grated cheese.
Top with bread crumbs and butter.
Cook 30 minutes at 225°.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together in a bowl.
Slowly add the milk, stirring to mix thoroughly.
Pour mixture into a heavy saucepan after you rub some margarine around the inside.
Bring slowly to a gentle boil; turn heat down to low and cook until gravy consistency.
Pour over hot, buttered buttermilk biscuits and get a belly ache and gain 5 pounds.
Ha!
Ha!

title: rice nair casserole
directions: Remove chilies from can; slit and open flat.
Remove seeds and strings; let drain on paper towel.
Cut into 1/2-inch squares. Add to sour cream with 1/2 of sliced olives.
Cut cheese into 1-inch strips. Season rice with salt and pepper.

title: baked steak
directions: Cut beef or chicken into serving-size portions (I use cubed steaks).
Combine flour, cornmeal and seasonings in a paper bag. Shape pieces of meat to coat.
Dip each piece in melted margarine, then roll each in crumb and cracker mixture.
Bake, uncovered, in a baking pan prepared with nonstick cooking spray at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: beef brisket
directions: Rub both sides of brisket with garlic salt, celery salt, onion salt, sugar, liquid smoke and Worcestershire sauce.
Wrap lightly in foil in both directions.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: divinity candy
directions: Boil
sugar,
corn
syrup
and	water together until it forms a hard ball when dropped in cold water.
Beat egg whites at high speed
until
a peak is formed when beater is raised. Continue beating while pouring sugar mixture in a thin stream over
egg whites.
Beat
until
the mixture passes the glossy stage.	Add vanilla
and
drop	by
spoonfuls onto wax paper. Let cool	and eat
(not too much) it's good.
Add nuts if you want to, when you add vanilla.
Don't make on a rainy day.

title: texas punch
directions: Mix together and serve over ice.

title: apricot chicken(quick and easy)
directions: Cook apricots until tender; cool and chop.
Place chicken pieces in baking dish.
Mix apricots, soup mix and dressing; pour over chicken.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for one hour.
Serves 8.

title: turkey loaf
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk.
Add turkey, broth, salt, rice, pimiento and celery; add well beaten eggs.
Pour into a buttered loaf pan.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: long johns
directions: Work like bread dough.
Let rise until about double in size. Roll out and cut in strips and let rise again.
Bake until light brown.
Cool, then cut them through the middle.
Fill with filling and spread over top.

title: spaghetti pizza lasagna
directions: Combine cooked spaghetti, milk and eggs.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix tomato soup and spaghetti sauce together and spread over spaghetti.
Brown hamburg.
Season with salt and pepper.
Put hamburg over spaghetti sauce.
Add a layer of pepperoni next.
Top with cheese.
Bake uncovered for 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: quick rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients into yeast that has been dissolved in warm water.
Set aside for 30 minutes, covered, in a warm place.
Spoon into greased muffin pans.
Fill half full.
Set aside and let rest 30 minutes more.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 12 rolls.

title: baked meatballs
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cover cookie sheet with foil, then spray with nonstick cooking spray.
Mix all ingredients.
Make small balls out of mixture.
Place on prepared cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: in-a-hurry mexican stew
directions: Add water to desired thickness; simmer.
Serve with tortilla chips or flour tortillas.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Boil
in double boiler until thick.
Cool in refrigerator. Top with whipping cream.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Melt oleo and chips.
When melted, add the sugar and beat well.
Add eggs and beat again.
Add rest of ingredients.
Pour into baked pie shells and bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Do not refrigerate!
This makes 2 pies.

title: crustless quiche lorraine
directions: Sprinkle bacon, onion and cheese in quiche pan.
Combine eggs, sugar, milk and cayenne pepper and beat until well blended.
Pour combined mixture over mixture in quiche pan.
Cook on Medium for 13 to 14 1/2 minutes or on High for 9 minutes.
Stir two times during first half of cooking time.
Let stand, covered, for 10 minutes to complete cooking.

title: orange julius
directions: Blend slightly in blender.
Add 12 to 15 ice cubes.
Continue to blend until slushy.

title: low-fat fried chicken(4 grams of fat)
directions: Ground turkey is available in two forms: lean ground turkey and ground turkey breast.
Lean ground turkey contains both white and dark meat and has 7 grams of fat per 3 1/2-ounce uncooked serving with 45% of the calories coming from fat.
Ground turkey breast contains 100% white meat and 1 gram of fat per 3 1/2-ounce uncooked serving with only 9% of the calories from fat.

title: light minute cherry cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in sugar. Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping.
Blend well.
Spoon into crust.
Chill until set (about 4 hours). Garnish with fresh strawberries, if desired.
(Cherry topping can be used.)

title: yum-a-setta
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add
salt,
pepper and brown sugar to taste. Add
tomato
soup.
Cook
noodles; drain.	Add a layer hamburger mixture,
then noodle mixture and cheese in a casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: country store slaw
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, celery seed, mustard seed and turmeric. Bring to a boil.
Pour over cabbage mixture while hot.
Will keep in refrigerator as long as two weeks.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed.
Melt butter.
Stir all together and pour in a greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, uncovered.
Remove from oven and top with Ritz cracker crumbs; bake for 15 minutes more.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Beat together then add: 2 tsp. baking powder and mix enough flour into mixture to make a soft dough.
Make dumplings.

title: old tyme dumplings
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt into a large bowl; add milk and mix with a fork.
Drop by heaping tablespoonfuls into boiling chicken broth.
Cover; cook 12 minutes (no longer, no peeking).

title: fruit punch
directions: Sweeten to taste and add lemon parts.

title: salsa
directions: Making fruit sauces is one of the easiest things a cook can do.
Some are cooked but most are not.
All you do is puree or mash the fruit of your choice, then turn your creative juices loose.
Fruit sauces are used with cakes, ice cream, fish, poultry, meats--you name it.
You can substitute fruits in most of these recipes.

title: tutti-frutti ice cream
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; blend well.
Add milk and water, stir slightly.
Pour mixture into freezer can of a 1-gallon freezer.
Freeze according to manufacturer's instructions.
Allow ice cream to ripen at least 1 hour.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions.
Pour 1/2 of batter in an oblong greased cake pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
While cake is baking, melt caramels and margarine in milk.
Pour over baked cake.
To remaining cake batter, add the chocolate chips and pecans.
Pour over caramel layer.
Bake for 20 minutes longer.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except for potatoes.
Drain potatoes and place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish and pour mixture over potatoes.

title: hazelnut tulipes with ice cream
directions: Special occasions are just that.
A holiday, good friends getting together or
a family reunion are just a few of the reasons for making a party.

title: chicken divan
directions: Boil chicken breasts with celery, carrots and quartered onions for 1 hour or until tender.
Drain chicken.
Cool and slice.
Cook or microwave broccoli while chicken is cooking.
Drain well.
Put broccoli into large pan (9 x 13-inch or 11 x 13-inch).
Cover with chicken and cover chicken with sliced onions.
Mix soup and sour cream; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes, uncovered.
I serve this with rice, noodles or linguine, tossed salad with vinaigrette dressing and French bread.

title: white chicken gravy
directions: In the frying pan used to fry chicken, take a fork and loosen chicken crumbles.
Make sure the bottom is covered in chicken drippings (at least 1/2 cup).
Add flour, milk, salt and pepper. Stir constantly, until bubbling and thick.
Serve over potatoes or biscuits.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and pour into greased and floured baking pan of choice. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: kool-aid play dough
directions: Mix flour, salt, oil and Kool-Aid. Add 1 cup boiling water; stir and knead until soft dough forms.

title: banana milk shake
directions: Peel and mash bananas.
Add milk and vanilla, and beat until well-blended.
Pour into tall glasses.
Add scoop of ice cream. Serves 2.

title: dog biscuits
directions: Most of our horses will not eat any type of medication in their feed.
So whenever necessary, I mix the pills, powdered, with a small amount of King or Karo syrup.
A large wormer syringe, washed thoroughly, will easily draw up and dispense the sticky preparation.
In extremely cold weather, I sometimes warm the syrup or add a bit of warm water.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together and form into ball.
Roll into crushed walnuts.

title: homemade yeast
directions: Pour the boiling potato water over the flour, salt, ginger and sugar; mix.
Then add potatoes, which have been mashed while hot. When this is lukewarm, add the cake of yeast, which has been soaked in a little lukewarm water.
Let the mixture work about 18 hours in a warm place, then stir in cornmeal until the batter becomes thick enough to mold into cakes.

title: brisket and wild rice in wine
directions: Place brisket in roasting pan with 4 cups of water, wine and Gravy Master.
Top meat with onion soup and sliced onion.
Cover and cook in slow 325° oven for 2 hours.
Remove from oven and add cup of wild rice.
Return to oven for about 1 hour more until meat is tender and most of gravy is absorbed but still juicy. Slice meat across the grain.
Mound rice around meat on platter and garnish with broiled tomatoes (optional).
Delicious company fare.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Mix flour and white sugar together; roll raw potatoes in mixture and place in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Turn every 15 minutes and sprinkle with brown sugar as you turn them.

title: shrimp salad(makes 8 servings)
directions: Combine all ingredients; toss lightly to mix.
Serve on salad greens.

title: mozzarella meat loaf
directions: Mix everything together, except cheese.
Flatten mixture out on waxed paper.
Spread cheese down the middle.
Fold sides over cheese; seal seams.
Flip over, seam side down, into pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until done.
Can put additional cheese and pizza sauce on top.

title: raisin sauce for ham
directions: Mix apple juice and cornstarch together in saucepan until well mixed with whisk.
Stir in sugar and cinnamon.
Heat over medium heat until thick and bubbly.
Stir in raisins.

title: trifle
directions: Whip together whipping cream, vanilla, and sugar.
Layer cake, strawberries, pudding and cream in a trifle bowl.

title: lobster newburg
directions: Cut lobster meat into bite size pieces and set aside.
Heat the butter in the food pan and fry the mushrooms for 2 minutes. Stir in the paprika and tomato paste.
Add the lobster and cook until hot.
Thicken the sauce with the cornstarch, stirred into the cold vermouth.
Serve on a bed of rice.

title: almond cheddar bread
directions: Mix 1 cup mayonnaise and 2 teaspoon Worcestershire sauce.
Stir in sharp cheddar cheese, onion, almonds, and bacon.
Spread onto baguette bread.
Place onto a greased baking sheet.
Bake on 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly; roll in wax paper. Refrigerate.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Cook sliced raw beef in sauce after browning the beef with onions or cook whole roast and onions in sauce.
Shred after cooking.
Cook at 325° for 1 to 2 hours or until meat easily shreds.

title: cordon bleu chicken
directions: Debone chicken and remove skin.
Wrap around 1/2 slice Swiss cheese and 1 slice ham.
Dip in melted butter, then crumbs.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 375°.

title: strawberry chiffon pie
directions: Mix gelatin, 3/4 cup sugar and salt in top of double boiler. Stir in milk, stirring with whisk until gelatin is dissolved. Stir in well beaten egg yolks while stirring briskly.
Cook until mixture coats a spoon.
Remove from heat.
Divide between 2 bowls. Add cream cheese and half the lemon juice to one and beat until smooth.
Pour into pie shell.

title: taffy
directions: Boil until it forms a hard ball in hot water or 260°.
Pour into buttered platter.
Pull when cool.

title: barbecued beef short ribs
directions: Brown short ribs.
Brown onion and celery in butter.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer until slightly thickened.
Pour sauce over short ribs and cook in slow oven until ribs are tender.

title: apple-sour cream pie
directions: Line a 9-inch pie plate with pastry.
Combine egg, sugar, brown sugar and sour cream.
Stir in cored, pared and thinly sliced apples and raisins.
Turn into pastry shell.
Add lattice top; seal edges and flute.
Bake in a 400° oven for 50 minutes or until done, covering edges with foil during last 15 minutes baking time.

title: tuna macaroni casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni dinner according to directions on box.
In a separate bowl, put tuna (drained) and break up with a fork.
Add egg, mustard and onion.
Mix well.
Add tuna mixture to cooked macaroni.
Pour into buttered 2-quart baking dish. Add enough milk to make it more moist.
Can add more shredded cheese, if desired. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Very good served with catsup.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil the first 4 ingredients together slowly for 5 minutes, then add peanut butter, Marshmallow Fluff and vanilla.
Quickly stir all together.
After mixed well, pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: frozen salad
directions: Mix together and freeze overnight. Salad can be cut while frozen.

title: apple pandowdy
directions: Fill a 1 1/2-quart Pyrex dish with apples.
Sprinkle on brown sugar and spices. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until apples are soft. Cream the butter.
Gradually add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add egg and beat well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Beat until smooth.
Spread on cooked apples. Bake 25 to 30 minutes. Serve with cream while warm.

title: chocolate caramel drizzled cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar, eggs, and vanilla with mixer.
Mix until your patience runs out because you want to get it as smooth as possible.
Next, take 1/2 of the mixture and put it in to your pie crust.
Try to level it out in the pie plate.
With the last 1/2 of your mixture, add hot fudge. Mix together and spoon that mixture on top of the mixture already in the pie plate.
Finally, swirl the mixtures together with a knife.Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes. Let it cool for 1 hour. Place in the fridge for at least 2 hours before serving.

title: asparagus loaf
directions: Mix all except butter.
Pour into greased pan.
Melt butter; pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: maple ice cream(people from abroad savor this native american flavor!)
directions: Cream butter and add vanilla.
Add sifted confectioners sugar. Add flour and then stir in nuts.
Dough may be a little dry (it will work together when you make your balls).
Roll into small balls.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until just browned on bottom.
Roll in sifted confectioners sugar while still hot.

title: sweet relish
directions: Chop cucumbers, onions and peppers fine and add salt.
Let set overnight covered with water.
In the morning, drain and add vinegar, sugar and celery seed.
Cook 1 hour and can in hot jars.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix crust ingredients and press into buttered 13 x 9 inch baking dish.

title: chocolate pie-pie
directions: Melt margarine in pan.
Add other ingredients.
Stir over medium heat until it thickens.
Great over Mama's hot biscuits!

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Bake crust of crescent rolls for 10 minutes at 350° or bread dough for 10 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Boil cabbage leaves and drain.
Mix remaining ingredients. Place inside the cabbage leaves.
Cook at 350° for 2 1/2-3 hours. Add butter when finished.

title: low cholesterol sugar cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
In large bowl, beat eggs.
Stir in oil and vanilla.
Blend in sugar.
Add flour mixture.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased sheet 2-inches apart. Flatten each cookie with oiled glass.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet immediately.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Mix sugar, oil, egg and pumpkin.
Sift flour and add other ingredients and add other ingredients all together mix add 1/2 c golden raisins, 1/2 cup english walnuts, grease muffin pans.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: chicken croissants
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Crush croutons.
In a separate bowl, mix together cream cheese, mushrooms, olives and onion.
Stir in diced chicken.
Fill crescent rolls with mixture and roll.
Dip crescent rolls in melted butter and roll in crushed croutons. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 25 minutes.
Makes 16 croissants.

title: mini pizza
directions: Grease a cookie sheet; spread each biscuit out on the cookie sheet.
Put as much tomato sauce as desired, then sprinkle cheese on pizza.
Add a dash of oregano.
Bake at 425° for about 10 minutes.
Serve immediately.
These may be used for snacks or cook an extra 10 for a meal.

title: cherry, pineapple dump cake
directions: Put ingredients in order given, pie filling, pineapple, cake mix, oleo, coconut and pecans,
in	a
x
9-inch pan. Smooth each layer.
Bake at 350°
for
1 1/4 hours or until it tests done.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: five layered salad
directions: Layer, serve and enjoy.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut pepper in half lengthwise.
Remove seeds and wash. Combine beef, cooked rice, onion, salt, pepper and 1/2 can Hunt's tomato sauce.
Put mixture into peppers in large baking dish. Pour Hunt's tomato sauce over each pepper.
Cover tightly and bake in moderate oven (350°) for 1 1/4 hours or until peppers are tender, basting occasionally.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Bring water to boil. Add Jell-O and stir until it has been completely dissolved. Add all other ingredients. Chill. Top with sour cream.

title: spinach curry tofu burrito
directions: Saute tofu (cut into small pieces) in olive oil with curry and garlic added, until cooked.
Steam spinach until done.

title: hamburger heaven
directions: Brown meat slightly in skillet.
Season with onion salt, salt and pepper to taste.
Add remaining ingredients in layers in order given (slice the cheese, chop the celery, slice the olives, small can).
Use No. 2 can tomatoes.
Rinse tomato can with 1/4 cup water and pour over all.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cook on high heat until steaming.
Reduce to low or simmer and cook for 10 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together and place in greased baking dish.
Cover with bread crumbs and butter.
You can use extra cheese.
Bake 30 minutes in 375° oven.

title: pie shell for chocolate pie
directions: Slice 1/4-inch thick and line a 9-inch pie pan.
Overlap slices or place close together.
Bake according to package directions; cool.
Pour favorite chocolate filling into crust. Refrigerate.
Top with Cool Whip or ice cream.
Serves 6.

title: cinnamon coffee cake
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with 1/3 cup sugar and 1 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Dot with butter (approximately 8 teaspoons).
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: pudding cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients until dough forms a ball.
Shape by teaspoonfuls into balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Dip fork tines into some sugar and flatten balls slightly.
Bake for about 8 minutes.
Makes about 2 1/2 or 3 dozen.

title: cream cheese squares
directions: Combine first four ingredients.
Flatten in 8 x 8-inch pan (reserving 1 cup for topping).
Bake for approximately 12 minutes. Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour onto baked crust.
Cover with reserved topping.
Return to oven for approximately 25 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven, cool, cut into squares.
These squares freeze well.

title: double scotch pecan bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add alternately with milk.
Fold in butterscotch pieces, coconut and pecans.
Spread in ungreased 11 x 14-inch pan. Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Pare apples.
Slice thin. Put in 8-inch pan.
Combine dry ingredients; cut in butter. Sprinkle over apples. Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve same day if want crisp topping. May add ice cream or other topping.

title: marlene's gingerbread muffins
directions: Cream sugar and shortening well; add egg and molasses.
Sift dry ingredients together and mix into creamed mixture, 1/2 dry ingredients, then hot water and end with other 1/2 dry ingredients.
Bake in muffin papers in muffin tin at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: one crust 9-inch pie shell
directions: Sift flour and salt together.
Cut in shortening, using 2 knives or pastry blended until size of small peas.
Sprinkle water over mixture, while tossing gently with fork, until particles stick together.
For ease in rolling out pastry, wrap dough in waxed paper and allow to chill in refrigerator.
Lightly roll pastry into circle 1-inch larger than pie plate.
Lift loosely into pie plate.
Pat out air.
Fold edges under and crimp.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together, then serve.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut all ingredients as if for salad.

title: almond fruit tart
directions: Cream butter and 1/2 cup sugar.
Beat in yolk, one teaspoon vanilla and 1/2 teaspoon almond extract.
Mix in flour and almonds to form dough.
Press into 11-inch tart pan or medium pizza pan. Prick shell.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Cool and reserve.

title: sarge's kale
directions: Strip and clean kale.
Steam until very tender.
In saucepan saute onion and garlic in olive oil.
Add tomato sauce and water. (Can add a little red wine.)
Simmer about 10 minutes.
Add kale; simmer a little longer.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Blend cream cheese, margarine and sugar.
Add vanilla and salt.
Blend.
Add some milk, if necessary, to spreading consistency.
Goes deliciously with carrot cake.

title: no-bake chocolate cookies
directions: Boil sugar, cocoa, butter and milk for 1 minute.
Add other ingredients and beat 1 minute.
Spoon out on waxed paper to cool. Makes about 2 dozen cookies.
Enjoy!

title: broccoli and raisin salad
directions: Combine broccoli, onion, bacon, cheese and raisins in a bowl. Blend mayo, sugar and vinegar in a small bowl.
Pour over broccoli mixture.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill for 4 hours.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Thoroughly cream the first 3 ingredients.
Add the beaten eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Sift the flour, baking soda and salt; add to cream mixture.
Add the oats and walnuts.
Form in long rolls.
Chill thoroughly.
Slice 1/4-inch thick.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 10 minutes.
Keeps well.

title: shrimp cocktail appetizer
directions: Put cream cheese in a bowl, pour cocktail sauce over it, then put shrimp over that.
Serve with Ritz or crackers of your choice.

title: layered blueberry delight
directions: Line 9-inch square pan with graham crackers.
Mix pudding as directed.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Then blend in Cool Whip.
Spread half of this and half of the pie filling over the crackers.
Add another layer of crackers and the rest of the pudding and then the pie filling.
Chill for 3 hours.

title: unbaked coconut cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in cold water.
Beat egg yolks.
Add flour, salt and milk and cook until it coats spoon.
Remove from fire; add gelatin.
Chill 1 hour.
Beat egg whites until stiff; add.

title: chicken jambalaya
directions: Brown chicken in oil. Add onions, celery and green pepper and saut until onions are transparent. Add rice, water, salt and pepper. Cover and reduce heat. Simmer for 1 hour. Add extra water as needed.

title: winter vegetable casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and place in greased casserole. Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Cover with Ritz crackers and cover Ritz crackers with melted butter. Bake another 15 minutes.

title: creamy chocolate layered pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar in large bowl with wire whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in 1 1/2 cups of the whipped topping.
Spread on bottom of crust.
Pour 1 1/2 cups milk into bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat with wire whisk 1 minute. (Mixture will be thick.)
Stir in 2 cups of the whipped topping. Spread over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate 4 hours or until set. Garnish with remaining whipped topping.
Store leftover pie in refrigerator.

title: cherry fruit salad
directions: Mix cherries, cream cheese and pineapple.
Fold in Cool Whip, pecans and marshmallows.

title: elegant beef tenderloin
directions: Place tenderloin on a lightly greased, shallow roasting pan; sprinkle with garlic salt.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Combine wine, soy sauce, butter and lemon pepper seasoning in a small saucepan; cook until mixture is thoroughly heated.
Pour over tenderloin; bake an additional 30 to 40 minutes or until a thermometer registers 140° (rare), basting occasionally with pan drippings.
(Bake until thermometer registers 150° for medium rare or 160° for medium.)
If desired, garnish with grapes, celery leaves and lemon zest.

title: cranberry-apple crisp
directions: For a higher ratio of fruit to crust, use 4 cups of cranberries, 3 apples and 2/3 cup sugar.

title: lemon herb asparagus
directions: Steam asparagus with little water in covered pot 5 to 8 minutes or until tender.
In separate pan, heat olive oil and herbs on medium heat just until heated through.
Remove from heat. Stir in lemon juice.
Drizzle over asparagus on serving dish.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt cream cheese and butter in milk.
Add this to corn and chilies.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: out of this world cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Drain 1 can crushed pineapple and spread on cake while hot. Ice when cool.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Combine all ingredients together in a large container.
Use about 1/3 cup mixture with 1 cup boiling water.
Top with marshmallows and enjoy an easy, delicious cup of hot chocolate!!!!

title: baked eggplant parmesan
directions: Cut 1/2-inch slices from peeled, medium-sized eggplant.
Dip in beaten egg and bread crumbs and fry until crisp in olive oil. Place fried slices of eggplant in casserole dish and cover with spaghetti sauce.
Cover with thin slices or shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Bake in moderate oven 15 to 20 minutes.
One-half pound of browned meat can be added.

title: indian corn stew
directions: Melt margarine in heavy skillet. Add onion and bell pepper. Cook 5 min. Add meat and brown well.
Add corn and tomato soup, sugar, salt and Worcestershire sauce. Simmer 1 hr.

title: mexican dip
directions: Place in a 9 x 13-inch casserole and top with chopped onions and grated cheese.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Combine salad dressing mix, sour cream and Miracle Whip.
Set aside.
Place half of crumbled cornbread in the bottom of an extra large serving bowl.
Top with half of beans.
In a medium bowl, combine tomatoes, pepper and onions.
Layer half of this mixture over beans.
Layer half of cheese, bacon, corn and reserved dressing.
Repeat layers, using the remaining ingredients.
Cover and cool 2 to 3 hours.
The longer it's chilled, the better.
Can be kept several days.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix zucchini, soup, sour cream, carrots, onion, sweet pepper, salt and pepper.
Set aside.
Melt margarine in pan you are baking in.
Mix in stuffing.
Put half the stuffing in bottom of pan. Put the other ingredients on top of stuffing.
Add the other half of stuffing to the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: taco salad dip(appetizer)
directions: Whip mayonnaise and cream cheese together until smooth.
Spread evenly on a flat tray or serving dish.
Spread taco sauce on top of mayo mix.
Add shredded lettuce next.
Then spread chopped tomatoes, red onion and green olives.
Top with cheese and black olives.
Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour minimum before serving with your favorite tortilla chips.
Dip chips into taco mixture. Mmm good.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes.
Add onion, cheese and mayonnaise.
Cook 8 strips of bacon crisp and sprinkle over top.
Bake in oven until cheese melts.

title: hard candy
directions: Mix sugar, water and Karo in a large saucepan.
Stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Boil without stirring, until temperature reaches 300°.
Remove from heat.
After boiling ceases, stir in flavoring and a few drops of food coloring.
Pour into a greased 9 x 9 pan. Let cool while greasing the table top and scissors.
Pour candy onto table top.
Have one person cut it with the scissors, into strips, while others cut the strips into candy pieces.
When done, put candy into a colander and sprinkle with powdered sugar, or pour onto lightly greased cookie sheet. Cool and break into pieces.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: chicken fricassee
directions: Brown chicken on both sides in skillet.
Add flour.
When chicken is brown, add vegetables.
Add tomatoes.
You may sprinkle a little curry powder and oregano.
Cover and simmer until chicken is done.
You may also bake in casserole in 350° oven.
Bake until chicken is done.
Serve with rice.

title: orange cream frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients in small bowl; beat until smooth.

title: garlic pretzels
directions: Mix all and bake 5 minutes at 325°. Stir and bake for 5 more minutes.

title: he-man casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onions and green pepper in skillet.
Drain off fat.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Meanwhile, cook noodles in boiling water about 8 to 10 minutes.
Drain noodles.

title: old fashioned vegetable soup
directions: Cut meat off bone and brown in heavy saucepan (large).
Add bone and 6 cups water.
Stir in all remaining ingredients.
Cook over low heat for 1 hour or more until done.
Can be frozen.

title: hermit cookies
directions: Mix together ingredients and drop by teaspoon.
Bake at 350° until done, approximately 8 to 10 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake 45 minutes or until done, then pour 1 can cream of mushroom soup over loaf and meat.

title: banana bars
directions: Bake in a
greased
15 x 10 x 1-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: quick chicken bake
directions: Dot chicken pieces with butter or margarine.
Pour on Worcestershire sauce, then sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 425° for 40 minutes.
Serve.

title: shish kabob marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Marinate beef in mixture a minimum of 4 hours.
Better if you can marinate overnight.

title: fruited ham slice
directions: Place ham slice in 10-inch square baking dish.
Arrange green pepper, apricots and pineapple chunks on ham.
Set aside.
In small bowl, combine reserved pineapple juice, sweet and sour sauce, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Pour over ham.
Cover.
Microwave at 70% (Medium-high) for 14 to 17 minutes or until ham is heated through and green pepper is tender-crisp, rotating dish once.

title: bacon-wrapped water chestnuts
directions: Mix soy sauce and brown sugar in a small bowl.
Stir in water chestnuts and marinate, stirring occasionally, 15 minutes.

title: italian cheese ball
directions: Mix Ranch dressing with mayonnaise and milk.
Chill 15 to 20 minutes to set.
Blend cream cheese, dressing mixture and shredded Cheddar with electric mixer until thoroughly mixed.
Form into 1 or 2 balls and chill briefly in freezer, approximately 10 minutes. Can be rolled in chopped nuts, paprika or light parsley or served plain.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Spray 9-inch square baking pan with Mazola no stick cooking spray.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, cocoa, cornstarch, baking soda and salt.
In medium bowl, using a fork or wire whisk, mix egg whites, water and corn syrup.
Add to flour mixture; stir until smooth.
Pour into pan; bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Makes 16 servings.

title: salad dressing
directions: Combine in jar and shake!

title: baked corn
directions: Beat sugar, eggs and cream.
Add onion, butter and green pepper.
Add approximately 1/2 of cracker crumbs.
Melt butter and sprinkle on top.
Sprinkle remaining cracker crumbs on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Dish will be light brown.

title: zebra bread
directions: Stir baking mix, sesame seed, salt and water to a soft dough. Gently smooth dough into a ball on floured surface.
Knead 5 times.
Divide dough in half.
Roll or pat each half into a rectangle, 12 x 8-inches; cut lengthwise in half.
Place strips on grill 5 inches from medium coals; cook 3 to 4 minutes on each side.
Cut each strip into 4 pieces and serve with hot butter.

title: congealed salad
directions: Pour water into boil; add jello and pineapple.
Let come to boil.
Then set boiler into sink of cold water (ice water).
Add cottage cheese; stir.
Pour into mixing bowl and add Cool Whip. Stir well with spoon.
Add nuts.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Place beans and carrots in 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Sprinkle with onion.
Top with broccoli.
Pour oil mixture over vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Drain on platter.
Makes 12 servings.
Allow a day for flavor to develop.

title: betty ford's beef stew
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Add onions, garlic and 2 teaspoons salt. Add flour, seasonings, wine and bouillon.
Simmer on low about 1 1/2 hours or more if needed, then add the vegetables and simmer 1/2 to 3/4 hour more, until tender.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix melted butter and crumbs together.
Press into your chosen container.
Slice bananas to make 2 layers.
Mix lemon juice and milk well.
Pour over bananas.
Pour pineapple and juice over lemon juice mixture.
Spread Cool Whip topping over pineapple. Sprinkle shredded coconut over whipped topping.
Arrange cherries and pecans over coconut.
Refrigerate until firm and cool. Enjoy!!

title: monster cookies
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients together.
Add peanut butter and beat again.
Add remainder of ingredients, except candy.
Mix well.
Make large cookies and press some candies on the tops. Bake in 350°F oven till bottoms of cookies are brown.
Do not overbake.

title: party ham rolls
directions: Cut tops off
rolls.
Mix
mustard,
butter
and
poppy seed. On bottom half
of rolls, layer ham and cheese and then spread with mixture.
Put	tops
back
on rolls. Wrap in foil. Bake at 300° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: granola bars
directions: In large plastic or glass bowl, put butter with marshmallows on top.
Microwave on High until marshmallows fluff up high.
This must be constantly watched.
Remove from microwave and stir in peanut butter and granola.
Mix well.
Pour into ungreased pan. Cool and cut into squares.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute onion, pepper and mushrooms in margarine.
Add Velveeta cubes until melted.
Stir in remaining ingredients and cook in casserole dish 30 minutes at 375° covered.

title: slovak christmas soup
directions: Cook mushrooms in 2 quarts water for 30 minutes.
Add sauerkraut and cook another 15 minutes.
Melt shortening, then add flour and brown lightly.
Stir constantly, adding milk.
Cook until smooth.
Add to mushrooms and sauerkraut.
Saute onion in butter, then add to soup.
Cook 1 minute and season.

title: corned beef scramble
directions: Break up corned beef and brown in skillet.
Add soup, mustard, horseradish and pickle.
Simmer for 5 minutes and serve on buns.

title: stuffed chicken breasts with wild rice
directions: Cook rice according to directions; set aside. Pound chicken breasts until each are 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick. Pour marinade over chicken; refrigerate 5 to 15 minutes. Heat oven to 350°. Place about 1 tablespoon of rice on each chicken breast; roll up. Hold together with toothpicks. Place in oven; bake 30 minutes or until chicken is done. Heat reserved marinade to boil; pour over chicken. Serve with remaining rice.

title: rhubarb crisp
directions: Mix together first five ingredients.
Spread 3/4 of mixture into 9-inch square pan.
Add rhubarb.
Cook last three ingredients until clear, add vanilla.
Pour liquid over all.
Sprinkle on remaining mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Great served warm with ice cream or half and half.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Cut up onion and green pepper and separate broccoli and cauliflower into bite-size pieces.
