Mix all ingredients in serving bowl.
Chill and serve.

title: german chocolate caramel bars
directions: Combine caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk in saucepan and heat over low heat until caramels are melted.
Set aside.
Mix by hand the cake mix, melted butter, 1/3 cup evaporated milk and walnuts.
(Batter will be thick.) Spread 1/2 batter in greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Sprinkle 1 cup chocolate chips over baked crust.
Drizzle melted caramel over. Spread remaining batter over caramel.
Return to oven and bake 15 to 18 minutes.
Cool, refrigerate 30 minutes.

title: roast and gravy
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook on low 3 to 4 hours or bake in oven at 350° for 2 hours.
Take meat out of crock-pot or pot; slice.
Add 3 tablespoons cornstarch in hot gravy mixture to thicken.
Serve gravy over mashed potatoes, rice, noodles, biscuits.
Or get gravy to boil and add dumplings!

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into generously greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares to serve hot with butter.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Place cabbage and 1 tablespoon salt in 5 cups boiling water and simmer 5 minutes.
Drain and remove outer leaves.
Mix ground beef with remaining ingredients.
Fill center of leaves with 1/2 cup of stuffing.
Roll up and arrange, seam side down, in heavy skillet or pot.
Pour tomato soup and sauce over stuffed cabbage. Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: frozen date salad
directions: Whip together cream cheese and syrup.
Add nuts, dates and pineapple.
Add whipped cream.
Mix together in a serving bowl and freeze.
Take out of freezer 3 hours before serving.

title: dot's potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in pan.
Sprinkle grated cheese over potatoes, then pour soup over all and top with cracker crumbs which have been mixed with butter.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken livers favorite
directions: Flour livers; fry in cooking oil until done and brown. Prepare gravy according to package directions.
Add mushrooms to gravy.
Place livers in baking dish.
Cover with gravy mixture. Cook in a 450° oven until bubbly (10 to 12 minutes).

title: leo's favorite
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients well.
Form into small balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet 2 inches apart. Press with a fork until flat.
Cook exactly 10 minutes.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Place all ingredients in mixer; beat 3 to 5 minutes.
Bake in 5 x 10-inch tube pan at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: crawfish cornbread
directions: Mix
everything together.
Bake in oblong pan.	Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: hawaiian cheese ball
directions: Mix all together, using 1/2 cup pecans.
Chill.
Shape into ball and roll in remaining 1/2 cup nuts.
Best made several days ahead so flavors blend.
Serve with Wheat Thins and Triscuits crackers.

title: zucchini beef skillet
directions: Saute beef, onions, green pepper and garlic in 12-inch skillet until well browned.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: seven-layer bars
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in crushed graham crackers.
Pat crumb mixture evenly in bottom of an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Layer in order:
chocolate pieces, butterscotch pieces, coconut and walnuts.
Pour Dairy Sweet sweetened condensed milk evenly over all.
Bake in a 350° oven 30 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into bars.
Makes 36.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook and drain beef, pork, onions and garlic in large saucepan.
Add tomatoes and sauce, 2 tablespoons parsley flakes, sugar, 1 teaspoon salt and basil.
Bring to a boil stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat and simmer uncovered for 1 hour or until consistency of spaghetti sauce.
Mix cottage and Mozzarella cheeses, 1 tablespoon parsley flakes, 1 1/2 teaspoons salt and oregano.
Reserve 1/2 cup meat sauce for topping.
Make 4 layers of noodles, sauce and cheeses.
Spread remaining sauce over top and sprinkle with Parmesan.
(If desired, lasagna can be covered and refrigerated at this point.)

title: holiday cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine; press onto bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan. Bake at 325° for 10 minutes. Reduce oven temperature to 300°. Combine softened cream cheese, sugar and juice, mixing until well blended. Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition. Pour mixture over crust. Bake at 300° for 55 minutes.

title: twice cooked divinity(the best!)
directions: Stir together sugar, corn syrup, water and salt.
Boil until it reaches 240°.
Pour 1/3 of this mixture into the beaten egg whites that have been mixed with vanilla.
Continue beating egg whites with white syrup mixture while bringing remaining syrup to 265°.
Now, beat this syrup into other mixture until it retains its shape when dropped by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Top each piece of candy with pecan half or mix pecans into candy before dropping onto wax paper.

title: rumaki
directions: Wash livers and pat dry.
Marinate livers for 30 minutes in honey, soy sauce, oil and garlic.
Put slice of chestnut on chicken liver and roll up; wrap bacon around that and secure with toothpick.
(Keep bacon chilled; easier to wrap with.)
Bake at 350° until bacon is crisp.
Serve immediately.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Grate cucumbers and sprinkle with salt.
Set aside to season for 5 to 10 minutes.
Rinse cucumbers with water to remove salt. Drain as well as possible.
Add a small amount of mayonnaise and sugar to cucumbers to taste.
Place in refrigerator to chill for approximately 30 minutes.
Cucumbers make lots of liquid but they can be drained.
Tastes great.

title: aunt sara ferguson's chicken supreme casserole
directions: Tear crackers into pieces (nibble size).
Spray 8 x 12-inch casserole dish with nonstick spray.
Spread 1/2 of cracker pieces on the bottom of dish.
Pour some melted butter over crackers. Mix chicken and other ingredients together.
Spread over crackers and then top with the rest of the crackers.
Pour melted butter over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until lightly browned and bubbly.

title: hidden valley hamburgers
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pat out into hamburgers.
Cook on grill or stove top.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and dice the eggplant. Boil in water until tender, then drain. Mix crumbled saltines, soup and milk. Add eggplant. Pour into buttered casserole dish. Cover with cheese and pats of butter. Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.

title: quick and easy green beans
directions: Combine ingredients in casserole and either: (1) Microwave for 5 minutes or (2) Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate caramel walnut fudge
directions: In a saucepan, over low heat, melt chocolate pieces with sweetened milk and salt. Remove from heat stir in walnuts, caramel topping and vanilla. Spread evenly into foil-lined 8 or 9 inch square pan.
Chill 2 hours or until firm.

title: banana blueberry bread
directions: Sprinkle berries with 2 teaspoons flour.
Mix other ingredients together and fold berries in last.
Pour into greased 5 x 9 loaf pan and bake at 350° for one hour.

title: zippy cheese snacks
directions: Cheese and butter should be at room temperature for ease of handling.
Mix all ingredients together with your hands.
Make into small balls.
Roll in flour and put on cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Remove from pan immediately and cool on pastry cloth, then place in cookie jar or tin.

title: muscadine pie
directions: Pop centers out of muscadines and boil the hulls in water to cover; cook until tender.
Drain muscadines.
Take cooked muscadine hulls, sugar, flour, cream and oleo and cook until mixture thickens.
Pour muscadine mixture into baked pie crust. Beat egg whites and pour over pie.
Bake until brown.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Peel and cut sweet potatoes.
Cook until tender.
Cream and make into balls with a marshmallow in each ball.
Roll in Post Toasties.
Drop into hot oil until brown.
Drain on paper towel.

title: chili sauce
directions: Peel tomatoes.
Chop onions and peppers fine.
Combine all ingredients in saucepan; cover.
Boil gently (uncover) for about 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Pour into bottle and seal.

title: tomato gravy
directions: Add milk to grease, onion, flour and tomatoes.
Let brown. Serve over hot biscuits.
Delicious!

title: garden rice
directions: In 3 qt. pan melt butter over med. heat.
Saute onion and garlic until tender.
Stir in water, bouillon cube, salt and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Stir in rice.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 20 minutes, until tender and all liquid is absorbed.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: Combine all ingredients but the oil.
Heat oil to 375° and drop batter by tablespoons into oil. Turn once.
Cook until golden.
Drain on paper towels.
Batter may be deep fried.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients; set aside.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add flour mixture, one cup at a time, alternating with milk.
Chill dough 1 hour.

title: pasta zucchini
directions: At least 2 hours before mealtime, grate zucchini.
Put in colander and salt to get as much moisture out as possible.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease spring-form pan (don't flour). Mix all ingredients in a large bowl thoroughly (hand mix).
Pour mixture into greased spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool on rack 10 minutes after removing outside of pan.

title: spaghetti sauce for canning
directions: Combine ingredients; bring to boil, then simmer for 12 hours or until reduced by 3 inches.
Remove bay leaves before processing. Process pints 55 minutes at 10 pounds pressure; quarts 65 minutes at 10 pounds pressure.
Add 3 to 6 ounces tomato paste per pint and ground beef if desired at time of serving.
Do not use open kettle method.

title: chicken and rice bake
directions: In 3-quart oblong baking dish, combine soup, broth and rice. Arrange chicken, bone side down, on rice mixture, then sprinkle paprika on the top.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until done.
Stir the rice before serving.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Use a sheet cake pan.
After cake cools, pour frozen strawberries on cooled cake.
Then spread Cool Whip evenly over strawberries.
Use fresh strawberries as design on top of Cool Whip.

title: lemon pie
directions: Wash lemon, quarter and remove seeds.
Use whole lemon.
Place all ingredients in blender until smooth.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: broccoli-rice dish
directions: Cook broccoli to thaw.
Fix rice according to package directions.
Add all ingredients in casserole dish.
A small can of mushrooms may be added, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: delicious corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix all ingredients together in medium size bowl.
Mix well.
Pour in baking dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: gunk
directions: Mix ingredients.
Dump into a greased 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 350°.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Stir in pie filling and pineapple.
Pour into 1-quart pan to chill.
Blend next 4 ingredients together and spread over chilled jello.
Sprinkle chopped pecans over top.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: In a cup, stir the mustard with the vinegar until dissolved. Let stand for at least 10 minutes.
In a small saucepan, heat the oil over moderately low heat.
Add the minced garlic, chili powder, oregano and salt.
Cook stirring occasionally for 8 minutes or until onion is soft.
Stir in the tomato sauce, Worcestershire sauce, honey and molasses.
Bring to a simmer. Cook partially covered, stirring occasionally, for 10 minutes or until thickened.
Will keep refrigerated for up to 2 weeks.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Brown beef in hot Crisco.
Add water and simmer in covered skillet, 1 1/2 hours, or until tender.
Reserve broth.

title: smoked beef dip
directions: Blend together all the ingredients and place in baking dish until bubbles (about 20 minutes) in a 350° oven.
Serve warm with dipables (i.e., tortilla chips, potato chips, crackers and raw vegetables).
Serves many.

title: escalloped onions("a favorite from the '76 cookbook.")
directions: Cook onions until tender.
Drain onions overnight or in morning if you are going to use at night.
Put in 1 1/2-quart casserole. Add bread crumbs and cheese.

title: john's favorite cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together (except peanuts).
Shape into 2 balls and roll in chopped peanuts.
Serve with assorted crackers or melba toast.

title: bean soup
directions: Saute onion and carrot in 1/4 cup stock and wine until soft. Add tarragon.
Add onion mixture and beans with remaining stock to a food processor fitted with metal blade.
Puree until creamy and smooth.
Pour into a large saucepan.
Add water and soy sauce and heat thoroughly.
Remove from heat.
Add lemon juice, romaine and pimento.
Stir to wilt spinach.
Serve hot.
Makes 6 servings.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Mix oil in slowly so it mixes well.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes with skins on until done.
Peel and slice to line casserole dish.
Make sauce with other ingredients and bring to a boil.
Pour over sweet potatoes and bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Mix well.
Store in container with tight lid.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Simmer chicken breasts in water for 2 to 3 hours (also add salt, pepper, garlic and bay leaves).
Remove chicken, remove skin, debone and shred into chunks.
Add chicken and vegetables to water and simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add the noodles during the last 15 minutes to allow them to cook until tender.

title: sheet fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, flour and vanilla.
Mix well.
Grease and flour the pan.
Spread nuts on bottom of pan. Pour batter over nuts and press in.
Mix chopped fruits together. Sprinkle over batter and press in.
Bake for 1 hour at 250° in 11 x 15 x 2-inch pan.
Cut when cool.

title: honey-coconut dip (for fruit)
directions: Place cottage cheese in blender.
Process at low speed until smooth.
Transfer to medium-sized bowl.
Stir in yogurt, honey, coconut and orange rind until well mixed.
Cover; refrigerate 1 hour or until chilled.
Serve in small glass serving bowl or chilled hollowed out cantaloupe half.
Use with bite-sized pieces of seasonal fruit of your choice.

title: elegant catfish
directions: Melt 1 stick butter.
Add lemon juice.
Place fish in Pyrex baking dish.
Salt and pepper.
Cover and refrigerate for one hour. Bake covered at 350° for 20 minutes.
Uncover and cook an additional 5 minutes.
While baking, in small saucepan, saute onions and cucumbers in 1/4 stick butter.
Add dill weed, washed and drained shrimp, milk and soup.
Heat, but do not boil.
Remove fish to plate and cover with soup mixture.

title: apple pudding with butter sauce
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs, then add flour, soda, cinnamon and nutmeg. Fold in nuts and apples. Pour into prepared 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean. Serve warm with Butter Sauce.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Mix together and let set in icebox for 3 to 4 hours.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Save a little cheese and sprinkle on top the last 10 minutes before done.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Beat margarine, shortening and sugar together.
Add the eggs and beat again.
Add flour, baking powder and soda that were mixed together, adding the vanilla and then the sour cream.
Mix well. Pour 1/2 of the batter into a greased tube pan.

title: chicken creole
directions: Brown flour in oil.
Add onion, pepper, celery and garlic. Cook until vegetables are transparent.
Add tomatoes, water, salt, pepper and sauces.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: quick cheesy enchiladas
directions: In a large skillet or Dutch oven brown meat and drain.
Add Taco seasoning mix and 1/2 cup of water.
Cook for 2 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add refried beans and rice.
Heat through. Add 1/2 jar salsa and hot peppers slices.
Grate cheese and put 1/2 of cheese in meat, bean and rice mixture.
Remove from heat.
In an oblong cake pan, lay one tortilla flat and spoon about 3 Tbsp. (more or less) onto middle of tortilla.
Fold one side of tortilla over meat mixture and roll tortilla into a tube shape.
Place at the far end of cake pan.
Repeat until all the mixture has been used.
Take remaining 1/2 jar of salsa and combine with the small can of tomato sauce.
Mix thoroughly.
Spread salsa mixture over the top of the enchiladas.
Cover the enchiladas with the remaining grated cheese.

title: tuscan chicken rolls with pork stuffing
directions: Place chicken between 2 pieces of plastic wrap and pound to 1/4-inch thick.
Don't tear meat.
Cook pork, onion and garlic over medium heat until pork is brown.
Drain fat.
Stir in egg, bread crumbs, salt, savory and pepper.
Place about 1/3 cup pork mixture on each chicken breast half.
Roll up and secure with wooden picks.
Place rolls in greased oblong baking dish.
Brush rolls with margarine and pour any remaining margarine over rolls. Add wine or water.
Cook, uncovered, in a 400° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Line the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with 1 unbaked pie crust.
Combine all ingredients and pour into baking dish. Cover with top crust and prick with a fork.
Bake at 375° for about 40 minutes or until top crust is brown.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Layer casserole dish with corn chips, then add meat mixture and cover with remaining chips.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat in olive oil.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer, stirring occasionally, for 5 to 7 hours.
Cool and remove bones. (Pork shoulder can be substituted for neck bones so you don't have to pick the bones.)
Recipe makes 16 quarts and serves about 80.

title: peach custard cake
directions: Combine flour, salt and butter and pack this mixture into a 9-inch square pan.
Drain peaches.
Save juice and arrange in pan. Mix cinnamon and sugar and sprinkle over peaches.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: orange coconut balls(no cook)
directions: Crush vanilla wafers.
Add orange juice, powdered sugar, nuts and margarine.
Roll balls in coconut and chill.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Use hands.
Drop from teaspoon to ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.
Do not overbake.
Makes about 150.
Mix well.

title: slow cooker dressing
directions: Mix butter, celery, onion, spices, eggs and broth together. Add crumbs; stir to blend.
Cook in slow cooker on high for 45 minutes.
Reduce to low for 4 to 6 hours.
Be sure to check after a couple of hours as crock-pots vary.

title: fresh vegetable pizza
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate dough into 4 long rectangles. Place rectangles crosswise in ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan; press over bottom and 1 inch up sides to form crust.
Seal perforations.
Bake
at 375° for 14 to 19 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely.

title: fireside coffee
directions: Combine all ingredients and put into decorative jars.
When giving as a gift, send a small card with the jar telling the receiver to use 2 heaping teaspoonfuls per one cup hot water.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Beginning with lettuce, layer the first 8 ingredients in the order given, ending with cheese.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 4 hours.
Sprinkle bacon over salad before serving.
(May be made the night before.)

title: jello with cherries and walnuts
directions: Mix Jell-O with hot water.
Put 3 cans of cherries in a colander (you need the juice).
Substitute the juice for cold water and add more cold water (as much as Jell-O directions call for). Add lemon juice.

title: chicken with tomatoes and peppers
directions: Add all ingredients to a crock-pot. Slow cook on low 6 to 8 hours. Serve over pasta.

title: quick veggie pizza
directions: *Broccoli, tomatoes, carrots, mushrooms, cucumbers, onions, sugar snap peas, radishes, red and green peppers and black and green olives

title: oatmeal chocolate chip bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 15 x 10-inch or 9 x 13-inch pan. In large bowl, beat brown sugar and shortening until light and fluffy.
Add molasses, vanilla and eggs; blend well.
Lightly spoon flour in measuring cup; level off.
Stir in oats, flour, baking soda and salt; blend well.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Spread in pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes, or until light brown and center is set.
Cool; cut into bars.

title: quick lasagne
directions: Boil lasagne noodles.
While noodles are boiling, in separate pan, brown hamburger, onion and garlic.
Drain grease; add mushrooms, spaghetti sauce, Italian seasoning and salt.
Let simmer on low heat.

title: pizza dip
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Set aside.
Spread softened cream cheese on a round pan or dish.
Spread pizza sauce over the cream cheese.
Sprinkle with hamburger, onion and green pepper. Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Spread olives on top of cheese. Serve with taco chips.

title: shortbread cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Combine flour and cornstarch. Add to butter/sugar mix with flour. Mix with your hands. Chill. Roll out on lightly floured surface. 1/4 inch cut. Place lightly greased cookie sheet. Cook at 300 for 20-25 minutes.

title: noodles and cottage cheese
directions: Boil noodles and drain.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Fry sausage; crumble.
Drain.
Cool slightly and mix with cheese, onions and flour.
Mix beaten eggs with milk and pour over other ingredients in shell.
Sprinkle with a little chopped parsley.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 30 minutes or filling is firm and pastry is browned.
Can be frozen and reheated.

title: baked pheasant
directions: Set oven to 350°.
Stuff cavity of birds with onion, celery, rosemary and apple.
Brush birds with 1/2 the melted butter and drizzle with 1/2 the lemon.
Arrange slices of bacon over birds and place in oven.
Cook, uncovered, until bacon is browned.
Remove from oven.
Brush with remaining butter and drizzle with the other 1/2 of the lemon.
Tightly cover pheasant and return to oven.
Cook until tender.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Sprinkle apples with lemon juice.
Mix celery, grapes, marshmallows and mayonnaise.
Chill.
Fold in whipped cream. Chill.
Just before serving, add nuts.

title: strawberry daiquiri
directions: Mix in blender.
Add 1 pint crushed ice and shake.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add eggs, flour, baking powder and flavorings.
Roll fruit in flour. Add to mixture. Bake 3 hours at 250°.
Start in cold oven.

title: i-45 squares(interstate 45 - minute cream cheese squares)
directions: Combine melted butter or margarine, 1 egg and cake mix; spread mixture into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: dixie fried chicken
directions: Cut chicken into pieces.
Place in a bowl.
Pour buttermilk over chicken.
Marinate for 2 hours.
In another bowl, combine flour, parsley, salt, thyme leaves and pepper.
Remove chicken from marinade.
Pour marinade in a shallow baking dish.
Roll chicken in flour mixture.
Heat shortening and butter in a heavy skillet. Brown chicken on all sides over medium to high heat.
Place chicken pieces on top of buttermilk in baking dish.
Add chicken broth to skillet.
Scrape up brownings.
Strain and pour around chicken in baking dish.
Bake chicken uncovered at 375° until crisp and tender, about 50 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Mix butter, cocoa and milk in bowl.
Cook on High in microwave for 2 minutes.
Stir in box of powdered sugar.
Add peanut butter. Press in bottom of square pan.
Put pecan halves on top.
Cool in refrigerator and cut in squares.

title: spinach cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch square pan that has been greased.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Wonderful!

title: chicken in a basket
directions: Cook celery and onion in microwave until soft, and add cream of chicken soup, bread cubes, salt, pepper and sage to taste.

title: chicken 'n broccoli biscuit wraps
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Separate dough into 10 biscuits.
Press each biscuit into 5 inch round.
In small bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Spoon about 2 tablespoons mixture onto center of each biscuit.
Fold dough in half over filling; press edges with fork to seal.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 13 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 10 wraps.

title: mom's divinity candy
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and cold water in saucepan. Cook until string (hard ball).
Have egg whites beaten stiffly and pour sugar mixture, a little at a time, beating egg whites constantly.
Keep sugar mixture hot until all used and hard to stir.
Add vanilla, nuts or fruit.
Pour onto buttered cookie sheet.

title: best yet ice cream
directions: Beat eggs
minutes;	add sugar until dissolved.
Add cream and
beat
until
mixed.
Add 1 quart milk and vanilla; beat. Pour
in freezer container.
Fill up to line with milk; don't go over line.

title: sandbakkels
directions: Press in tins.
Bake at 350° until golden.

title: tijuana meat loaf
directions: Thoroughly mix beef, soup, onion and rest of ingredients. Shape firmly in a shallow baking dish.
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 350°. Serve with shredded cheese, green pepper and tomato topping.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cook and drain spinach as directed on vegetable mix package. Mix ingredients together and chill.
Use with pumpernickel bread.

title: bow-tie pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain.
Cook vegetables according to package directions.
Combine pasta and vegetables with remaining ingredients in a large bowl.
Cover and chill until ready to serve.

title: swiss steak
directions: Combine salt, pepper and flour.
Roll steak in flour mixture. Brown in hot oil.
Add onion, pepper, water and ketchup.
Cover and simmer until done, about 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: hot tuna bake
directions: Place 4 slices of bread in buttered 6-cup shallow baking dish. Combine tuna, pepper, onion and salt in small bowl.
Stir in 1/2 the shredded cheese.
Spread over bread.
Top with the remaining 4 slices of bread.
Beat eggs in a medium size bowl.
Stir in milk and oregano.
Pour mixture over bread.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour or overnight.

title: chinese barbecue chicken
directions: Cut chicken wings into 3 pieces and throw tips away.
Bring water, vermouth and soy sauce almost to a boil.
Pour sauce over wings and bake at 275° for 3 hours in an uncovered oblong glass casserole dish.
Baste and turn periodically.
Turn oven up to 350° for last 30 minutes.
Bake a total of 3 1/2 hours.

title: weight watcher's vegetable noodle soup
directions: The ingredients for soup are as follows, keeping in mind that you must follow Jesus' instructions on how to measure as recorded by Luke 6:38:
"Give to others, and God will give to you.
Indeed, you will receive a full measure, a generous helping, poured into your hands, all you can hold.
The measure you use for others is the one that God will use for you."

title: easy to make flan
directions: In a double boiler over pan over medium heat, brown the sugar until golden brown; do not burn.
Once golden brown and liquid, remove from heat and coat pan all around.
Let it sit for 5 minutes.
Blend the rest of the ingredients in blender and pour into sugar coated pan.
Set oven temperature at 375°.
Place double boiler pan in oven.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Insert knife; if clean the flan is cooked.
Cool.
Then turn the flan over into a deep dish and refrigerate.

title: easy refrigerator pickles
directions: Combine cucumbers and onion in large bowl.
Combine rest of ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to boil; boil 1 minute.
Pour over cucumbers and onion.
Cool.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator at least 4 days, stirring twice each day.
Makes 7 cups.

title: kahlua
directions: Mix the sugar, water and coffee and boil.
Simmer for 1 hour. Cool.
Stir in the brandy, vodka and vanilla.
Bottle.
May be used stat.
Will keep, tightly corked, indefinitely.

title: shrimp stir-fry
directions: Fry shrimp until done.
Cook rice as instructed on box.
Add Worcestershire and soy sauce.
Add chestnuts and bamboo to rice. Mix shrimp and 1/2 cup of stir-fry sauce.
Simmer for 5 minutes. Depending on amount of rice, makes 2 to 4 servings.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Refrigerate in covered dish for 3 days. Form into 5 loaves (2 1/4-inch in diameter).
Place on rack of oven in pan. Bake 15 hours at 150°.
Wipe with paper towel.
Refrigerate or freeze.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, salt, cinnamon and eggs with wire whip.
Add pumpkin, milk, vanilla and water, using wire whip.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour until filling is thick.
Makes 3 (9-inch) pies.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in a 9-inch square dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese and bake 10 more minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together well all ingredients.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 90 minutes.
Check often after 60 minutes.

title: real e-z rolls
directions: Stir yeast and 1/2 cup lukewarm water together.
Set aside. Heat sugar, Crisco and 1/2 cup water.
Beat egg.
Add yeast and sugar mixtures to egg.
Stir in the flour and salt.
Mix well. Cover and put in refrigerator overnight.
Three hours before needed, remove from refrigerator and form into rolls.
Place in a greased pan.
Cover and let rise in a warm place.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes, until golden brown.

title: "marsha's marinated cucumbers and onions"
directions: Will need 1 bowl with tight lid.

title: mother's pumpkin pie
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into pastry and bake 45 minutes at 450° or until set.

title: enchiladas with red sauce
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in a large skillet, stirring to crumble meat.
Drain and return mixture to skillet.
Add flour and next 5 ingredients, stirring well.
Bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer 10 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pour 1 1/2 cups red sauce into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Set aside. Wrap tortillas in aluminum foil and heat at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until softened.
Combine 1 cup chopped onion and 1 cup sliced olives; stir well.
Working with 1 tortilla at a time, keeping remaining tortillas covered and warm, sprinkle 2 heaping tablespoonfuls of onion olive mixture down center of tortilla. Top with 1/4 cup meat mixture.
Roll tortilla tightly and place in prepared dish, seam side down.
Repeat with remaining tortillas. Cover and bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Uncover and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake uncovered an additional 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Top enchiladas with sour cream and olives.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: "white chili"
directions: In large pot, boil chicken (in water); remove from broth. Debone chicken and return to broth.
Add beans that have been soaked overnight.
Add onion and spices.
Cook 1 to 2 hours.
Add chilies last half hour.
Good served with sour cream and grated cheese.
Also very good served with corn bread.

title: brown sugar chewies
directions: Mix brown sugar, egg and vanilla.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour into a pie dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery until tender, then add cooked broccoli. Cook rice.
Add Cheez Whiz to rice; stir, then add soup, milk, celery, onion and broccoli.
Stir and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dee's dish
directions: Cook and brown hamburger and onion.
Cook macaroni and drain. Blend these together.
Put in casserole dish.
Grate cheese on top of casserole. Put in microwave for 10 minutes.

title: teriyaki marinade
directions: Combine well.
Pour over London broil.
Marinate at least 4 hours, turning occasionally.

title: scalloped ham and potatoes
directions: Melt butter in saucepan over low heat; add flour, stirring until smooth.
Gradually add milk; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in salt and pepper. Spoon 1/4 cup sauce into 8 x 12-inch dish.
Layer potatoes, onions and sauce; add cheese and ham.
Repeat layers.
Cover and bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining cheese and bake an additional 5 minutes.

title: cracker jack
directions: Cook sugar, molasses and water until it forms a ball in cold water (or candy stage on thermometer).
Add soda and stir well. Pour over popped corn.

title: shrimp gumbo
directions: Brown okra with a little oil, stirring often until a little brown and dry, at least 30 minutes.
Be careful not to burn; add onion, bell pepper and celery.
After it browns, add a little water, salt, pepper and tomatoes.
Add raw shrimp; simmer a long while.
Serve over rice.

title: italian creme cake
directions: Cream oleo and shortening.
Add sugar and beat until mixture is smooth.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Combine flour and baking soda, then add to creamed mixture, alternating with buttermilk. Stir in vanilla.
Add coconut and chopped nuts.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in greased and floured 8-inch pans (3) at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.
When cool, frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: cinnamon basil peaches
directions: Peel peaches; cut in halves and discard pits.
Simmer honey, water and basil for 5 minutes.
Add peaches.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes or until peaches are tender.
Chill and serve as dessert or meat garnish.

title: seafood and basil phyllo
directions: Process first 7 ingredients in food processor.
Cut phyllo lengthwise into 4 strips.
Place on damp cloth and cover with wax paper to prevent sheets from drying out.
Working with 1 or 2 strips at a time, brush with melted butter.
Fold over about 1/4-inch from the bottom edge.
Add a spoonful of filling just above fold and fold again to form a triangle.
Continue folding as if you were folding an American flag.
Place seam side down on baking sheets.
When all triangles have been made, brush tops with melted butter.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes, until tops are browned.
Freeze or refrigerate, if desired.

title: chicken choppin broccoli
directions: Steam broccoli and place in bottom of casserole dish.
Place 2 slices of Swiss cheese on top.
Mix soup, lemon juice and mayonnaise.
Spread 1/2 of mixture over cheese.
Place chicken in dish, topped with 2 slices of cheese and add remaining mayonnaise mixture on top of cheese.
Top with lightly buttered bread crumbs. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: brownies in a jar
directions: Pour sugar into a clean and dry quart jar. Press down firmly. Add cocoa powder and press down firmly. Pour in chopped pecans. Making sure pecans are evenly layered in the jar. Combine flour, baking powder and salt. Pour into jar and seal.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Prepare stuffing according to package directions.
In 13 x 9-inch greased pan, arrange in layers stuffing, partially cooked vegetables, almonds and meat.
Mix soups and milk.
Pour all of soup mixture on these ingredients.
Sprinkle cheese over top. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Last 10 to 15 minutes, add Ritz crackers, mixed with 1/2 stick butter.
(May use soda crackers). Serves 8 to 10.

title: grillades and grits
directions: Season the veal with salt and pepper.
Heat the butter in a large skillet and saute until the veal is lightly browned, about 3 minutes per side.
Transfer meat to warm preheated oven (175°) while preparing the sauce.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in casserole dish.
Cook 35 minutes at 350°.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Wrap each apple quarter in a crescent roll. Sprinkle cinnamon over crescent rolls. Mix margarine, sugar and orange juice in a saucepan; bring to a boil. Remove from heat and add vanilla. Pour over rolls. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: salsa dip
directions: Spread cream cheese with knife on large cookie sheet.
Pour and spread salsa over.
Spread onion and green pepper evenly over salsa.
Spread cheese, then Bac*Os over substance.
Serve with corn chips.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel eggplant and cut in chunks.
Boil 10 minutes in salted water.
Drain.
Saute sausage and onion until done.
Add bread, celery, spices and bouillon.
Mix in cooked eggplant and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican artichoke dip
directions: Puree artichoke hearts in food processor.
Combine all ingredients.
Spoon into a lightly greased 1-quart casserole dish. Cover.
Microwave on High until hot and bubbly, about 4 to 5 minutes, stirring once.

title: cheesy new potatoes with bacon
directions: Wash potatoes thoroughly; don't peel. Place potatoes in a small Dutch oven and cover with water. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and cook for about 20 minutes or until tender. Drain well and cool slightly. Cut into 1/4-inch slices.

title: cheese spread
directions: Put cheese in freezer for a while.
Mix ingredients together and add enough salad dressing to moisten.
Good on baked potatoes!

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Saute celery, onion and green pepper.
Cook frozen broccoli 5 minutes and drain.
Place rice on the bottom of an oblong baking pan.
Place sauteed items on top of rice, then place broccoli on top of sauteed items.
Mix Cheez Whiz with cream of chicken soup. Heat and pour over the top.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: gwen's ham recipe
directions: Soak ham in cold water overnight.
Preheat oven to 500°.
Scrub ham to remove pepper, etc.
Place ham in covered roaster with 6 cups cold water.
Close vents and bake ham for 20 minutes.
Turn off oven; allow ham to remain in oven without opening door for 3 hours.
Turn oven to 500° (do not preheat) and leave for 15 minutes.
Turn off heat and allow ham to remain in oven at least 3 hours or overnight.
Remove from roaster.
Cut off skin.
Ham is ready to serve or glaze.

title: cream cheese dip
directions: Cut onions and ham very fine.
Mix all together!

title: grandma's bran bread
directions: Pour boiling water over All Bran, salt and oleo.
Add sugar; stir well and cool.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water, then add yeast to mixture and 2 beaten eggs.
Add 3 cups flour and beat well.
Add 3 1/2 cups flour (maybe more).
Knead until light and elastic.
Place in greased bowl.
Turn over.
Let rise until double.
Punch down then divide into 3 parts; roll out to fit pan and roll up.
Bake at 350°.
Check after 35 minutes but no longer that 1 hour.

title: grandma's buckeyes
directions: Melt margarine and let it cool a bit.
Add the confectioners sugar, peanut butter and cereal to the margarine.
Mix well.
Roll the mixture into small bite size balls and refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
After one hour, melt the chocolate chips and wax over hot water.
Keeping the chocolate hot so that it remains thin, dip the balls into the chocolate.
Drop the balls onto wax paper until they are set.
There isn't a need to refrigerate the Buckeyes after they set.

title: paradise pudding
directions: Chop cherries, marshmallows and pecans in a bowl.
Crumble the box of graham crackers and mix all, pouring juice of pineapple over it.
Form a roll, wrap and put in refrigerator.

title: almond bombe
directions: Slice pound cake into 1/4-inch slices.
Slice each slice on the diagonal.
Sprinkle pound cake with Amaretto.
Arrange cake in a pinwheel design in a 1 1/2-quart mixing bowl which has been lined with plastic wrap.
Toast almonds in 375° oven until golden brown, approximately 10 minutes.
Cool and chop.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and bake for 25 minutes in a medium oven at 350°.
Makes a small casserole, double or triple for a larger casserole.

title: tamale pie
directions: In large skillet, cook beef, onion and garlic until meat is done.
Stir in tomato sauce, milk, eggs, corn, olives, corn meal, salt, chili powder and Tabasco or red pepper.
Bake in 350° oven until knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 45 minutes.

title: no bake banana pudding
directions: Layer vanilla wafers and bananas in dish.
Pour some of the pudding mixture over.
Continue to make layers of wafers, bananas and pudding until gone.
Refrigerate about an hour.

title: strawberry cooler
directions: Put into blender and frappe until slushy.
May add one banana for extra flavor, if desired.

title: goop
directions: Dice onions.
Mix with hamburger and brown.
Peel potatoes and slice as if to fry.
Open can of tomato soup.
After the hamburger and onions are brown, in a casserole dish put one layer of hamburger.
Put one layer of potatoes and a teaspoon of tomato soup over the top of the potatoes.
Repeat layers, ending with tomato soup.
Cover and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake until potatoes are done, 30 to 45 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients in a large bowl with a spoon.
Then add the zucchini and nuts; mix well.
Then add the oil, eggs, pineapple with juice and vanilla; mix well.
Makes 3 medium loaf pans.
Spray with Pam.
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 325°.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: corn muffins with green chile
directions: Mix all ingredients and let stand 3-4 minutes. Put in muffin tins and bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes. Enjoy!

title: cheese soup
directions: Bring water to a boil and add next 6 ingredients.
Bring to a boil again. Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.
Stir in soup and cheese.

title: mediterranean beef casserole
directions: Cook beef, onions and pepper in olive oil.
Mix together soup, olives and cheese.
Season with chili powder, salt and pepper. Mix all together.
Bake, covered, in 2-quart greased baking dish for 45 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and add Parmesan or Romano cheese and bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Take vegetable oil and beat the eggs with it.
Mix all the rest of the ingredients.
Bake, uncovered, in greased casserole for 1 hour at 325°.
Very good!

title: black devils food cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl, blend for 2 min. and pour into a greased and floured 9 by 13 in. cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with Chocolate Chips and Chopped Walnuts before baking, or frost when baked.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix ingredients together; cook at 325° in 3 layers.

title: macaroni cheese salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except mayonnaise and mustard.
Blend mayonnaise, mustard and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Add to salad.
Toss lightly.
Chill.
Serves 6.

title: eve's florida-licious key lime pie
directions: Melt butter; pour over other ingredients.
Stir until sufficiently moist to press into a Pyrex pie pan.
Set aside.

title: spiced tea
directions: Boil the first 4 ingredients 30 minutes.
Bring to a boil the 2 quarts of water and tea bags; let stand 30 minutes.
Add juices.

title: dilly casserole bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Soften yeast in warm water.
Combine in mixing bowl with warm cottage cheese, sugar, onion, butter, dill seed, salt, soda and egg.
Add flour to form a stiff dough, beating well after each addition.
Cover and let rise until doubled in size (50 to 60 minutes).
Stir dough down.
Place in well-greased 8-inch round casserole (1 1/2 to 2 quarts) and let rise in warm place 30 to 40 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes until golden brown.
Brush with butter and sprinkle with salt.
Makes one loaf.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook meat in water for 1/2 hour.
Remove any bones and place meat in oblong casserole.
Mix soup, sour cream, salt, pepper and milk.
Pour over meat.
Prepare favorite bread stuffing (or mix), substituting chicken broth for water.
Spread over casserole. Bake 45 minutes covered in 350° oven and 15 minutes uncovered. Serves 8.

title: vinegar pie pastry
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar and salt with pastry blender or 2 knives used scissor-fashion, cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Combine water, vinegar and egg and beat with fork.
Pour into flour mixture.
Mix well until pastry holds together (dough will be sticky).
Cover and chill at least 2 hours.
Divide dough into 4 or 5 balls.
Wrap tightly and refrigerate up to 2 hours.
May be put in jar; will keep for a long time.

title: guacamole
directions: Mash avocado(s) with fork, leaving a bit lumpy.
Stir in all other ingredients.
Serve with tortilla chips or vegetables.

title: amarillo punch
directions: Combine water and sugar.
Bring to a boil; cook 3 minutes. Let cool.
Stir in pineapple juice, orange juice and bananas. Freeze until ready to serve.
Mash the frozen mixture and add ginger ale.
40 servings.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Sift together the flour, sugar, cinnamon and soda. In another bowl combine the eggs, oil, strawberries and nuts.
Combine all together and bake in a 350° oven 1 hour or until done.
Makes 2 large loaves.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: In another pan, melt chocolate on low heat (double boiler). Add 1/2 cake wax.
Dip balls in chocolate.
Chill.
Enjoy.

title: pork medallions with brandy cream
directions: Rub pork roast with pepper.
Place on rack in shallow baking pan.
Roast at 325° until meat thermometer registers 160°.
In saucepan, combine chicken broth and green onion.
Bring to boil, reduce, cover and simmer 2 minutes.
Add whipping cream and brandy.
Simmer uncovered 10 minutes.

title: rosie's fudge
directions: Boil for 8 minutes and pour over Marshmallow Creme and chocolate pieces.
Beat until chocolate dissolves.
Add nuts, if desired.
Let stay in pan until firm and cut into squares.

title: layered green salad
directions: Take all ingredients and layer in oblong dish. You can mix mayo, lettuce, pepper and onion first, if you prefer. Sprinkle cheese and bacon bits on top.

title: chocolate fudge candy *
directions: Mix sugar, butter and milk together.
When boiling, cook for 8 minutes or until it forms a soft ball in cold water.
Take off stove and mix marshmallows, chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour into greased pan or dish.
Let cool and cut into blocks.
Makes 5 pounds.

title: margaret's corn casserole
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Mix corn, sour cream and corn bread mix. Pour into baking dish. Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: michigan rock cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, flour, cinnamon and baking soda (dissolved in hot water).
Mix well.
Fold in grapes, dates and nuts.
Drop by spoonful onto greased sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: savory broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in small amount of salted water just until tender.
Drain.
Combine eggs, milk, soup, mayonnaise, cheese and water chestnuts.
Stir in broccoli.
Pour mixture into a greased 2-quart casserole and sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: blackberry cake with caramel icing
directions: Bring berries to boil. Sweeten to taste. Cool. Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs. Beat well. Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk. Stir well. Fold in berries. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: kathy's beef stroganoff
directions: Flour meat strips, brown with onions in shortening & butter. Add seasonings & water.
Cover & simmer 45 min. or until meat is tender, stirring occasionally.
Add gravy & mushrooms, stir to mix.
Simmer for 20 min.
Just before serving, stir in sour cream. Serve over cooked noodles.

title: savory green beans
directions: Melt butter over a low flame in a pan and saute onion until golden, about 5 minutes.
Add herbs, spices and beer; bring to a boil and boil briskly about 3 minutes.
Add beans and cook, uncovered, over medium flame about 20 minutes or until liquid is almost evaporated.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley and serve at once.
Serves 4.

title: macaroni, cheese and chicken casserole
directions: Mix together, then tear the 2 slices of bread on top.
You can also add more shredded cheese on top, if desired.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: korean salad
directions: Wash and clean spinach.
Fry bacon and crumble.
Chop boiled eggs.
Drain canned water chestnuts, if used and add to spinach with eggs and bacon; toss.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Dissolve lemon jello in 2/3 cups boiling water.
Mix cake mix, lemon jello and vegetable oil; add eggs.
Pour into greased bundt pan and bake at 340 degrees for 50 minutes.
Mix confectioners sugar and lemon juice to make a glaze you can drip over the top of the cake while hot.

title: mormon punch
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: mom's no egg cake
directions: In a large sauce pan, add water and raisins. Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes. Remove from heat and set aside one cup of the water. Let cool. Sift dry ingredients together in a bowl. Add crisco and raisins w/liquid to dry ingredients. Stir well. Add last cup of raisin liquid. Mix well and pour into 13 x 9 pan. Bake at 325° for one hour.

title: pretzel salad 2
directions: Melt oleo.
Add pretzels and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Pour in a small baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Let cool.

title: glazed pork kabobs
directions: Cut carrots into 1-inch pieces.
In a small saucepan, cook, covered, in a small amount of boiling salted water, for 15 to 20 minutes; drain.

title: chinese beef and fried rice
directions: Brown ground beef, stirring occasionally.
Drain and set aside.
Brown rice in the tablespoon of oil.
Add boiling water to which the 2 beef bouillon cubes have been dissolved.
After rice begins cooking, add the chopped onions, peppers and celery.
Add the soy sauce and cook until rice is done.
Add the beef and stir together.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Combine cereal, garlic powder, oregano and pepper in blender container.
Process until cereal is finely crushed.
Place in bowl.
Add oil; mix until crumbs are moist.
Dip chicken into water and coat with cereal mixture.
Place into baking dish. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until crisp and brown.

title: cheesecake dessert
directions: Heat oven to 350°.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine
all ingredients.
Bake in a large casserole at 350° for 1 hour.

title: summer spaghetti *
directions: Chop tomatoes coarsely.
Chop onion and olives.
Mince garlic. Combine tomatoes, onion, olives, garlic, parsley, basil, capers, paprika and oregano in medium bowl.
Toss well.
Drizzle vinegar over tomato mixture.
Then pour oil over mixture.
Refrigerate, covered, at least 6 hours or overnight.
Just before serving, cook spaghetti 8 to 10 minutes; drain well.
Immediately toss hot pasta with cold marinated tomato sauce.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pistachio cream cheese fingers
directions: In large bowl, beat sugar, margarine and cream cheese until fluffy. Add vanilla and egg; beat well. In medium bowl, combine flour, pudding, baking powder and salt. Add flour mixture to cream cheese mixture. Mix well. Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: royal fudge
directions: Mix together sugar and cocoa in a heavy saucepan.
Add milk. Stir over low heat until sugar is dissolved, then bring to boil. Stir occasionally and cook to 234° or until drops of the mixture form a soft ball in cold water.
(This ball should flatten a bit when taken from the water.)
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla but do not stir.
Allow to cool to lukewarm, then beat until mixture thickens.
Stir in nuts and quickly pour into a buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Cut in squares.
Makes about 1 3/4 pounds.

title: thanksgiving chowder
directions: Fry bacon.
Drain and reserve.
Saute until tender the onions in bacon grease.
Then add potatoes, celery, turkey broth and salt. Simmer, covered, until potatoes and celery are tender.
Add turkey, whole kernel corn, cream-style corn, half and half and ground pepper.
Heat thoroughly.

title: raspberry bars
directions: Mix flour, margarine, salt, baking powder and milk and egg together.
Pack in a 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan.
Spread a thin layer of raspberry jam over this.
Mix together the brown sugar, egg, vanilla, butter and coconut; spread over pan mixture.
Bake for 25 minutes at 325°.
Cool; cut into bars.

title: crisped baked potatoes(diet)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cut each potato into wedges and transfer to a small bowl; set aside.

title: ozark apple pudding
directions: Beat eggs; stir in sugar and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir into eggs.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Bake in 9 x 9-inch pan (buttered or sprayed with Pam).
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Let cool in oven before taking out.
Serve with milk, ice cream or plain.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in pan; bring to a boil.
Boil gently 15 minutes to thicken.
Use with spareribs.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine 1/2 cup sugar, flour and salt in top of double boiler. Cook over boiling water, stirring until thick.
Beat egg yolks. Gradually stir into hot mixture.
Return to double boiler.
Cook 5 more minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla. Cool.
Line bottom of 1 1/2-quart casserole with vanilla wafers. Top with layer of sliced bananas, then custard on top.

title: refrigerator pineapple pie
directions: Combine sour cream, undrained pineapple and both pudding mixes with electric mixer.
Pour into graham cracker pie shell.
Top with whipped cream and nuts.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: pineapple delight cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour cake mix into bowl.
Add eggs and pineapple juice from can of crushed pineapple.
(If you need more liquid to make up the 1 1/2 cups, add water.
If oil is needed in the cake mix, also add.)

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix water, sugar and white vinegar until sugar is dissolved. Cool.
When cool, add mayonnaise, turmeric powder, celery salt, salt and pepper.
Set aside.
Cook rotini or ruffled macaroni until tender.
Drain.
Rinse with cold water; drain again.
Mix dressing and macaroni together.
Mixture will be soupy.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Next day, add some diced celery, chopped onions and green peppers.
Top with sliced, boiled eggs.
Cover and refrigerate several hours.

title: apple cake
directions: Do not use electric mixer.
Mix by hand.
Mix together sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, soda, cinnamon and salt together; add to mixture.
Add and mix, the apples and walnuts. Pour into a greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Glaze, if desired.
It is excellent without it.

title: speedy stroganoff
directions: Saute meat until brown.
(If using ground beef, drain off excess fat.)
Add celery and onion and cook until soft.
Add mushroom soup and 1 can water and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Add sour cream and dill and cook until thoroughly heated.
Do not let boil once sour cream is added.
Serve over egg noodles.
Serves 4.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: gaylynn's chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except onion rings and cheese, tog ether and place in a casserole.
Top with onion rings and Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: jam cake
directions: Mix butter
and
sugar.
Add
eggs,
milk and flour, in which baking soda and baking powder have been added.
Add jam, raisins, nuts
and
coconut.
Mix well and pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch
cake pans.	Bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until done.

title: fruit delight
directions: Mix melted margarine with cracker crumbs.
Cool crumbs in refrigerator so they become firm for ease of spreading next layer. Mix 10x sugar with cream cheese.
Add milk.
Mix well.
Put on top of chilled cracker crumbs.
Mix whip mix.
Put on top of cream cheese mixture.
Cool.
Top with pie filling.

title: baked corn casserole
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Butter a 2-quart casserole dish or spray with nonstick cooking spray.

title: eyelene's meat balls
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in a crock-pot.
Brown the meat balls, turning so they brown evenly.
Add the meat balls to the sauce mixture.
Set crock-pot on low for 35 to 45 minutes. Serve on party picks.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt margarine; beat eggs and add milk, cheese, salt and pepper.
Mix in macaroni.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, sour cream and bananas.
Blend in flour, baking powder, soda and nuts. Pour into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour.
Makes 1 regular loaf or 2 small loaves.

title: fruit squares
directions: Cream the butter and sugar, then add eggs one at a time.
Add the flour and almond flavoring to the creamed mixture.
Spread on a greased and floured jelly roll pan.
With a knife, make scores (X) of 4 across and 6 down.
Drop a spoonful of pie filling in middle of each score.

title: fried okra
directions: In a medium bowl, combine egg and water. Stir in okra, making sure it is thoroughly coated with egg mixture.

In a plastic bag, combine cornmeal, flour and salt. With a slotted spoon, remove okra from egg mixture and place it in the plastic bag with cornmeal mixture. Shake vigorously so that okra is totally coated. Add more cornmeal, if needed.
In a large skillet, heat 1/4-inch of oil until it is hot.
Add okra.
Reduce heat to medium.
Place a cover on the skillet and cook for about 30 minutes or until okra is browned on all sides, turning okra every 10 minutes.
You may need to add more oil if skillet dries out.

title: onion soup potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes; slice 1/4-inch thick into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Add onion soup mix and stir lightly.
Cut butter into pieces; place on potatoes.
Cover; place in microwave.
Cook on High for 9 to 11 minutes or until potatoes are tender, stirring once.
Let stand, covered, about 5 minutes before serving.
Yield: 4 to 5 servings.

title: no bake lemon cheese bake
directions: Coat a 9-inch spring-form pan with nonstick cooking spray. Sprinkle half of graham cracker crumbs on the bottom and 1-inch up the sides of pan. Set aside. Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Cool to room temperature. In a blender, combine the gelatin mixture, cream cheese and cottage cheese; cover and process until smooth. Transfer mixture to a bowl; fold in whipped topping. Pour into prepared pan. Sprinkle with remaining graham cracker crumbs. Cover and refrigerate for at least 4 hours or until set. Carefully run a knife around edge of pan to loosen, then remove sides of pan. Garnish with pie filling. Yield: 8 servings.

title: irish cream liqueur
directions: In blender, combine all ingredients until smooth.
Serve over ice, if desired.
Store tightly covered in refrigerator up to one month before serving.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Fry
chicken in light batter until golden brown.
Place cooked rice
in
bottom
of
baking
dish with chicken on top. Cover with soup.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: the pinkston cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add baking powder, salt and flour, alternately with milk, to mixture, starting and ending with flour. Set aside.
Beat egg whites and vanilla until soft peaks form. Add to preceding mixture.
Bake at 350° until done in pan that has been greased and floured.

title: easy outrageous candy
directions: In large mixing bowl, mix together the first four ingredients. Break the almond bark into small chunks and melt in microwave for about 90 seconds on High.
Stir in peanut butter and microwave for 30 seconds more.
Drizzle over and mix into the first ingredients. Drop onto waxed paper.
If mixture hardens, microwave for few seconds.
After candies cool, store in covered tins between layers of waxed paper.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together, then add the lemon juice.
Pour into graham cracker pie shell, then put the pie filling on top and refrigerate overnight.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, eggs, baking soda and 1/2 cup nuts.
Bake in a 9 x 12-inch pan for 40 minutes at 350°.
Mix cream cheese, butter, vanilla, powdered sugar and nuts for frosting on cake.

title: jubilee jumbles
directions: Mix thoroughly the shortening, sugars and eggs.
Stir in evaporated milk and vanilla.
Sift together flour, soda and salt; stir in.
Blend in nuts.
Chill 1 hour.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 425° for 45 minutes.

title: holiday punch(serves 40 people)
directions: Mix altogether in large punch bowl.
Float scoops of sherbet in punch.

title: reese's peanut butter candy
directions: Cream together the first 3 ingredients; pat out in a 13 x 9-inch cake pan and cover with melted chips.
Put into freezer to set up.
Remove from freezer and cut into bars.
Store in airtight container.

title: shoe peg corn salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding salt and pepper to taste. Refrigerate.
Yields 4 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 60 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: armenian rice pilaf
directions: Melt butter in
pan.
Break up vermicelli into pieces and fry in the butter until slightly browned, stirring constantly. Add rice to the vermicelli and saute them together for a few minutes, always stirring.
Add broth and salt.
Bring to boil; lower the heat.
Cook until water is absorbed.
Stir once during cooking. Serve hot.

title: peach cooler
directions: Place milk, peaches and cinnamon in blender.
Cover and blend at high speed until smooth.
Add ice cream and blend on low speed until smooth.
Pour into glasses and enjoy.

title: mini pizzas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
On greased cookie sheet, flatten out biscuits with greased hands.
Top with pizza sauce, toppings and cheese.
Bake for 8 minutes or until crust is brown and cheese melts.

title: potato salad dressing
directions: Combine and heat until it thickens, stirring constantly.

title: rocky road frosting
directions: Combine butter, sugar, milk and vanilla in bowl.
Add egg; beat until well blended.
Add chocolate (melted); mix well.
Stir in walnuts and marshmallows.
Enough for 2 layers.

title: worthy bars
directions: Mix oatmeal, brown sugar and margarine together like a pie crust.
Add vanilla and white Karo syrup; mix well.
Press mixture onto the bottom of a well-greased cookie sheet that has edges. Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: chicken criniti(with peas, prosciutto and roasted peppers)
directions: Slice chicken into strips.
Flour lightly and saute with a little oil of choice until cooked.
Add peas, Prosciutto and sliced, roasted peppers.
Add your favorite tomato sauce to the mixture.
Pour over spaghetti.

title: cheese fries
directions: Deep-fry fries until done. Put on paper towel to drain grease. Put them on a foil-lined cookie sheet (I like to put nonstick spray on the foil, then cheese doesn't stick), then spread cheese and bacon bits over. Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: chicken fettucini oriental stir-fry
directions: Boil fettucini in water until tender; drain and set aside.
In large skillet, stir-fry in olive oil chicken pieces with cabbage or broccoli until tender.
Stir in snow peas and water chestnuts. Sprinkle several drops of soy sauce while stir-frying.
Pour this mixture over fettucini and serve.
(This is best if you also add soy sauce to fettucini and mix.)

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt. Cream together the oleo, shortening, sugar and vanilla. Add the egg and cream until mixture is fluffy. Stir in dry ingredients until mixture is smooth.
Mix in the milk.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet. Flatten with glass that has been dipped in sugar. Bake at 400° about 12 minutes. Makes 5 1/2 dozen.

title: arctic melon pops
directions: Combine ingredients in blender and blend until smooth.
Place in 8 (5 ounce) paper cups (or Tupperware popsicle containers) and cover with foil.
Insert wooden stick through hole in the middle of foil.
Freeze overnight.
Remove foil and paper.

title: chocolate caramelita bars
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan. Combine first 7 ingredients. Reserve 1 cup.
Press remaining onto bottom of pan. Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°. Cool 10 minutes.
Top with nuts and chocolate pieces. Drizzle with topping mixed with 1/4 cup flour.
Sprinkle with reserved oat mix.
Bake an additional 18 to 22 minutes. Cool completely.

title: grandma's cheesecake
directions: Cream the two cheeses together.
Add sugar and blend until smooth.
Add eggs, flour and cornstarch.
Mix well.
Add margarine, lemon juice and vanilla.
Mix well and fold in sour cream.
Bake in greased spring pan for 1 hour at 350° or until golden brown.
Turn oven off.
Leave in closed oven for 2 hours.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Grease 10-inch skillet.
Combine cornmeal, flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
In another bowl combine eggs, buttermilk, sour cream and corn, then stir in melted butter and chili peppers.
Combine cornmeal mixture and buttermilk mixture. Pour in skillet.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake one hour at 375°.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and heat to dissolve sugar and salt.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender container.
Cover and blend on high speed until completely mixed.
Refrigerate in a tightly covered container up to 4 weeks.
Serve on fruit or tossed salad. Makes 2 cups of dressing.

title: cheese crispies
directions: Cream margarine with cheese; add flour and salt, then blend in Tabasco sauce and add Rice Krispies.
Chill dough overnight.
Form level teaspoons of dough into balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten balls with fork; they can be placed fairly close together, since they do not spread.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 10 minutes.

title: batter for onion rings
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Dip onion rings in batter.
Deep fry to a golden brown.

title: neiman-marcus cookies
directions: Mix together and spread in greased cake pan.

title: crab dip (or casserole)
directions: Cook onions, celery and butter over low heat until wilted, not brown.
Add rest of ingredients and mix altogether.
This can be used as dip or poured into a buttered dish and topped with buttered bread crumbs; bake as for a casserole.

title: communion bread
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Work in the butter as for pastry.
Add milk to make stiff dough.
Roll out in sheets; mark in strips 1-inch wide and prick with fork 1-inch apart.
Bake in moderate oven (350°), until lightly browned.
Serves 50.

title: chow-chow
directions: Boil first 5 ingredients; sprinkle with turmeric.
Let boil again.
Add sugar and salt to taste.
Put in jars and seal.

title: 7 day pickle
directions: Cover cucumbers with boiling water for 3 days.
Take cucumbers out and boil fresh water.
If cucumbers become soft, discontinue. On fourth day, peel
and slice.
Heat vinegar, sugar, salt and pickling spice.
Add sliced cucumbers.
On the fifth and sixth day, drain.
Heat brine to boiling, then add cucumbers.
On seventh day, heat brine, add cucumbers and heat through.
Put a little alum in jar.
Seal.

title: bacardi tropical punch
directions: Mix together and chill 2 hours. Pour punch over block of ice in punch bowl.
Float strawberries, lemons, limes and oranges.

title: chess cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter and mix with cake mix and 1 egg.
This will be thick and you will need to pat into greased cake pan.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine onion rings and cheese.
Sprinkle on chicken mixture. Bake 1/2 hour at 350°, uncovered.
Don't overheat as mayonnaise may separate.

title: banana nut bread with butter icing
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs together in mixer or by hand for 2 minutes.
Add sifted flour and mix well.
Stir in crushed bananas and nuts.
Pour in a well-greased and floured pan and bake in moderate oven 40 to 50 minutes.

title: upside-down date pudding
directions: Dissolve brown sugar and water in a deep cake pan.
Mix other ingredients and drop by teaspoonful on brown sugar mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Turn upside-down onto large serving plate and serve with whip cream.

title: herb hot and sour soup
directions: Partially freeze chicken or pork.
Cut meat into 1 x 1/4-inch strips.
Sprinkle meat with 1 tablespoon of the soy sauce.
In large saucepan, bring chicken broth to boiling; stir in meat, the remaining soy sauce, vinegar, pepper, sugar, mushrooms, cabbage and carrots.
Simmer, covered, 20 minutes.
Add basil; simmer 3 minutes.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Cook bacon until crisp, removing crumbles.
Brown beef in drippings (if bacon is very greasy, pour off grease).
Add soup, wine, parsley and pepper.
Cover; cook over low for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Add onions and mushrooms.
Cover and cook 1 hour more. Serve over wide noodles and top with bacon.

title: cayenne potatoes
directions: In large skillet, heat oil until hot.
Saute potatoes 20 to 25 minutes, or until golden brown.
Stir in cayenne, tarragon, scallions, salt and pepper; toss to coat potatoes well.
Cook about one minute more.
Serves 4.

title: dill bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Slice bread in 1/2-inch slices, but do not cut all the way through the bread.
In microwave, melt butter along with rosemary and dill weed.
Pull bread slices apart and brush the butter mixture in between the slices and on top of the loaf.
Wrap the loaf in tinfoil and bake at 350° for approximately 15 to 20 minutes.

title: festive tossed salad
directions: In a blender or food processor, combine sugar, vinegar, lemon juice, onion and salt.
Cover and process until blended.
With blender running, gradually add oil.
Add poppy seed and blend.

title: classic new york cheesecake
directions: Mix crumbs, 3 Tbsp. sugar and margarine. Press onto bottom of 9 inch springform pan. Bake at 325 degrees for 10 minutes. Mix cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and vanilla with electric mixer until well blended. Add sour cream; mix well. Add eggs one at a time mixing on low speed after each addition just until blended. Pour over crust. Bake at 325 degrees for 1 hour and 5 minutes or until center is almost set if using silver springform pan. If using dark metallic springform pan, bake at 300 degrees for 1 hour and 5 minutes. Loosen cake from side of pan. Cool before removing rim of pan. Refrigerate 4 hours or over night.

title: salmon ball(dip)
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Form into a ball.
Roll ball in chopped nuts and parsley.
Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Combine meat, rice, onions, garlic, oil, 1 tablespoon tomato paste, 1 tablespoon salt, 1/2 teaspoon black pepper, oregano and egg.
Wash green peppers; cut off tops and remove seeds.
Fill peppers with meat mixture.
Place, open side down, in circle in roasting pan.
Combine all remaining ingredients, except potatoes; pour over peppers.
Place potato slices in center of pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 400°.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients with hands.
Shape in rolls.
Wrap in Handi-Wrap and put in the refrigerator for 24 hours.
Unwrap and bake at 300° for 1 hour on a broiler pan.

title: manicotti and cheese
directions: Brown beef, onion and pepper.
Add puree, salt, pepper, sugar, oregano and basil.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Combine Ricotta, 3/4 cup Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese with egg.
Cook manicotti shells and fill with cheese mixture.
Place 1/2 of meat sauce in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add filled shells.
Cover with remaining sauce, Mozzarella and Parmesan.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Sift
flour
with
baking powder and salt.
Add oil and milk; mix
quickly to a soft dough.
Knead until smooth.	Pat or	roll to	1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with biscuit cutter and place	in greased baking pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 12 to 18 biscuits.

title: jason's "rice stuff"
directions: Mix all ingredients, using 1 (8 ounce) package cheese. Put in greased pan; cover with other 8-ounce package of cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Coarsely chop 1 1/2 cups candy.
Beat margarine and sugars. Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, soda and salt; mix well. Stir in candy. Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 11 minutes.
Remove from oven. Press remaining candy into cookies.

title: melt away bars
directions: Combine egg yolk and remaining ingredients, except walnuts. Blend well at low speed of mixer.
Stir in 1/2 cup walnuts; mix thoroughly.
Spread in ungreased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.

title: deluxe gingerbread(serves 9)
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Blend in egg and molasses.
Stir in dry ingredients sifted together alternately with buttermilk.
Pour in a greased and floured 9 x 3-inch square pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: gumbo
directions: Season and brown chicken in oil over medium heat. Add sausage to pot and saut with chicken. Remove both from pot. Make a roux with equal parts of oil (must be free of food particles to avoid burning) and flour to desired color. Add onions, celery and green peppers. Add garlic to the mixture and stir continuously. After vegetables reach desired tenderness, return chicken and sausage to pot and cook with vegetables, continuing to stir frequently. Gradually stir in liquid; bring to a boil. Reduce heat to simmer and cook for an hour or more. Season to taste with Joe's Stuff seasoning. Ten minutes before serving, add green onions. Serve gumbo over rice or without rice. Serve with French bread.

title: barbecue sauce(sloppy joes)
directions: Heat all ingredients, except meat.
Brown meat and drain.
Mix with barbecue sauce.

title: italian chicken and rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir together water, rice, tomato sauce, cheese spread, onions and 1 teaspoon Italian seasoning into greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Top with chicken, sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and remaining Italian seasonings.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In a bowl, combine the sour cream, soup and poppy seeds. Stir in chicken and pour into a greased 11 x 7 x 2 baking dish. Combine the cracker crumbs and butter and sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: caramel walnut bars
directions: Combine flour, sugar and egg.
Cut in butter until crumbly. Stir in nuts.
Reserve 2 cups crumbs.
Press remainder of mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: barbecue pork chops(pork chops and barbecue sauce is a great combination.)
directions: In a skillet, brown pork chops in oil, then place in casserole dish.
Make sauce by mixing in a bowl the remaining ingredients and pour over pork chops.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Cook and crumble sausage .
Drain.
Line bottoms of pie shells with sausage.
Beat eggs, 2/3 cup milk, mustard, salt, grated cheese and sour cream.
Mix and pour over sausage.
You can freeze pies at this point or bake at 350° for 1 hour.
If frozen, do not thaw before cooking.

title: wisconsin toasted cheese sandwich
directions: For one sandwich, toast one side of bread; butter untoasted side.
Lay 2 (1/3-inch) thick slices tomato on buttered side. Spread with 1 tablespoon each of onion and green pepper.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika, then sprinkle or place 3 tablespoons of aged cheese over all.
Place the cheese-topped slice under the broiler and boil until cheese is melted and toast nicely brown.
Remove from broiler and serve immediately.

title: cocoa bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in cooled milk.
Add 1 teaspoon sugar and 2 cups flour.
Beat well.
Let rise.

title: grand marnier french toast
directions: Heat 2 cups skim milk.
Put in large bowl.
Add 4 tablespoons sugar (somewhat more if you want a slightly sweeter taste).
Add 2 eggs (or 3 egg whites/no yolks, if you want to lower your LDL cholesterol).
Carefully add 1 tablespoon cardamon.
Stir.
Mixture should be warm (just about body temperature if you have a high fever).
Add 1 package yeast.
Add 2 or 3 cups flour and 1 cup whole oats.
Mix well and let rise several hours.

title: potato soup-in-a-skillet
directions: Cover potatoes, onion and celery with water in large saucepan. Bring to a boil. Cover and cook until tender.
Drain and set aside.
In a large iron skillet, melt margarine. Add vegetables, milk and ham. Season to taste.
Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes, adding more milk to desired consistency.

title: no-clam chowder
directions: Saute onion in bacon drippings in a saucepan until lightly browned.
Add potatoes and water.
Cook, uncovered, over medium heat for 10 to 15 minutes or until tender.
Add corn, milk, salt and pepper.
Heat to serving temperature over low heat, stirring frequently.
Do not boil.
Ladle into soup bowls.
Top with crumbled bacon.
Serves 5.

title: low fat lunch
directions: Microwave potato until done, according to size of potato. Add toppings in order of preference.
Very filling!

title: honey oatmeal bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup warm water.
Pour boiling water over oatmeal and set aside to cool until lukewarm. Mix all ingredients and beat well, then add yeast, being sure everything is just warm before adding.
Work in enough white flour (preferably unbleached) to make a nice spongy dough that is not sticky.
Grease top and let rise; knead and let rise again.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes, depending on the size of the loaves.
A delicious, nourishing bread.

title: mango squash
directions: Boil the sugar and the water; strain through a cloth to clean it.
Add mango juice and other ingredients which will act as preservative.
If you don't want to keep the squash for any length of time, omit the potassium meta-bisulfite.

title: orange baked chicken
directions: Arrange in shallow pan, not overlapping.
Sprinkle with onion. Blend flavor with 1/2 cup orange juice and add remaining orange juice.
Pour over breasts and sprinkle with seasoning.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour (until tender).
Baste occasionally. Serve on rice or noodles.

title: potato filling-stuffing
directions: Boil and
mash the potatoes.
Add warm milk; beat until light and
fluffy.
Cook	the
chopped onion and celery in the butter; do	not
brown.
Add the cubed bread, parsley, egg and salt and pepper.
Add
this	to the potatoes.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: peach delight jello salad
directions: Make jello according to package directions.
Cool slightly and add drained peaches.
Cool completely until congealed.

title: ho-ho cake
directions: Bake as directed and cool completely.
Cut into 4 layers or make 2 layers.

title: condiment
directions: Mix all ingredients and use to season meats, gravies, gumbo, etc.

title: mexican chef salad
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add kidney beans, if desired, and salt.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Cut up lettuce.
Toss with grated cheese.
Add hot sauce to taste, onion, if desired, French dressing and ground beef mixture (cooled).
Crunch and add corn or tortilla chips on top.

title: crab meat casserole
directions: Squeeze lemon on crab meat.
Make a cream sauce of milk, flour and butter.
Add crab meat and other ingredients.
Place in casserole and top with cheese and crumbs.
