Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together the margarine and sugar.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Combine ingredients and bake at 350° until done. Top with Banana Icing.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Cover broiler pan with foil.
Cut eggplant into 1/2-inch slices.
Place on broiler pan.
Use 1 to 1 1/2 tablespoons olive oil to brush both sides of eggplant.
Broil 4 to 5-inches from heat until medium brown, turning once.
Set aside.

title: brownie pie
directions: Coarsely chop 1 1/2 cups nuts.
In medium saucepan, over low heat, stir condensed milk, butter and cocoa until butter melts and mixture is warm; remove from heat.
Stir in eggs, flour, vanilla and chopped nuts.
Pour into prepared crust.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until center is firm.
Serve warm or cold garnished with whipped cream and remaining nuts.

title: fried apple pies
directions: Can use giant canned biscuits.
Roll out flat.
Put apples in and fold over.
Fry until brown.

title: kahlua cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together in bowl; beat for 5 minutes. Add chocolate chips.
Spray Pam in Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on top.

title: chili dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and heat. Serve in a chafing dish with your choice of chips.

title: chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar in a large bowl.
Add eggs and vanilla. Blend well. Combine flour, cocoa, soda and salt. Gradually blend into creamed mixture. Stir in nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 9 minutes. Do not overbake. Cookies will be soft.
Cool on sheets until set, about 1 minute.
Remove to wire rack to cool completely. Store in airtight container.
Yields about 4 1/2 dozen.

title: fruit punch
directions: Heat sugar and water until sugar dissolves; cool.
Combine juice with mixture.
Add ginger ale and club soda just before serving.
Make fruit cups with cherries and orange slices; add water.
Freeze and use in punch instead of punch ring.

title: beer and kraut fudge cake
directions: Mix chocolate with cream cheese.

title: chicken con queso
directions: Take skin off chicken breasts.
Boil until chicken is done. Drain, peel chicken off the bones and tear into small pieces. Combine soup, cheese, milk, peppers and onions.
Blend together. In a 3-quart casserole dish, put 1/3 cup crushed chips on the bottom.
Top with chicken, then 1/2 cup soup mixture.
Repeat layers until all is gone.
Bake in
a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: lower fat meat loaf
directions: Combine oats and milk in a bowl.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Add turkey and next 7 ingredients.
Stir. Shape into loaf and place on rack coated with cooking spray.
Place rack on a shallow roasting pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a buttered baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Stir about every ten minutes so that it turns dark. Top pudding with cream.

title: chicken and macaroni
directions: Mix altogether.
Put
buttered	crumbs on top.	Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: teriyaki marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients well.

Marinate vegetables and chunks of meat (beef, chicken or shrimp) for 30 minutes. Place on skewers and grill over medium-hot fire until done, about 15 to 20 minutes. Use remaining sauce for basting toward the end of the cooking time.

title: corn and sausage casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cracker crumbs, mixing well. Spoon into a lightly greased 10 x 6 x 1 3/4-inch baking pan; sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes, or until done.
Serves 6.

title: summer punch
directions: Mix punch base.
Add 1 quart ginger ale to each quart base when ready to serve.
Makes 40 (5-ounce) cups.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Brown hamburger and bacon. Combine in bowl with onion, celery, tomato, egg and tomato sauce. Sprinkle half of cheese. Clean
out seeds from zucchini and stuff with ingredients. Partially cook zucchini if it is large. Place in pan with 1/2-inch water. Bake 45 minutes at 350°. Last 5 minutes top with rest of cheese to melt.

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar, eggs, lemon juice and vanilla until fluffy.
Line muffin tin with baking cups.
Place vanilla wafer in each baking cup.
Fill cups 2/3 with batter.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.
Top with 1/2 teaspoon of blueberry pie filling.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: In a casserole dish, put your first layer of crescent rolls. Spread a layer of cream cheese on top of this. Next, layer sausage and then bacon pieces. Put your final layer of crescent rolls on top. I usually spread a little "squeeze" butter on top of this. Bake in a preheated oven at 350° until golden brown. There is really no set recipe for this, just judge by how many you are serving.

title: vegetable sauce
directions: Blend all ingredients in a bowl.
Spoon over hot vegetables. Serve at once.

title: bean salad
directions: Combine beans, peppers, onions and pimentos.
In another bowl combine sugar, oil, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Mix together. Chill.
Tastes better if made 24 hours or more in advance.
Keeps 2 weeks or more in refrigerator.

title: pineapple cole slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, apples, pineapple, celery, marshmallows and enough Miracle Whip to moisten.
Toss lightly.
Serve in lettuce lined salad bowl.

title: candied grapefruit peel
directions: Grapefruit directions:
Cut peel from grapefruit; cut peel into strips.
Add cold water to cover strips of peel.
Cover and bring to boil; boil 5 minutes.
Drain and repeat 3 times (this removes bitterness).
Add sugar and 1 cup water to drained peel.
Bring to boil and boil gently over low heat until syrup is thick and almost absorbed by peels, stirring occasionally.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Roll in tinted sugar while still hot so sugar will stick to peels.

title: peanut butter and jelly bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Generously	grease	a
x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix flour,
baking
powder
and sugar in a large bowl until well blended.
Cut	in butter with a pastry blender or two knives until
mixture
resembles
coarse crumbs.
Beat eggs and vanilla with fork
in a small bowl until foamy;
stir into flour mixture until well blended.
Drop half the dough by heaping tablespoonfuls into
prepared
pan.
Pat
into
a flat layer with greased fingers
(dough
will
be sticky).	Spread evenly with jelly; drop
teaspoonfuls peanut butter over jelly.
Spoon remaining dough
over
top.
Bake
for
30 to 35 minutes until brown.
Cool in	pan on rack until warm.
Cut in 2 x 1-inch bars.
Store covered.
Makes 48 bars.

title: sweet potato-chocolate nut cake
directions: Butter and flour a 10-inch tube pan. Place chocolate and vanilla in double boiler and melt until smooth. Sift dry ingredients and set aside. Beat oil and sweet potatoes together, then beat in eggs one at a time until well blended. Slowly add dry ingredients; mix well and stir in nuts. Put 1/3 of mixture in another bowl and stir in chocolate. Alternate batters in tube pan (like a marble cake). With a knife, cut through the 2 batters to swirl together.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Melt oleo and dates.
Cream sugar with egg yolks and add to oleo and dates.
Cook in heavy skillet over low heat for 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add nuts, Rice Krispies and vanilla.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Butter pan and press firmly.
It will be hot.
Use back of spoon.
Let set until cold.
With buttered knife, cut into 1-inch squares and dust with powdered sugar.
Freezes well.

title: mexican squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender, then mash.
Combine in a large bowl squash, cheese, green chilies and tomatoes and onion.
Pour mixture in a 2-quart baking dish.
Bake in oven at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes until casserole is bubbling.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: creamed tacos
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and bell pepper; drain.
Add soups and chilies.
Tear tortillas to quarter size and mix with other ingredients.
Put in casserole dish.
Cover with cheese and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: elida's flan
directions: Melt the sugar in an 8 or 9-inch cake pan; set aside.
Mix all remaining ingredients together.
Pour into pan where sugar was melted (be sure pan with sugar is cooled).
Bake double boiler-style with cake pan placed in water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Turn over after cooled.

title: south-of-the-border casserole
directions: Brown meat and add onion; cook until tender.
Stir in tomato sauce and seasonings.
Alternate layers of meat mixture, tortillas and cheese in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: strawberry nut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients for cake with an electric mixer.
Put in 3 greased and floured 8-inch
pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: yams with pineapple
directions: If using fresh yams, cook and salt them.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Beat the butter and sugar to a cream and add well-beaten yolks of
the
eggs, then the milk, chopped nuts (toss nut meats
in small
amount
of flour to coat; this prevents nuts from
falling to bottom of layers) and extract.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt and add to the other ingredients.
Bake in two 8-inch layer pans for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Ice
with Butter
Frosting.
If desired, dribble glaze over top and garnish with nut meats.

title: chicken-vegetable pot pie
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Cook vegetables in broth.
Remove one-half of the broth and add soups.
Stir, mixing well.
Thicken with flour.
Pour into 8 x 11-inch glass dish and cover with pie crusts.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes 2 pies.
I usually freeze one.

title: jumbles(flora engle's written note:  "tried, good, may 14, '08.")
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Beat in eggs, milk, baking powder and flavoring to taste.
Add flour, enough to make into a soft dough.

Do not roll it on the paste-board, but break off pieces of dough the size of a walnut and make into rings by rolling out rolls as large as your finger and joining the ends; lay them on tins to bake, an inch apart, as it rises and spreads, baking in a moderate oven.

title: double-chocolate walnut brownies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate in medium saucepan over moderate heat.
Remove from heat.
Beat in sugar, gradually, with a wooden spoon, until thoroughly combined.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Stir in flour until thoroughly combined.
Stir in 1 cup of walnuts. Spread into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: cookin' beef supper
directions: Heat oil in wok or large skillet.
Cook and stir meat and onion until onion is tender and meat is almost done.
Add water, the reserved mandarin orange syrup, soy sauce and ginger.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and cover.
Simmer as long as desired to tenderize the meat.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add oil, vanilla and sugar.
Add combined dry ingredients, then mix in nuts and zucchini.
Bake at 350°.
Use 2 regular loaf pans.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Separate eggs.
Keep the egg white for topping of pie.
Beat yellow and mix with all other ingredients.
Cook over burning eye until thickened.
Pour into a pie crust.
Bake in oven at 350° until top is browned.

title: tangy tomato salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of electric blender. Process until smooth.
Cover and chill.
Serve over salad greens. Yield:
1 1/2 cups (18 calories per tablespoon).

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add pumpkin, nuts, raisins or chocolate chips.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder and cinnamon together.
Combine mixes.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: bridal shower punch
directions: Thaw ice cream, adding ginger ale when ready to serve.
Mix to right consistency.
Makes 40 to 50 (5 ounce) servings.

title: bundt cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Combine dry ingredients and stir in alternately with milk and vanilla.
Pour 2/3 of the batter into a greased Bundt pan.
To remaining batter stir in chocolate syrup.
Pour over batter already in the pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Cake is done when toothpick comes out clean.
when the cake is cooled, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: peach congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; then add cold water.
Stir in the pie filling.
Pour in dish and congeal until firm.
Mix sugar, sour cream and cream cheese together and spread on top of salad.

title: flank steak marinade
directions: Blend ingredients well.
Pierce meat on both sides; marinate 6 hours (or however long you have).
Broil meat 3 inches from heat, 4 minutes per side.
Boil down remaining marinade on stove and pass as sauce.

title: marshmallow fudge pie
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine, add sugar, egg, Marshmallow Creme and vanilla extract. Pour into crust.
Microwave 9 minutes, rotating at 3 minute intervals.

title: banana pudding
directions: Make pudding according to directions. Add sweetened condensed milk. Mix. Add Cool Whip. Mix. Layer cookies, bananas and pudding mixture. Continue this, ending with pudding mixture. Top with cookies. Best when made the day before.

title: blueberry sauce
directions: Measure blueberries.
In saucepan, combine the sugar with cornstarch or flour and salt.
Add lemon juice and water; stir until well blended.
Then bring to a boil over high heat, whisking vigorously.
Cook until thickened, about 2 minutes.
Stir in the berries, butter and flavoring.
Serve warm
over pound cake, angel cake or ice cream.

title: low-fat and sodium soup
directions: All vegetables listed are select Green Giant frozen packages.

title: poor boy casserole
directions: Butter pan all over.
Spread peeled potatoes across the bottom of pan.
Then spread hamburger meat, then another layer of potatoes.
Next, put mixed vegetables on top.
Cook 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: burgundy beef and mushrooms(microwave method)
directions: Cut
steak
into
1-inch cubes and place in
a	2
quart casserole.	Add stock, wine, tomato paste,	garlic,
bay
leaf, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Stir, cover and refrigerate overnight.
Stir in mushrooms.	Cover
and
microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Stir.
Microwave on
(Medium-low) for 15 minutes, stirring midway through.
Combine
water
and flour and stir into beef mixture.
Microwave on
30% (Medium-low) for 10 minutes, stirring midway through cooking.
Remove
bay leaf. Serve over rice.

title: fish camp slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients and
place	in a gallon jar.
Store in refrigerator.

title: chocolate fudge pudding
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt, sugar and 2 tablespoons cocoa.
Add milk, shortening and vanilla.
Mix until smooth.
Add pecans.
Put in greased 1-quart baking dish.
Mix brown sugar and remaining 4 tablespoons cocoa.
Sprinkle over top.
Add 1 1/2 cups boiling water to top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: don's vidalia onion grill
directions: Petal onion; put in foil and top with ingredients.
Wrap up. Cook on grill until tender, about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: leek soup
directions: Cook bacon and remove from pan.
Add onion, leeks and potato to bacon grease.
Cook for 1 minute. Add chicken broth, pepper and nutmeg.
Let simmer for 45 minutes until potato is soft.
Put into blender and puree (put in a little at a time).
Put mixture back in pot. Add milk.
Cook on low until hot (do not boil).

title: lemon poppy bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat 3 minutes.
Bake in 2 greased loaf pans (8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 3/4-inch) at 350° for 40 minutes. Spread slices with butter.
This bread is light and delicious!

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix and sift the flour, sugar, soda, salt and baking powder. Cream the shortening and peanut butter; gradually beat in eggs and milk.
Add to flour and sugar mixture.
Add vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased baking sheet.
Bake in a moderately hot oven, 375°, for 12 minutes.

title: banana-nut cake
directions: Mix
all
ingredients together.
Place in a greased pan at 350° degrees for 30 minutes.

title: heavenly chocolate ice cream
directions: In large saucepan mix candy and Eagle Brand milk.
Cook on low heat until candy melts.
Stir all the time.
Let cool and add 1 quart of milk; mix well.
Add chocolate syrup.
Pour in freezer. Finish filling freezer to line with milk.
Add ice and salt. Freeze.

title: pennsylvania dutch dressing
directions: Fill large mixing bowl with soft bread crumbs.
Add onion and celery (both chopped, not minced, in blender), parsley, butter, milk (enough to moisten), eggs, potatoes, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Can add more mashed potatoes; doesn't make much of a difference.
Pour a little more melted butter over top of casserole.
Use all the butter.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: scotcheroo
directions: Cook in a saucepan over medium heat until mixture boils, corn syrup and sugar.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter (can be crunchy).
Add and mix Rice Krispies.
Press mixture in buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Let harden. Melt over low heat; stir to blend the chocolate chips and butterscotch chips.
Spread over Krispies mixture in pan.
Chill until top is firm.
Cut into bars.

title: apricot pasta
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix cream cheese, butter and flour as for pie crust.
Cut four pieces of waxed paper the size of your cookie sheet.
Divide the dough in half and roll each half out between two layers of waxed paper until entire paper is covered. Refrigerate 15 to 30 minutes.
Place one layer of pastry on greased cookie sheet.
Spread with all of the jam and top with second layer of pastry.
Remove waxed paper as you work.
Brush top of pastry with water and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake 45 minutes or until nicely browned.
Cut in squares.

title: baked sausage cheese balls
directions: Take sausage out of wrapper.
Place in mixing bowl.
Grate cheese; add to sausage.
Mix well.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Coat with coating mix.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake until brown at 400°.
Cool on paper towel.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Melt oleo in a skillet.
Saute onion over medium heat until clear.
Place 1/2 of saltine crumbs in the bottom of casserole dish.
Add 1/2 of sauteed onions to mushroom soup.
Add 1/2 of milk and spread a layer over onions.
Add the other 1/2 of onions and then the rest of soup.
Combine the eggs and the rest of the milk and pour over all.
Top with crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until slightly brown and bubbly.

title: barbecue polish sausage appetizers
directions: Slice sausage 1/2-inch thick.
Place sausage in casserole dish.
Mix the remaining ingredients together and pour over sausage.
Stir to blend.
Cover dish and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or place all ingredients in small crock-pot and cook for several hours for flavors to blend.

title: hawaiian banana nut bread
directions: Combine flour, salt, baking soda, sugar, cinnamon, stir in pecans.
Combine beaten eggs, vegetable oil, mashed bananas, drained pineapple and vanilla;
add to
flour mixture, stirring, just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Spoon batter into 2 greased and floured 8-1/2 x 4-1/2 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and let cool on wire racks.

title: hot ham sandwiches
directions: Mix butter, mustard, onion, seed and Worcestershire sauce together.
Spread on rolls (both sides).
Top with cheese and ham. Wrap in foil and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Can be frozen or made the day before and refrigerated.

title: bagels
directions: Prepare dough; dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water and add 1 1/2 teaspoons of sugar.
Set aside.
Sift the flour into a large bowl.
Make well in center of flour and add dissolved yeast mixture.
Add 1/2 cup of sugar, egg, 1 cup water, oil and salt. Mix with a large spoon, adding flour as needed until no longer sticky.
Use hands to mix dough into a ball.
Place in greased dish.
Set in warm place and let rise until doubled in size (about 1 1/2 hours).

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dump all ingredients in layers in order given in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Do not mix anything.
Bake for 55 minutes or until done.

title: frozen fruit cup
directions: After preparing and combining fruits, boil water.
Add sugar and stir until dissolved.
Add orange juice and lemonade.
Cool. Pour over fruit after it is put in freezer containers.
Freeze for no longer than 6 months.

title: no bake bars
directions: Melt chips, butter and peanut butter. Add remaining ingredients. Stir. Press into buttered pan. Chill.

title: shish kabob "russian style"
directions: Cut lamb into squares.
Pour into big bowl.
Cover, or mix with sliced onion and pepper, then soak in the white wine.
On the next day, you may put it into the grill.
Soaking lamb should be stored in refrigerator overnight.

title: potato kugel
directions: Grease 40 madeleine molds.
(If you have only 1 pan with 12 molds, wash, dry and grease pan each time.)
In 3-quart saucepan, place potatoes and add enough water to cover.
Heat to boiling over high heat.
Cook potatoes 20 minutes or until fork-tender. Drain potatoes well and return to saucepan.
Cook drained potatoes over medium-high heat 1 to 2 minutes, stirring constantly, until all moisture on potatoes evaporates.

title: coconut-sour cream layer cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions, making two 8-inch layers.
When cool, split each layer to make a total of 4 layers.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown together hamburger and onion and drain fat.
Add tomato sauce, tomato paste, garlic powder, salt and oregano to
hamburger and simmer.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli.
Cook rice.
Saute onion and celery.
Stir in broccoli and rice.
Add soup and milk; stir in Cheez Whiz.
Bake in a 2-quart casserole for 1 hour at 350°.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Heat milk until hot.
Mix sugar and cornstarch; add a little milk to moisten.
Add egg yolks and mix well.
Pour gradually into hot milk.
Cook until it thickens (it takes a long time).
Pour into ice cream freezer and add remaining ingredients.

title: my favorite fresh spinach salad
directions: Wash spinach and tear into pieces.
Add drained bean sprouts and water chestnuts (drained and sliced thin).
Add boiled eggs, cut up; add bacon, fried crisp and crumbled.
Add onion, sliced thin and separated into rings.
Toss in large bowl and add dressing.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pork chop supreme
directions: Brown pork chops, season with salt and pepper.
Drain on paper towel.
Place pork chops in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Put onion slices on top of pork chops, follow with potato slices, spoon cheese soup mixed with water over all.
Sprinkle with garlic salt. Bake, covered at 350° for 1 hour or until meat and potatoes are tender.

title: baked chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli as directed until tender.
Place broccoli in oblong shallow baking dish.
Combine soup, nutmeg and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour half the mixture over broccoli. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup cheese.
Slice chicken and place over broccoli.
Pour remaining soup mixture over chicken.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Put onion soup mix in large plastic bag.
Add potatoes and oil.
Shake until potatoes are coated.
Put potatoes in shallow baking pan.
Bake for 40 minutes, stirring occasionally, and bake until tender and golden brown.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: chicken pie
directions: Remove chicken from bone and cut into bite-size pieces; place in a well-greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle chopped onion and celery over chicken.
Mix soup, 1 stick of melted margarine and 1 cup self-rising flour into a smooth paste; then add 1 cup of milk and mix well.
Pour mixture over chicken and bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: best ever carrots
directions: Combine carrots, bacon, onion, salt and pepper in an oiled 1-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and butter or margarine.
Cover and bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: rio grande pork chops
directions: Brown chops in a greased skillet over low heat for about 15 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Remove pork chops to platter.
Serve with sauce from skillet.

title: chicken breasts marinara
directions: In saucepan, combine onion and 1 tablespoon water.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Add water if needed.
Stir in tomatoes, water, celery, parsley, vinegar, spices and garlic; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer; discard bay leaf.
Cook chicken until done.
Cut into strips and add to sauce.
Spoon over cooked fettuccine.
Add cheese.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar well together.
Then add the egg, lemon juice and given amount of rhubarb.
Break butter in bits over this.

title: striped delight
directions: Combine crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and melted butter.
Press into bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill.
Beat the cream cheese with 1/4 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons of Cool Whip until smooth.
Fold in 1/2 of the whipped topping; spread over crust.
Prepare pudding, using 3 1/2 cups cold milk.
Pour over cream cheese layer.
Before serving, spread remaining whipped topping over pudding.

title: beef and potato loaf
directions: Arrange evenly in 2-quart greased baking dish potatoes, 2 tablespoons onions and 1 teaspoon of parsley flakes.
Mix the ground beef, milk,
crumbs, catsup, 1/4 c. onions, salt and pepper.
Spread evenly over potatoes.
Spread 1/4 cup catsup on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.

title: hot mulled punch
directions: Pour juices into 30 to 36-cup coffee maker. Place remaining ingredients in basket of coffee maker and brew according to coffee maker instructions. When complete, remove basket and discard spices. Serve hot. Makes 28 punch cup servings.

title: chocolate crinkle cookies
directions: Mix sugar, oil and cocoa.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add vanilla and dry ingredients.
Chill a few hours.
Drop teaspoons of dough in 1 cup 10x sugar; roll in sugar.
Shape into ball. Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: delicious bean soup
directions: Boil the beans in water for 2 minutes and remove from heat; let stand for 1 hour.
Then add the ham bone, garlic and bay leaf to the beans and cover and simmer for 2 hours or until they are tender.
Add vegetables and salt and pepper to taste and simmer for 1 hour longer.
Remove ham bone; cut off the meat and dice it; add to beans.
Reheat soup to boiling and then remove bay leaf.
Serve.

title: roast leg of lamb
directions: Sprinkle the lamb with lemon juice.
Mix garlic, curry, salt and pepper to paste; rub into lamb (a day before roasting).
Put roast in pan; arrange onions around.
Roast at 400° for 30 minutes. Drain off fat.
Add vermouth (or wine).
Reduce heat to 350°. Roast 1 1/2 hours longer, basting frequently.
Three (1/4-inch thick, 3-inch square) slices contain 275 calories.

title: no-bake strawberry lush
directions: Make jello.
Start to chill.
When partially chilled, add strawberries. Chill a little longer. combine sugar and cream cheese. Beat well.
Layer ladyfingers around bottom and edges of pan.
Pour 1/2 of cream cheese mixture in.
Add 1/2 of strawberry mixture.
Layer ladyfingers again.
Add rest of cream cheese mixture and final strawberry mixture.
Chill overnight.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Mix shortening, brown sugar and sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
In another bowl, mix together flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix the second mixture into the first.
Stir in 1/2 cup of M&M's.
Drop rounded teaspoonful of cookie dough 2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Decorate tops with candies.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt butter and chocolate, add sugar and milk.
Heat to blend. Bring to a rolling boil.

title: texas stew
directions: Drain tomatoes and save juice; add corn, beans and chopped tomatoes in a bowl.
Brown hamburger; drain.
Add juice mixture, picante sauce, salt, pepper and cumin.
Boil and simmer 20 to 30 minutes.

title: ira harvey's sweet pickle slices
directions: Cover cukes with salt water for 14 days.
Drain, rinse and slice.
Soak overnight, covered with alum water.
Drain; rinse. Soak overnight with vinegar.
Drain.
Add 10 pounds sugar and 1 box pickle spices.
Cover.
Set until sugar is dissolved.
Use sterilized canning procedures.

title: mary louise's pineapple casserole
directions: Beat eggs and mix with all other ingredients. Pour into buttered casserole dish. Cook in 350° oven for 45 minutes. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: chicken diable
directions: Melt butter in a pan (baking dish).
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Roll chicken in butter mixture coating (both sides). Arrange, skin side down, in a single layer in the same dish. Bake at 375° for 1 hour, basting every 15 minutes.

title: black bean salsa dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate for 2 hours before serving.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: baked fruit dish
directions: Drain all fruit.
Cut in bite size pieces.
Place in large baking dish.
Mix cornstarch with the brown sugar.
Sprinkle over fruit.
Sprinkle cinnamon over the top.
Cut up bits of butter over top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple frosting
directions: Add lemon juice to pineapple.
Use enough sugar to make a paste to spread on cake.

title: coconut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all together and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake until pie is well set and golden brown.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cornstarch. Add eggs, milk and melted butter and mix well; then add vanilla. Bake about 30 minutes at 350° or until brown. Makes 2 pies.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Pour all ingredients into blender; blend on medium speed. Pour into greased 10-inch glass pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Place berries in a thick layer in pie shell.
Cook sugar, water, cornstarch and jello until thick and clear.
Remove from heat.
Cool and pour over berries.
Chill several hours until set. Top with cool whip when ready to serve.

title: my chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate and water in saucepan.
Remove from heat and slowly stir in egg yolks.
Add vanilla.
Mix well and set aside to cool completely.
In separate bowl, cream together butter and powdered sugar.
Stir into cooled chocolate mixture.
Beat egg whites until very stiff.
Fold gently into chocolate.
Pour into pie shell and chill.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients (except for chips) together in a large bowl.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Cover with crushed potato chips.
Bake in a 450° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken and cheese enchiladas
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In center of each tortilla, place 1/4 cup chicken, 2 tablespoons cheese and 1 teaspoon salsa; roll up. Arrange seam-side down in 8-inch square baking dish.
Top with remaining salsa and cheese.
Bake 25 minutes or until thoroughhy heated.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: chocolate rocks
directions: Cream shortening and brown sugar; add the slightly beaten egg, then add the melted chocolate and mix until blended.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with the milk.
Mix in the chopped nuts.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet and bake in moderate oven (350°).
Do not overbake.

title: crab cakes
directions: Let butter and cheese soften to room temp.
Mix together all ingredients.
Spread on muffins.
Broil until crisp.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour and baking powder; add to sugar and Crisco, a little at a time. Also add milk a little at a time.
Add flavorings.
Pour in greased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool. Remove from pan.
Spread lemon juice and sugar mixture over top.

title: fish chowder
directions: Heat oven
to
Put all ingredients except butter and cream in 9 x 13 x 2-inch glass dish.
Put butter on top of vegetable and fish mixture;
cover	with tinfoil and bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours.	Put vegetable fish mixture into crock-pot.
Warm cream until just scalded;
add to crock-pot.
Set crock-pot on warm or low until ready to serve.

title: red salad dressing
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly and serve with mixed salad greens.

title: meat and shepherd pie
directions: Saute green peppers and onions in butter.
Brown chopped meat. Add bouillon
cubes,
salt,
pepper,
thyme and a little water and cornstarch.
Layer chopped meat, then layer of potato mixture. Boil
potatoes
and
mash.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese, bread crumbs and dabs
of
butter
on
top.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: ranch pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix 1 cup brown sugar, water and butter in saucepan.
Boil 5 minutes; pour into 8-inch square pan.
Mix rest of ingredients in bowl.
Spoon batter on top of sugar mixture; it will sink into the liquid and will spread out as it bakes.
Bake 45 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream or just plain.

title: spinach dip
directions: Put in blender and mix well. Season with salt, pepper and garlic powder.

title: potato skins
directions: Scrub and prick potatoes.
Rub with oil.
Bake 1 hour at 400° or until a fork comes out clean.
Let the potatoes cool.
Cut potatoes in 1/2 lengthwise and then slice in 1/2 again.
Scoop out inside of potato, leaving a shell about 1/4-inch thick (make sure they are not too thin).
Melt butter and brush onto sides of the potato skins.
Arrange skins on an ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 500° for 12 minutes or until crisp.
Remove carefully from oven with oven mitts and sprinkle with cheese and bacon bits.
Return to oven for 2 to 3 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serve with sour cream.

title: mexitalian lasagne
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine chili, salsa, mushrooms, Parmesan cheese and Italian seasoning.
In small bowl, stir together cottage cheese and parsley flakes.
Layer noodles, cottage cheese, chili mixture and Mozzarella cheese in a 9 x 9-inch baking dish sprayed with cooking spray; repeat to make 3 layers. Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Serves 6 to 9.

title: artichoke salad
directions: Prepare salad dressing mix according to package directions. If artichokes are whole, cut them up.
Pour all of the prepared salad dressing over the artichokes in a covered bowl.
Marinate at least 4 hours, longer if time allows.
Place salad greens, onions and pimentos in bowl.
Sprinkle with as much or as little Parmesan cheese as you like.
Pour artichokes and dressing over all and toss to coat.

title: trifle
directions: Mix jello according to package directions.
Allow to partially congeal.
Slice partially thawed strawberries in half (easier to work with this way).
In a large bowl, place a layer of cake (using 1/2 the cake) broken into several (about 10 or 12) pieces. Distribute 1/2 of the strawberries over the cake for the second layer.
Pour 1/2 of the partially congealed jello as the third layer.
Top with 8 ounces of the Cool Whip.
Repeat layers.
Keep in the refrigerator.
